<seg id="b.1CO.1.10" type="verse">And to þe Corynthes he wryteþ, &amp; seiþ, Breþeren, y prey ȝow by þe name of oure Lord Iesu Crist, þat ȝe suggen on þing, &amp; þat þer ben none dyuysyones among ȝow; bote be ȝe parfyt in on wyt &amp; in on cunnynge.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.11" type="verse">For it is y-tolde me þat þer beþ stryuynges among ȝow.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.12" type="verse">&amp; y ne sugge bote þat, þat euerichone of ȝow saiþ, Ich am of Poule; &amp; ych am of Apollo ; &amp; ich am of Petur; &amp; ich am of Crist.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.13" type="verse">Þanne is Crist departed? Wheþer Poule were y-don on þe cros for ȝow? oþer wheþer ȝe weren y-baptyzed in þe name of Poule?
<seg id="b.1CO.1.14" type="verse">&amp; y þonke God þat y ne haue noȝt y-baptyzed none of ȝow,
<seg id="b.1CO.1.15" type="verse">bote Crispen &amp; Gayen; lest eny man sugge, þat ȝe ben y-baptyzed in my name.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.16" type="verse">Safe ich baptyzed Stephanies houshold, &amp; y ne knewe no mo þat ych haue y-baptyzed.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.17" type="verse">For Crist ne sende noȝt me for to baptyze, bote for-to preche þe gospel: noȝt in þe wysdom of wordes, þat þe cros of Crist ne be noȝt y-voyded a-wey.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.18" type="verse">For þe word of þe cros to þilke þat perescheþ is foly; bote to þilke þat beþ y-safed, as to ous, it is þe vertu of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.19" type="verse">For it is y-wryten, Ych wole dystruye þe wysdom of wyse men, &amp; ych wole reprefe þe redynesse of redy men.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.20" type="verse">Where is þe wyse man? where þe makere of þe lawe? where þe getere of þe worlde ? ne haþ noȝt God mad þe wysdom of þis world folye?
<seg id="b.1CO.1.21" type="verse">&amp; for þat þe world in wysdom ne knew not God þorowȝ wysdom, it wes
<seg id="b.1CO.1.22" type="verse">For Iewes secheþ sygnes, &amp; Grekes secheþ wysdom:
<seg id="b.1CO.1.23" type="verse">bote we precheþ Crist þat is y-crucyfyed, þat is sclaundre to
<seg id="b.1CO.1.24" type="verse">þe Iewes, &amp; foly to oþer mysbylefed men; bote to þilke þat beþ y-cleped, boþe Iewes &amp; Grekes, we precheþ Crist þe wysdom of God, and þe vertue of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.25" type="verse">For þat þat is folye of God it is wiser þan men; &amp; þat is febel of God is strengere þan man.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.26" type="verse">&amp;, bryþeren, y-seo ȝe ȝoure clepynge, for nouþer mony wyse men aftur þe flesch, ne mony myȝty men,
<seg id="b.1CO.1.27" type="verse">ne mony nobel men: bote þilke þinges þat beþ foly of þe worlde God ches, to confounde wyse men; &amp; febel þinges of
<seg id="b.1CO.1.28" type="verse">þe worlde God ches, to confounde stronge þinges; &amp; þilke þinges þat weren noȝt nobel, but dispised of þe worlde, God chees, and þilke þinges þat beþ noȝt, to distruye þilke
<seg id="b.1CO.1.29" type="verse">þinges þat beþ: þat eferich flesch ne reioysche hym noȝt in his siȝt.
<seg id="b.1CO.1.30" type="verse">Bote of hym ȝe beþ in Iesu Crist, þat is y-mad wysdom to ous of God, &amp; riȝtfulnesse, &amp; holynesse, &amp; forbuggynge:
<seg id="b.1CO.1.31" type="verse">þat, as it is y-wryte, He þat ioyeþ, ioye he in God.
<seg id="b.1CO.2.10" type="verse">Bote to ous God haþ y-schewed hit by his Spiryt: for þe Spiryt sercheþ alle þinges, ȝe, &amp; þe depe þinges of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.2.11" type="verse">For what man knoweþ þilke þinges þat beþ of men, bote þe spiryt of man, þat is in hym? so þilke þinges þat beþ of God no man knoweþ, bote þe Spiryt of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.2.12" type="verse">&amp; we ne hafeþ noȝt vnderfongen þe spiryt of þis worlde, bote þe spiryt þat is of God; þat we knowen þilke þinges þat beþ y-graunted to ous of
<seg id="b.1CO.2.13" type="verse">God; þe whuche þinges we ne spekeþ noȝt in vntauȝt wordes of mannes wysdom, bote in þe techynge of þe Spiryt, tellynge
<seg id="b.1CO.2.14" type="verse">to spirytual men spirytual þinges: bote þe bestych man ne parceyfeþ noȝt þilke þinges þat beþ of þe Spiryt: for þei ne beþ but folye to hym, &amp; he ne may noȝt vnderstonden, for he is examyned spirytualyche.
<seg id="b.1CO.2.15" type="verse">Bote þe spirytual man demeþ alle þinges, &amp; he ne is noȝt y-demed of no man. For
<seg id="b.1CO.2.16" type="verse">it is y-wryten, Who haþ y-knowe þe wyt of oure Lord, bote þe Spiryt of oure Lord, þat haþ enformed hym? &amp; we habbeþ þe wyt &amp; þe vnderstondynge of Crist.
<seg id="b.1CO.2.1" type="verse">And , bryþeren, whan þat ich com to ȝow, y ne come noȝt yn hyȝenesse of wordis ne of wysdom, schewenge to ȝow þe wytnesse of Crist.
<seg id="b.1CO.2.2" type="verse">For ich demed þat y ne knewe no þing a-mong ȝow, bote Iesu Crist y-crucifyed.
<seg id="b.1CO.2.3" type="verse">And ich wes a-mong ȝow in infirmyte, &amp; in gret drede, &amp; in quakynge.
<seg id="b.1CO.2.4" type="verse">&amp; my word &amp; my predicacioun ne wes noȝt in semynge wordis of mannes wysdom, bote in schewynge of þe spiryt &amp;
<seg id="b.1CO.2.5" type="verse">of vertu: þat ȝoure feiþ ne be noȝt in mannes wysdom, bote in þe vertu of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.2.6" type="verse">&amp; we spekeþ wysdom a-mong parfyt men: bote non wysdom of þis worlde, ne of þe princys of þis
<seg id="b.1CO.2.7" type="verse">world þat beþ destruyed: bote we spekeþ þe wysdom of God in mysterie þat is y-hud, þe whuche wysdom God ordeynyd
<seg id="b.1CO.2.8" type="verse">byfor þe worldes to oure ioye: þe whuche wysdom non of þe princes of þis worlde knew: for ȝif þei hadden y-knowe, þei
<seg id="b.1CO.2.9" type="verse">nolde nefer haue crucyfyed þe Lord of blysse: but as it is
<seg id="b.1CO.3.10" type="verse">And aftur þe grace of God þat is y-granted to me, as a wys buyldere ich hafe y-sett a foundement; bote an oþer buldeþ abofe. Bote loke eferych man how he buyldeþ a-bofe.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.11" type="verse">For no man may setten anoþer foundement þan þat þat is y-set, þat is Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.12" type="verse">&amp; who-efer þat buyldeþ abofe þis foundement gold, oþer selfer, oþer precyous stones, treo , oþer
<seg id="b.1CO.3.13" type="verse">hey , oþer stubbel; eferich mannes werke schal ben openliche y-schewed; &amp; þe day of oure Lord schal declaren it, for in fuyr it schal be schewed; &amp; fuyr schal prefen whuch mannes werk.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.14" type="verse">For whos werk þat is y-buyld a-bofe &amp; dwelleþ stylle, it schal vndurfongen his mede.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.15" type="verse">Bote whos werk branneþ a-wey , he schal suffre harmynge: bote he schal be safed; bote þat schal ben as þoroȝ fuyr.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.16" type="verse">Ne knowe ȝe noȝt þat ȝe beþ Goddes temple, &amp; þe Spiryt of God dwelleþ in ȝow?
<seg id="b.1CO.3.17" type="verse">&amp; who-efer þat defouleþ þe temple of God, God wole destruyen hym: for ȝe beþ þe holy temple of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.18" type="verse">No man bygyle ȝow: ȝef þer seme eny man among ȝow a wys man in þis world, be he y-maad a fool, þat he be a wys man.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.19" type="verse">For þe wysdom of þis world is folye byfore God. For it is y-wryten,
<seg id="b.1CO.3.1" type="verse">And, bryþeren, y ne myȝte noȝt herbyfore speke to ȝow as to spirytual men, bote as to fleschlyche men, &amp; as to smale children in Crist.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.20" type="verse">Ich wole take wyse men in hure folye: &amp; eftsones, God knoweþ þat þe þouȝtes of wyse men beþ veyn.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.21" type="verse">&amp; þerfore no man reioyesche hym-selfen a-mong men. For alle þinges beþ
<seg id="b.1CO.3.22" type="verse">ȝouren; wheþer hit be Poul, oþer Apollo, oþer Petur, oþer þis worlde, oþer lyf , oþer deþ, oþer þinges þat beþ nouþe, oþer þinges þat schuleþ comen heraftur; for alle þinges beþ
<seg id="b.1CO.3.23" type="verse">ȝouren; &amp; ȝe beþ of Crist, &amp; Crist is of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.2" type="verse">Ich ȝef ȝow mylk to drynke, &amp; noȝt mete; for þat tyme ȝe ne myȝte noȝt, ne ȝit now , ȝe ne mowe noȝt;
<seg id="b.1CO.3.3" type="verse">for ȝit ȝe beþ fleschlyche: for whyles þer beþ enuye &amp; stryuynge a-mong ȝow, ne be ȝe noȝt fleschlyche, &amp; walkeþ after þe flesch?
<seg id="b.1CO.3.4" type="verse">For whyles þat on saiþ, Ich am of Poul; &amp; an oþer, Ich am of Apollo; ne be ȝe noȝt men?
<seg id="b.1CO.3.5" type="verse">&amp; what þanne is Apollo? &amp; what is Poul? His serfauntes in whom ȝe habbeþ byleued, &amp; to eferich man as God haþ y-grauntyd .
<seg id="b.1CO.3.6" type="verse">Y plaunted, &amp; Apollo moysted; bote oure Lord ȝefeþ þe waxynge.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.7" type="verse">&amp; þerfore nouþer he þat plaunted is ouȝt, ne he þat moysted; bote he þat ȝefeþ þe waxynge is God.
<seg id="b.1CO.3.8" type="verse">Bote he
<seg id="b.1CO.3.9" type="verse">&amp; we beþ Goddes helperes, &amp; ȝe beþ Goddes erþe-tylyynge, &amp; Goddes buyldynge.
<seg id="b.1CO.4.10" type="verse">medle noȝt wiþ lecchoures, ne wiþ none lecchoures of þis world, ne wiþ coueytous men, ne wiþ rafeneres, ne wiþ hem þat serfeþ mawmetes; for wharto schulde ȝe elles haue y-gon
<seg id="b.1CO.4.11" type="verse">out from þe world: &amp; now ych hafe y-wryte to ȝou þat ȝe ne medle noȝt wiþ hem; &amp; ȝif he þat is y-cleped a broþer of ȝow is a lecchour, oþer a coueytous man, oþer serfynge to mawmetis, oþer a mysseggere, oþer dronkelew man, oþer a rafeyner; ne ete ȝe noȝt wiþ such a manere man.
<seg id="b.1CO.4.12" type="verse">&amp; what is þat to me for-to demen of þilke þinges þat beþ wiþouten-forþ? Ne deme ȝe noȝt of þilke þinges þat beþ wiþinne-forþ?
<seg id="b.1CO.4.13" type="verse">For þilke þat beþ outen-forþ God schal deme. Doþ a-wey þat þing þat is efel from ȝow-selfen.
<seg id="b.1CO.4.1" type="verse">Bote þer is y-herd fornycacyoun a-mong ȝow, &amp; such fornycacyoun as ne is noȝt a-mong mysbylefed men, in so muche þat summe of ȝow hafe his fadur wyf.
<seg id="b.1CO.4.2" type="verse">&amp; ȝe beþ y-blowe wiþ pruyde, &amp; ȝe ne hafeþ y-mad no sorow, þat he be don a-wey from þe myddel of ȝow, þat haþ y-do þis dede.
<seg id="b.1CO.4.3" type="verse">&amp; ich, þat am absent in body &amp; present in spiryt, hafe y-demed
<seg id="b.1CO.4.4" type="verse">as present þilke þat haþ y-don so, in þe nome of oure Lord Iesu Crist, whan ȝe beþ y-gedered to-gedere in my spiryt, wiþ
<seg id="b.1CO.4.5" type="verse">þe vertu of oure Lord Iesu, to take þilke man to Satanas in slauȝt of his flesch, þat þe spiryt be saf in þe day of oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.1CO.4.6" type="verse">Ȝoure ioyynge ne is noȝt good. Ne knowe ȝe noȝt þat a lytel sowrdowȝ schendeþ al-to-geder?
<seg id="b.1CO.4.7" type="verse">Þerfore make ȝe clene ȝoure olde sowrdowȝ, þat ȝe ben a newe spryngenge to-gedere, as ȝe beþ þerf. For Crist is y-offred,
<seg id="b.1CO.4.8" type="verse">oure astur-lomb : &amp; þerfore ete we, not in þe olde sowrdowȝ, ne in sowrdouȝ of malyce, ne of wykkednes, bote in þerfnes of clernes &amp; of trewþe.
<seg id="b.1CO.4.9" type="verse">Y wrot to ȝow in an epystel þat ȝe ne
<seg id="b.1CO.5.10" type="verse">ne spouse-brekeres, ne sodomytes, ne þefes, ne coueytous men, ne dronken men, ne glotones, ne curseres, ne rafeneres, ne schulleþ not owe þe kyngdom of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.11" type="verse">And ȝe weren suche: ȝe , bote ȝe beþ now y-wasche, &amp; ȝe beþ y-halewed, &amp; beþ y-iustyfyed in þe name of oure Lord Iesu Crist, &amp; in þe Spiryt of oure God.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.12" type="verse">Alle þinges beþ lefful to me, bote alle þinges ne beþ noȝt spedful to me. Alle þynges ben lefful to me, bote y ne schal noȝt ben ybrouȝt aȝeyn vnder no mannes power .
<seg id="b.1CO.5.13" type="verse">Mete to þe wombe, &amp; wombe to þe mete: &amp; God wole distruye boþe þe body &amp; þe mete. &amp; þe body ne is noȝt to fornycacyoun, bote to oure Lord: &amp; oure Lord to þe body.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.14" type="verse">&amp; God haþ rered up oure Lord, &amp; he wole areren us up by his verteu.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.15" type="verse">And ne knowe ȝe noȝt þat ȝoure bodyes beþ membres of Crist? schal me take þanne Cristis membres, &amp; make hem þe membres of an hore? God forbede.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.16" type="verse">Ne knowe ȝe noȝt þat he þat draweþ hym to an hore ys y-mad on body wiþ hure? For he seyde, þei schulleþ ben tweyn in on flesch.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.17" type="verse">Bote þilke þat draweþ to God beþ on spirit. Fle ȝe fornycacyoun.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.18" type="verse">Eferech synne þat a man doþ it is wiþ-outen þe body, bote he þat doþ fornycacyoun synneþ in-to his body.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.19" type="verse">Wheþer ȝe ne knowe noȝt þat ȝoure membres beþ þe temple of þe Holy Gost, þat is in ȝou, whom ȝe han of God?
<seg id="b.1CO.5.1" type="verse">And dar þer any of ȝow, þat haþ any þing a-ȝeyn oþer, ben y-demed to-fore wikked men &amp; noȝt to-fore goode men?
<seg id="b.1CO.5.20" type="verse">&amp; ȝe ne beþ noȝt ȝoure owne; for ȝe beþ y-boȝt for a gret prys: &amp; þerfore glorifye ȝe God &amp; bere ȝe hym in ȝoure body.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.2" type="verse">Wheþer ȝe ne knowen noȝt þat goode men habbeþ to demen þis word? &amp; ȝif þis world schal ben y-demed in ȝow, be ȝe noȝt worþi to demen þe leste þinges?
<seg id="b.1CO.5.3" type="verse">Ne knowe ȝe noȝt þat we schulleþ demen angeles?
<seg id="b.1CO.5.4" type="verse">How muche more þanne wordlyche þinges. &amp; þerfore ȝif ȝe habbeþ wordlyche domes a-mong ȝow, þilke þat beþ y-left worþi a-mong ȝou, ordeyneþ hem for to demen .
<seg id="b.1CO.5.5" type="verse">To ȝoure schame y sugge it. Is þer no wys man of ȝow þat may
<seg id="b.1CO.5.6" type="verse">demen by-twene hym &amp; his broþer, bote on broþer styueþ
<seg id="b.1CO.5.7" type="verse">in dom wiþ his broþer, &amp; þis is a-mong mysbylefed men?
<seg id="b.1CO.5.8" type="verse">Bote ȝe doþ wrong in gyle also to ȝoure bryþeren.
<seg id="b.1CO.5.9" type="verse">Wheþer ȝe knowe noȝt þat wykked men ne schuleþ noȝt haue þe kyngdom of heuene? Ne erre ȝe noȝt: for nouþer lecchoures, ne þilke þat serfeþ false goddis,
<seg id="b.1CO.6.10" type="verse">Bote to þilke þat beþ ywedded to-gedere ych comaunde, &amp; not ych, bote oure Lord, þat þe wyf ne departe hure
<seg id="b.1CO.6.11" type="verse">noȝt from hure housbonde, &amp; ȝif heo doþ , dwelle he stille vn-wedded, oþer elles turne heo a-ȝeyn to hure housbonde, &amp; þe housbonde ne lefe noȝt his wyf.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.12" type="verse">To oþer men y seye, &amp; not oure Lord, A man þat haþ a mysbylefyd wyf &amp; heo assenteþ to dwelle stille wiþ hym, ne lefe he noȝt hure.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.13" type="verse">&amp; þe womman þat haþ a mysbylefed man to housbonde þat assenteþ to dwelle wiþ hure, ne lefe heo noȝt hure housbonde.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.14" type="verse">For a mysbylefed man is y-maad holy þoroȝ a feyþful womman, &amp; a mysbyleued womman is y-mad holy þorowȝ a feyþful man: oþer elles ȝoure children weren vnclene; bote now þei beþ holy.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.15" type="verse">&amp; ȝif þilke þat is mysbylefed goþ a-wey, go he a-wey: for in suche nouþer broþer ne suster is soget to þraldam: bote in pes God haþ y-cleped us.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.16" type="verse">&amp; þerfore ȝif þe womman knoweþ þat heo schal safen hure housbonde, oþer þe
<seg id="b.1CO.6.17" type="verse">man knoweþ þat he schal safen his wyf: ryȝt as God haþ departed to eferych man, &amp; as God haþ y-cleped eferich man, so walke he as y teche in alle churches.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.18" type="verse">He þat is circumsidid
<seg id="b.1CO.6.19" type="verse">For circumscycyoun is noȝt, ne þe prepucye nouþer; bote þe kepynges of þe comaundementis of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.1" type="verse">And þo ilke þinges þat ȝe wryten to me, þat it is good for a man þat he ne touche no womman.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.20" type="verse">&amp; eferiche man in þe clepynge þat he is ycleped, duelle he stille to-fore God.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.21" type="verse">Ȝif þou art a serfaunt þat art y-cleped, ne charge þou noȝt; but ȝif þou myȝt be mad fre, vse it þe more.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.22" type="verse">For he þat is y-cleped in oure Lord, he is oure lordes serfaunt &amp; is freman; also he þat is a fre man &amp; y-cleped, he is Cristis serfaunt.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.23" type="verse">Ȝe beþ y-boȝt þorowȝ prys; ne wilne ȝe noȝt to ben y-mad mennes serfauntes.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.24" type="verse">&amp; eferiche man in þat þing þat he is y-cleped broþer, in þat dwelle he stille to-fore God.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.25" type="verse">Of maydenes y ne hafe non commaundement: bote a counseyl ych ȝefe as he þat haþ y-had mercy of God, þat y be trewe.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.26" type="verse">For y trowe þat it be good for þe nede þat is nouþe, &amp; þat it is good to a man for-to be so.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.27" type="verse">Bote ȝif þou art y-bounden to þi wyf, ne seche þou noȝt to ben vnbounden. Ȝif þou art vnbounden, ne wilne þou noȝt to sechen a wyf.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.28" type="verse">&amp; ȝif þou takest þe a wyf, þou ne synnest noȝt; &amp; ȝif a mayde be y-wedded, heo ne synneþ nouþer. Naþeles suche schulleþ haue tribulacyoun of hure flesch: bote y spare ȝow.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.29" type="verse">&amp; bryþeren, y sey to ȝow þese þinges, tyme is schort; an oþer is, þilke þat habbeþ wyfes , ben þei, as þouȝ þei ne hadden none
<seg id="b.1CO.6.2" type="verse">Bote, for fornycacioun, eferich man hafe his wyf, &amp; eferiche womman hure
<seg id="b.1CO.6.30" type="verse">wyfes; &amp; þilke þat wepeþ, as þilke þat wepeþ noȝt; &amp; þilke þat ioyeþ, as þilke þat ioyeþ noȝt; &amp; þilke þat buggeþ, as
<seg id="b.1CO.6.31" type="verse">þilke þat oweþ no þing; &amp; þilke þat vseþ þis worlde, as þauȝ þei ne vsed it noȝt: for þe fygure of þis worlde passeþ forþ.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.32" type="verse">&amp; ych wole þat ȝe ben wiþ-outen bysynesse of þe worlde. He þat haþ no wyf þenkeþ whuche þinges beþ of God, &amp; how
<seg id="b.1CO.6.33" type="verse">he schal plese God : but he þat haþ a wyf is bisy aboute þinges þat beþ of þe worlde, &amp; how he schal plese his wyf, &amp; so he is departed.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.34" type="verse">&amp; a womman þat is a mayden &amp; vnwedded þinkeþ whuche þinges beþ of God, &amp; þat heo be holy in body &amp; in spiryt: but heo þat is y-wedded þynkeþ þinges þat beþ of þe worlde, &amp; how heo schal plesen hure housbonde.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.35" type="verse">But þese þinges y sey to ȝow for ȝoure profyte; noȝt þat y þrowe to ȝow a gren, but for þat þing þat is honest, &amp; þat it ȝefe ȝow myȝt to knowe wiþ-outen lattynge to bysechen oure Lord.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.36" type="verse">&amp; he þat troweþ þat me holdeþ hym an efel man for his mayde, þat heo is ouer-waxe, &amp; it mote be so: þat he haþ wylle to don do he; for þouȝ he be wedded, heo ne synneþ noȝt.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.37" type="verse">&amp; he þat haþ sadlyche y-stabled in his herte, noȝt hafynge nede, but power of his wylle, &amp; haþ y-demed in his herte to kepen his mayde, he doþ wel.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.38" type="verse">&amp; he þat maryeþ his mayde doþ wel also; &amp; he doþ betere þat maryeþ hure noȝt.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.39" type="verse">Also longe as a wommannes housbonde lyfeþ, heo is y-bounde to þe lawe; bote ȝif hure housbonde dye, heo is delyfered from þe lawe of hure housbonde: be heo y-wedded to whom heo wole, bote onlyche in God.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.3" type="verse">&amp; þe housbonde ȝelde his dette to his wyf; &amp; þe womman also to hure housbonde.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.40" type="verse">Bote heo is muche more betere ȝef heo dwelle stille so, aftur my counseyl: &amp; y trowe þat ych haue þe Spiryt of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.4" type="verse">Þe womman ne haþ no power of hure owne body, bote þe housbonde haþ: ne þe housbonde ne haþ no power of his owne body, bote þe womman haþ.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.5" type="verse">Ne bygyle ȝe noȝt to-gedere, but it be to a certeyn tyme of ȝoure boþe assent, þat ȝe ben occupyed in preyynge, &amp; afturward turne ȝe aȝeyn to þe same doynge, þat þe defel ne tempte ȝow noȝt for ȝoure in-contynence.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.6" type="verse">Bote þese þinges y sugge to ȝow ȝefynge ȝou lefe, &amp; noȝt comaundynge.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.7" type="verse">For ich wole þat alle men ben as ich myselfe. Bote eferyche man haþ a propre ȝifte of God, on man so, &amp; an oþer man so.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.8" type="verse">&amp; y seye to þilke þat beþ vn-weddyd &amp; to wydewes, It is good for hem to ben so, ȝif þei dwellen stille as ych do.
<seg id="b.1CO.6.9" type="verse">Bote ȝif þei mowe noȝt ben contynent, ben þei y-wedded: yt is betur to ben y-wedded þan to ben y-brent.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.10" type="verse">y-mad for þe womman, bote þe womman for þe man: &amp; þerfore þe womman schal haue an helyng on hure hed, for angeles.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.11" type="verse">Naþeles nouþer man wiþ-oute womman, ne womman
<seg id="b.1CO.7.12" type="verse">For riȝt as womman is man, riȝt so man is þorowȝ womman; &amp; alle þei beþ of God.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.13" type="verse">Deme ȝe ȝow-selfe: wheþer it byseme a womman vnkefered to preyen to God?
<seg id="b.1CO.7.14" type="verse">Þe kynde of hem techeþ ȝow: &amp; ȝif
<seg id="b.1CO.7.15" type="verse">a man norsche his her, it is schenschype to hym; bote ȝif a womman norsche hure her, it is worschupe for hure: for heres beþ y-ȝeuen to hure for hure keferynge.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.16" type="verse">And ȝif þer be any of ȝow a stryfer, we ne hafeþ no suche custom, ne Goddes churche nouþer.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.17" type="verse">&amp; þese þinges y bydde ȝow, noȝt preysynge , þat ȝe comeþ to-gedere in þe churche.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.18" type="verse">Ich heere þat þer be dissensyones a-mong ȝow, and a party y trowe it.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.19" type="verse">For it byhofeþ þat þer ben heresyes a-mong ȝow, þat þilke þat beþ apprefed men a-mong ȝow ben openlyche y-schewed.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.1" type="verse">,
<seg id="b.1CO.7.20" type="verse">And þerfore whan ȝe comeþ to-gedere in-to on, now it falleþ
<seg id="b.1CO.7.21" type="verse">noȝt for ȝow to eten oure Lordes soper : for eferich man takeþ byfore his soper for-to eten; &amp; on is an-hungred, &amp; anoþer is dronken.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.22" type="verse">Wheþer ȝe ne hafeþ none houses to eten in &amp; drynken in ? oþer ȝe dispiseþ Godes churche, &amp; schendeþ þilke þat haueþ none houses? What schal ich seye to ȝow? Ich preyse ȝow, bote in þis ich preyse ȝow noȝt.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.23" type="verse">And ich hafe vnderfongen of oure Lord þat ich hafe y-take to ȝow: for oure Lord Iesus in þat nyȝt þat he was y-take toke bred;
<seg id="b.1CO.7.24" type="verse">&amp; dude þankynges to God, &amp; brake it, &amp; seyde, Take ȝe, &amp; ete ȝe: þis is my body þat schal be take for ȝou: makeþ þis in mynde of me.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.25" type="verse">Also aftur þat he had souped he toke þe cuppe, &amp; seyde, Þis cuppe is a newe testament in my blod: makeþ þis, as ofte as ȝe drynkeþ, in mynde of me.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.26" type="verse">For as ofte syþes as ȝe eteþ þis bred, &amp; drynkeþ þis cuppe, ȝe schulen schewen þe deþ of oure Lord forto þat he come.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.27" type="verse">&amp; so who-euere þat eteþ þis bred or drynkeþ þe cuppe of oure Lord vnworþylyche , he schal be gulty of oure Lordes body &amp; his blood.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.28" type="verse">And þerfore prefe a man hym-selfe, &amp; so ete he of þis bred, &amp; drynke he of þis cuppe.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.29" type="verse">For he þat eteþ &amp; drynkeþ vnworþiliche, eteþ &amp; drynkeþ dom to hymselfe, noȝt demynge oure Lordes body.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.2" type="verse">Be ȝe my foleweres, as ych am Cristis folewere. And my bryþeren, y preyse ȝow, for in alle þinges ȝe hafeþ mynde of me; &amp; riȝt so as ych ȝefe ȝou my comaundementis, so ȝe holdeþ hem.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.30" type="verse">&amp; among ȝow þer
<seg id="b.1CO.7.31" type="verse">&amp; ȝif we demen ous-selfe, þanne ne schulde we noȝt ben y-demed.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.32" type="verse">But whyles þat we beþ y-demed of oure Lord , we beþ a-mendyd, þat we ne be noȝt y-dampned wiþ þis world.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.33" type="verse">And þerfore, breþeren, whan ȝe comeþ for-to eten, abyde ȝe togydere eferichone oþer.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.34" type="verse">&amp; ȝif þat any man be an-hungred, ete he at home, þat ȝe ne come noȝt to-gedere in-to dom. Oþer þinges y wole ordeyne whanne þat y come my-selfen.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.3" type="verse">And ych wole þat ȝe knowen, þat þe hed of eferych womman is a man; &amp; þe hed of eferich man is Crist; &amp; þe hed of Crist is God.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.4" type="verse">Eferich man þat preyeþ oþer prophecyeþ wiþ a kefered hed, he defouleþ his hed.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.5" type="verse">Bote eferech womman þat preyeþ oþer prophecyeþ wiþ hed vnheled, defouleþ hure hed: for it is al on as þouȝ he were balled.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.6" type="verse">For ȝif a womman be noȝt y-kefered, be heo y-dodded: &amp; ȝif it be foul for a womman to ben y-dodded oþer balled, wrye heo hure hed.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.7" type="verse">But a man ne schal noȝt wrye his hed, for he is þe ymage &amp; þe ioye of God: &amp; þe womman is þe ioye of a man.
<seg id="b.1CO.7.8" type="verse">For þe man ne is noȝt of
<seg id="b.1CO.7.9" type="verse">womman, bote þe womman is of man: for man ne is noȝt
<seg id="b.1CO.8.10" type="verse">men; to an-oþer man werchynge of vertues; to an-oþer prophecye; to an-oþer discrecyoun of spirytes: to an-oþer dyuerse
<seg id="b.1CO.8.11" type="verse">kyndes of langages; to an-oþer interpretacyoun of wordis: and alle þese þinges wercheþ on Spiryt, departynge to dyuerse men as he wole hym-self.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.12" type="verse">And ryȝt as þe body is on, &amp; haþ many membres, &amp; þouȝ þe membres ben many, ȝit þei beþ alle on body; riȝt so Crist.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.13" type="verse">For in on spiryt alle we beþ y-baptyzed into on body, boþe Iewes &amp; oþer Gentyles, and serfauntes &amp; freo men: &amp; alle we haueþ y-drunke of on Spiryt.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.14" type="verse">&amp; þe body ne is noȝt for on membre, bote many membres.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.15" type="verse">&amp; ȝif þe fot seiþ, Y ne am noȝt þe hond, y ne am noȝt of þe body; ȝet he is ner-þe-latere of þe body.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.16" type="verse">&amp; ȝif þe ere seiþ, For y ne am noȝt þe yȝe, y ne am noȝt of þe body; he ne is nefer-þelatere of þe body.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.17" type="verse">Ȝef al þe body were yȝe , where were þe
<seg id="b.1CO.8.18" type="verse">Bote now God haþ y-set þe membres eferychone of hem in þe body, as he wole hym-selfen.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.19" type="verse">&amp; ȝif alle þe membres weren on membre, where were þe body?
<seg id="b.1CO.8.1" type="verse">Of spirytual þinges, my breþeren, y ne wole noȝt þat ȝe ben vnknowynge.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.20" type="verse">Bote now þe membres beþ many, bote þe body ne is but on.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.21" type="verse">And þe yȝe ne may not seye to þe hond, Me nedeþ noȝt þyne workus : ne þe hed to þe feet, Ȝe ne beþ noȝt nedeful to me.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.22" type="verse">Bote þilke membres of
<seg id="b.1CO.8.23" type="verse">þe body þat semeþ most febel, þei beþ most nedful: &amp; þilke membres þat semeþ us most vnnobel of þe body, aboute hem we doþ most worschupe; &amp; þilke membres þat beþ most inhonest,
<seg id="b.1CO.8.24" type="verse">to hem we doþ most honestee; for oure honeste membres ne haueþ nede of no þing: bote God haþ y-tempred þe body, ȝefynge to hym þat fayled ouȝt þe more worschupe;
<seg id="b.1CO.8.25" type="verse">þat þer be no debate in þe body, bote þat alle þe membres ben bysy eferichone for oþer.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.26" type="verse">And ȝif any membre suffre any þing, suffren alle þe membres to-gedere; oþer ȝif on membre ioye, ioyen alle þe membres to-gedere.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.27" type="verse">&amp; ȝe beþ Cristis body, &amp; membres of a membre.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.28" type="verse">And God haþ y-put in his churche, furst sum men aposteles, in þe secunde place prophetes, in þe þridde techeres, seþþe vertues, seþþe graces of helynge men, helpynges, gouernynges, dyuerse kyndes of langages, interpretacyons of wordys.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.29" type="verse">Wheþer alle ben aposteles? oþer alle
<seg id="b.1CO.8.2" type="verse">For ȝe wyteþ wel þat whylys ȝe weren mysbyleued, as ȝee weren y-lad, ȝe wenten to dombe mawmetes.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.30" type="verse">prophetes? oþer alle techeres? oþer alle vertues? wheþer alle men han grace to hele men? wheþer alle men speken dyuerse langages? wheþer alle men maken interpretacyoun of wordys? Folewe ȝe þe betre ȝiftes of grace.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.31" type="verse">&amp; ȝit y wole schewe ȝow a more excellent weye.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.3" type="verse">And þerfore y certefye ȝow, þat no man spekynge in þe spiryt of God seiþ, A-cursed Iesu; &amp; no man may seye, Oure Lord Iesus, bote it be in þe Holy Spiryt.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.4" type="verse">And þer ben dyuerse graces, bote it is al on Spiryt.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.5" type="verse">And þer ben dyuerse seruynges, bote it is al on Lord.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.6" type="verse">And þer ben dyuerse manere werchynges, bote it is on God, þat worcheþ alle þinges in alle þinges.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.7" type="verse">&amp; to eferich man þer is y-graunted a schewynge of þe spiryt to profyte.
<seg id="b.1CO.8.8" type="verse">To on man þer is y-graunted speche of wysdom þoroȝ þe Spiryt; to anoþer man
<seg id="b.1CO.8.9" type="verse">speche of kunnynge þoroȝ þe same Spiryt; to anoþer man feiþ in þe same Spiryt; to an-oþer man grace of helynge
<seg id="b.1CO.9.10" type="verse">Bote whanne þat comeþ þat is parfyt, þanne it schal ben voyded þat þinge þat ne is bote a party.
<seg id="b.1CO.9.11" type="verse">Whan y was a lytel chylde, I spak as a lytel chyld, &amp; y þouȝte as a lytel child, &amp; y safered as a lytel chyld: bote whenne y was man, y voyded a-wey þilke þinges þat weren of childhode.
<seg id="b.1CO.9.12" type="verse">We seþ now þorowȝ a myrour in derknesse, bote þanne we schulen sen facé to face. Now y knowe a partye, bote þanne y schal knowe ryȝt as y am y-knowe my-selfe.
<seg id="b.1CO.9.13" type="verse">&amp; now dwelleþ þes þinges, feiþ, hope, &amp; charite; bote þe grettest of þese is charyte.
<seg id="b.1CO.9.1" type="verse">Ȝef þat y speke wiþ mennes tunges oþer wiþ aungeles tunges, &amp; y ne hafe noȝt charyte , y am y-mad as bras þat souneþ, oþer a cymbal þat souneþ.
<seg id="b.1CO.9.2" type="verse">&amp; ȝef y haue eueriche prophecye, and knowe alle pryuetees, &amp; ȝif y haue euery cunnynge &amp; euery feiþ, so þat y mowe mefen hulles from hure places, ȝif y ne hafe no charite, y ne am noȝt.
<seg id="b.1CO.9.3" type="verse">And ȝif y dele al my catel in-to pore mennes lyflode, &amp; ȝefe my body to brenne, &amp; y ne hafe no charite, it profyteþ me no þing.
<seg id="b.1CO.9.4" type="verse">Charite is pacyent &amp; benygne; charite ne hateþ no man,
<seg id="b.1CO.9.5" type="verse">ne doþ not wykkedlyche, ne is not y-blowe wiþ pruyde; he ne is not coueytous, he ne secheþ noȝt his owne þinges, he ne
<seg id="b.1CO.9.6" type="verse">is noȝt y-wraþþed, he ne þenkeþ non yuel, ne ioyeþ noȝt up-on
<seg id="b.1CO.9.7" type="verse">wykkednesse, bote ioyeþ to trewþe; alle þinges he suffreþ, alle þinges he byleueþ, alle þinges he hopeþ, alle þinges he abydeþ.
<seg id="b.1CO.9.8" type="verse">Charite ne falleþ nefer a-wey: wheþer þat prophecyes schuleþ ben voydyd a-wey , oþer langages schulen cessen, oþer cunnynge schal be destroyed.
<seg id="b.1CO.9.9" type="verse">For a party we knoweþ, &amp; a party we prophecyeþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.10" type="verse">&amp; ȝef we seye þat we ne haueþ noȝt y-synned, we makeþ hym a gabbere, &amp; his word ne is noȝt dwellynge in ous.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.10" type="verse">If þat we seye we synned nouȝt, we make him a lyere, &amp; his word is not in vs.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.1" type="verse">The lyf þat was wiþ-outen ende fro þe bygynnynge, þe whuche we herde, and wiþ oure eyȝen sawe, þat we byholde, &amp; oure hondis him handlede, of þe whuche word of lyfe we haue drawe,
<seg id="b.1JO.1.2" type="verse">&amp; we him sawe, &amp; bere wittnes, &amp; schewe vnto ȝow þe lyf euerelastynge (þat is, Crist Godis sone) þat was wiþ þe Fadur &amp; to us apperud:
<seg id="b.1JO.1.2" type="verse">honden habbeþ y-touched of þe word of lyf, &amp; þe lyf was openlyche y-schewed, &amp; we han y-seyen it, &amp; we bereþ wytnesse þer-of, &amp; we scheweþ to ȝow an eferlastynge lyf þat
<seg id="b.1JO.1.3" type="verse">was at þe Fader, &amp; haþ appered to ous; &amp; þat þing þat we habbeþ y-seye and y-herd we scheweþ to ȝow, þat ȝe han feloschype wiþ us : &amp; þat þe felauschype be wiþ þe Fader &amp; Iesu Crist his sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.3" type="verse">þat we haue herde &amp; seyne we schewe it vn-to ȝow, þat ȝe mowe haue felowschupe wiþ vs, &amp; þat oure felowschepe be wiþ þe Fadur and wiþ his sone Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.4" type="verse">&amp; þis haue we wryte vnto ȝow þat ȝe make ioye, &amp; þat ȝoure ioye be fulle.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.4" type="verse">And we wryteþ þese þinges to ȝow, þat ȝe ioyen, &amp; þat ȝoure ioye be ful.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.5" type="verse">&amp; þis is oure tellynge þat we han yherd of hym &amp; þat we scheweþ to ȝow: for God is lyȝt, &amp; in hym ne beþ no derknesse.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.5" type="verse">&amp; þis is þe schewynge þat we herde of him, &amp; we schewe it vnto ȝow: for God is þe lyȝt, &amp; þer is in him no manere of derknes.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.6" type="verse">And ȝef we seye þat we han feloschype wiþ hym, &amp; walkeþ in derknesse, we lyeþ, &amp; doþ no trewþe: &amp; ȝef we walkeþ in lyȝt, as he is in liȝt, we han felowschupe to-gydere, &amp; þe blood of Iesu Crist his sone clansyþ ous of eferich synne.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.6" type="verse">If we seye þat we haue felowschepe wiþ him, &amp; we in derknes walke, we lye &amp; doþ not soþfastnes.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.7" type="verse">Soþly if we walken in lyȝte, so as he is in lyȝte, þanne haue we felouschype to-gedur, &amp; þe blode of Iesu Crist his sone makeþ vs clene of alle synne.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.8" type="verse">&amp; ȝef we seye þat we ne haueþ no synne, we bygyleþ ous-selfe, &amp; trewþe ne is noȝt in ous.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.8" type="verse">If þat we seye we haue no synne, we diceyue vs-self, &amp; soþfastnes is not in vs.
<seg id="b.1JO.1.9" type="verse">Ȝef we knowlecheþ oure synnes, he is trewe and ryȝtful to forȝeuen ous oure synnes, &amp; to clensen ous of euerich wikkednesse .
<seg id="b.1JO.1.9" type="verse">If þat we schryue us of oure synnes, God is trewe &amp; ryȝtwyse, &amp; forȝeueþ oure synnes, and he schal make vs clene of alle manere of wickednes.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.10" type="verse">&amp; who þat loueþ his broþer dwelleþ in lyȝt, &amp; in hym is no sclaundre.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.10" type="verse">Whoso loueþ his broþer he dwelleþ in lyȝte, &amp; sclaundur is not in him.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.11" type="verse">Bote who þat hateþ his broþur he is in darknesse, &amp; walkeþ in darknesse, &amp; he ne wot noȝt whyderward he goþ, for derknesse haþ y-blend his yȝen.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.11" type="verse">Soþly whoso hatiþ his broþur, in derknesse he is, &amp; in derknesse he goþ, &amp; wote not whydur he goþ, for derknesse haþ blyndid his eyȝen.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.12" type="verse">My smale chyldren, y wryte to ȝow, for ȝoure synnes beþ forȝeuen to ȝou in þe name of Crist.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.12" type="verse">Sones , I wryte vnto ȝow, þat for his name ȝoure synnes beþ forȝeue ȝow.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.13" type="verse">I write to ȝow, fadrus, for ȝe haue knowen him þat is wiþ-owten ende. I write to ȝow, ȝonge men, for ȝe haue ouercome þe wicked.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.13" type="verse">Y wryte to ȝow, fadres, for ȝe habbeþ y-knowen hym þat is from þe bygynnynge. Y wryte to ȝow, ȝonglynges, for ȝe habbeþ ouercome hym þat is wykked. Y wryte to ȝou, ȝonge chyldren, for ȝe habbeþ y-knowe þe Fader.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.14" type="verse">I wryte to ȝow, ȝonge children, for ȝe haue knowen ȝoure Fadur. I wryte to ȝow, fadrus, for ȝe haue knowynge of God. I write to ȝow, ȝonge men, for ȝe beþ stronge, &amp; Godes dwelleþ in ȝow, &amp; wickednes ȝe haue ouercome.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.14" type="verse">Y wryte to ȝou, fadres, for ȝe habbeþ y-knowen hym þat is from þe bygynnynge. Y wryte to ȝou, ȝonge men, for ȝe beþ stronge, &amp; þe word of God dwelleþ in ȝow, &amp; ȝe habbeþ ouercome hym þat is wykked.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.15" type="verse">And ne loue ȝe noȝt þe world, ne þynges þat beþ in þe world. For who þat loueþ þe world, þe charyte of þe Fader ne is noȝt in hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.15" type="verse">Ne wil ȝe not loue þe worlde, neyþur þe þinges þat in þe worlde beþ. For who-so loueþ þe worlde, þe charite of þe Fadur is not in him.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.16" type="verse">For al þat is in þe worlde, it is a desyre of þe flesche &amp; desyre of eyȝen, &amp; pride of lyf, þe whuche is not of þe Fadur, but of the worlde it is.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.16" type="verse">For al þinge þat is in þe worlde, oþer it is coueytyse of yȝen, oþer coueytyse of þe flesch, oþer pryde of lyuynge, þat ne beþ noȝt of þe Fader, bote of þe world.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.17" type="verse">&amp; þe worlde schal passe wiþ alle his lykynges &amp; desyres: who-so doþ þe wille of God, he dwelleþ wiþ-outen ende.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.17" type="verse">&amp; þe world schal passe, &amp; his coueytyse: bote who þat doþ þe wylle of God he dwelleþ efere-more.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.18" type="verse">My leue sones, it is þe laste oure; &amp; as ȝe haue herd þat Antecrist comeþ; now beþ many Antecristes maked, wherfore we wote þat it is þe laste oure.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.18" type="verse">My smale chyldren, now is þe laste hour; &amp; ȝe habbeþ y-herd þat Antecrist is y-come, &amp; now þer beþ y-mad many Antecristes; &amp; þerfore we wyteþ þat þis is þe laste houre.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.19" type="verse">From ous þei passeden, bote þei ne were noȝt of ous; for ȝef þei hadden y-ben of ous, þei wolden haue dwelled stylle wiþ ous: bote in þis it is openlyche y-schewed þat þei beþ noȝt of ous.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.19" type="verse">Þei ȝede forþ fro vs, but þei were not of vs; for soþly hadde þei ben of vs, soþly þei had dwellid wiþ us: but þat þei schul mow be knowen, for þei ne beþ not alle of us.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.1" type="verse">My children, þis I write to ȝow, þat ȝe synne not. But whoso-euere haþ synned, we haue Iesu Crist oure ryȝtwyse avocat byfore þe Fadur:
<seg id="b.1JO.2.1" type="verse">My smale chyldren, þese þynges y wryte to ȝou, þat ȝe synne noȝt. And ȝef þat eny man synneþ, we haueþ an
<seg id="b.1JO.2.20" type="verse">Bote
<seg id="b.1JO.2.20" type="verse">But ȝe haue ennoyntynge of þe Holy Goste, &amp; alle þinges ȝe haue knowen.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.21" type="verse">I wrote not þis to ȝow as vnto hem þat knewe not soþfastnesse, but as to hem þat knewe it, and wherfore al lesynge is not of soþfastnes.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.21" type="verse">Y ne haue noȝt y-wryte to ȝou as to hem þat knoweþ noȝt þe trewþe, bote as to hem þat knoweþ þe trewþe, &amp; for þat eueryche lesyng ne is noȝt of trewþe.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.22" type="verse">Who is a lyer, bote he þat seiþ þat Iesu ne is noȝt Crist? He is Antecrist, þat denyeþ boþe þe Fader &amp; þe Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.22" type="verse">Who is a lyere, but he þat denyeþ þat Iesus is Crist? He þis is Antecriste, þat denyeþ þe Fadur &amp; þe Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.23" type="verse">Alle þat denyeþ þe Sone, denyeþ þe Fader (þat is, he denyeþ þat he is a fader, for no fader may be wiþ-outen a sone or a chylde) ; who-so is a-knowe þe Fader, he is a-knowe þe Sone; &amp; whoso is a-knowe þe Sone, a Fader he haþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.23" type="verse">For who þat denyeþ þe Sone, he ne haþ noȝt þe Fader; &amp; who þat knowlecheþ þe Sone, he haþ þe Fader.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.24" type="verse">&amp; leteþ þat dwelle stille in ȝow þat ȝe habbeþ y-herd from þe bygynnynge, ȝe schulen dwelle boþe in þe Sone &amp; in þe Fader.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.24" type="verse">Þat at ȝe fro þe bygynnynge haue herde, in ȝow mote it dwelle. Ȝif it dwelle in ȝow þat ȝe fro þe bygynnynge haue herde, þan ȝe schul dwelle in þe Fader &amp; in the Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.25" type="verse">&amp; þis is þe byheste þat he haþ byhoten ȝow, þat he wol ȝeuen ȝow an eferlastynge lyf.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.25" type="verse">&amp; þis is þe byheste þat þe Sone haþ byhette ȝow, lyf euere-lastynge (þat is, of Criste) .
<seg id="b.1JO.2.26" type="verse">Þese þinges ich haue y-wryte to ȝow, of þilke þat bygyleþ ȝow.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.26" type="verse">Þise þinges I wryte vnto ȝow of hem þat deceyue ȝow.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.27" type="verse">&amp; ȝee þe ennoyntynge þat ȝe toke of him, it mote dwelle in ȝow. &amp; ȝe ne haue not nede þat eny teche ȝow: but his ennoyntynge techiþ ȝow of alle þinges, it is soþ, &amp; it is no lesynge. &amp; as he haþ tauȝte ȝow, so dwelleþ þerinne.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.27" type="verse">&amp; þilke anoyntynge þat ȝe han vnderfongen of hym dwelle stylle in ȝow, &amp; ȝe ne haueþ no nede þat any man teche ȝow; bote riȝt as þe anoyntynge of hym techeþ ȝou in alle þinges, &amp; it is trewe, &amp; no lesynge, &amp; riȝt so as ich haue y-tauȝt ȝow, dwelle ȝe in hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.28" type="verse">&amp; whanne þat ȝe schal appere, haue we feyþfulnes, &amp; be we not confoundid of him in his comynge.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.28" type="verse">And now, my smale children, dwelle ȝe in hym; þat, whan he appereþ, we han a trust, &amp; þat we ne ben noȝt y-schend of hym in his comynge.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.29" type="verse">&amp; as ȝe wyteþ þat he is ryȝtful, so wyte ȝe wel þat he þat doþ riȝtfulnesse is y-boren of hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.29" type="verse">If ȝe wite þat he is ryȝtwyse, wete ȝe forsoþe þat alle þat doþ ryȝtwysnesse is bore of him.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.2" type="verse">aduoket to-fore þe Fadur, Iesu Crist þat is riȝtful: &amp; he is þe forȝeuenesse of oure synnes; noȝt onlyche for ouren, bote for al þe worldes.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.2" type="verse">&amp; he is socoure and helpe for oure synnes; soþly not only for oures, but also for al þe worlde, þat wiþ trewe trowþe wile to him clepe.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.3" type="verse">And in þat we wote þat we haue knowen him, if þat we kepe his biddynges.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.3" type="verse">And in þis we wyteþ wel þat we haueþ y-knowen hym, ȝef we kepeþ his hestes.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.4" type="verse">Whoso seiþ þat he knoweþ God, &amp; kepeþ not his biddynges, he is a lyere, &amp; soþfastnes is not in him.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.4" type="verse">Who þat seiþ þat he knoweþ God, and kepeþ noȝt his hestes, he is a lyer, &amp; trewþe ne is noȝt in hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.5" type="verse">Bote who þat kepeþ his word, soþlyche, in hym is þe charyte of God parfyt. &amp; in þis we
<seg id="b.1JO.2.5" type="verse">Soþly whoso-euere kepuþ his word, verreyly, in him is Godes charite parfyte. &amp; in þat we knowe þat we dwelle in him, if þat we be parfyte in him.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.6" type="verse">knoweþ þat we beþ in hym: &amp; who þat seiþ þat he dwelleþ
<seg id="b.1JO.2.6" type="verse">Whoso seiþ þat he in him dwelleþ, as he haþ go mote he go.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.7" type="verse">My dere frendes, I wryte vnto ȝow not
<seg id="b.1JO.2.7" type="verse">My dereste breþeren, y ne wryte noȝt to ȝou a newe comaundement, bote an old comaundement þat ȝe hadden from þe bygynnyng: þe olde comaundement is þe word þat ȝe haueþ y-herd.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.8" type="verse">&amp; y write to ȝow a newe comaundement, þat is trewe boþe in hym &amp; in ȝow; for derknesse beþ now y-passed, &amp; verrey lyȝt schyneþ nowþe.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.8" type="verse">eftsones I write a newe mawndement to ȝow here, þat is soþ in him &amp; in ȝow; for derkenesse now beþ passed, and now schyneþ verrei lyȝt.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.9" type="verse">Whoso seiþ þat he is in lyȝte, &amp; hatuþ his broþur, he is in derkenes.
<seg id="b.1JO.2.9" type="verse">Who þat seiþ þat he is in lyȝt, &amp; hateþ his broþer, he is ȝet in darknesse.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.10" type="verse">And in þis beþ openlyche y-schewed boþe Goddes chyldren &amp; þe deueles children: euerich man þat is noȝt riȝtful ne is noȝt of God, ne he þat loueþ noȝt his broþer.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.10" type="verse">In þis beþ Godes sones schewed &amp; þe fendus sones: whoso is not riȝtwyse he is not of God, &amp; he þat loueþ not his broþur.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.11" type="verse">For þis is þe tellynge þat ȝe habbeþ y-herd from þe bygynnynge, þat ȝe louen to-gydere: noȝt as Caym þat was wykked &amp; slouȝ his broþer.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.11" type="verse">For þis þe schewynge þe whuche ȝe haue herde fro þe bygynnynge, þat eche of ȝow loue oþur:
<seg id="b.1JO.3.12" type="verse">And herfore he slouȝ hym, for his werkes weren wykked, &amp; his broþeres werkes weren goode.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.12" type="verse">nouȝt as Caym þat of wickednes was, &amp; sleare of his broþur. &amp; for what þing slowe he him? For his dedus were wicked, &amp; his broþeres riȝtwyse.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.13" type="verse">And ne wondre ȝe noȝt þouȝ þe world hate ȝou.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.13" type="verse">Ne wondreþ ȝow nouȝt, breþeren, if þe worlde ȝow hate.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.14" type="verse">For we wyteþ þat we beþ y-translated from deþ to lyf, for þat we loueþ oure breþeren. Who þat loueþ noȝt he duelleþ in deþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.14" type="verse">We wote þat we beþ translatud fro deþ vnto lyf, for þat we loue oure breþeren. He þat loueþ not dwelleþ in deþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.15" type="verse">Euerich man þat hateþ his broþer he is a mansleer: &amp; ȝe wyteþ þat euerich mansleer ne haþ noȝt an euerlastynge lyf dwellynge in hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.15" type="verse">Whosoeuere hateþ his broþer he is a man-sleare: &amp; wyte ȝe þat eche mansleare haþ not lyf euerelastynge in him dwellynge.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.16" type="verse">&amp; in þis we habbeþ y-knowe þe charite of God, for he putte his soule for ous: &amp; we oweþ to putten oure soules for oure breþeren.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.16" type="verse">In þat we haue knowen þe charite of God, for he putte his soule for us: &amp; we owe for oure breþeren to putte oure soules.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.17" type="verse">He þat haþ þe goodes of þis worlde, &amp; seeþ his broþer haþ nede &amp; helpeþ him not, how dwelleþ þe charite of God in him?
<seg id="b.1JO.3.17" type="verse">Who þat haþ þe substaunce of þis world, &amp; seþ his broþer haue nede: ȝef he closeþ his in-wardnesse from his broþer, how dwelleþ þe charite of God in hym?
<seg id="b.1JO.3.18" type="verse">My children, loue we nouȝt worde, neiþer wiþ tunge, but wiþ deede &amp; soþfastnes.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.18" type="verse">My lytul chyldren, ne loue we noȝt in word, ne in tonge; bote in werk &amp; in trewþe.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.19" type="verse">In þat we knowe þat we beþ of soþfastnes, if we amoneste &amp; make meke oure hertes in his syȝte.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.19" type="verse">In þis we knoweþ þat we beþ of trewþe, &amp; in his syȝt we scheweþ
<seg id="b.1JO.3.1" type="verse">Seeþ what charite þe Fadur haþ ȝeuen to us, þat we Godes sones be nemnyd. &amp; we knowe &amp; wite wel, þat þerfore þe worlde knewe ȝow not:
<seg id="b.1JO.3.20" type="verse">For if oure herte reprehende vs nouȝt, God is more þan oure herte, &amp; he knoweþ alle þinges.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.20" type="verse">oure hertes; for ȝef oure herte vndernemeþ ous, God, þat is more þan oure herte, he knoweþ alle þinges.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.21" type="verse">My dere frendus, if oure herte reprehende vs not, we haue feiþfulnes to God;
<seg id="b.1JO.3.21" type="verse">My dereste breþeren, ȝef oure herte vndernymeþ ous not , we han a
<seg id="b.1JO.3.22" type="verse">&amp; what-so-euere we aske of hym, we schal it haue, for þat we kepe his bydynges, &amp; do þe þinges þat beþ plesynge byfore him.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.22" type="verse">truste in God; and what-euere we axeþ of hym, we schuleþ vnderfongen of hym, for þat we kepeþ his hestes, &amp; doþ þilke þinges þat beþ plesynge to-foren hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.23" type="verse">&amp; þat is his comaundement, þat we trowe in þe name of his sone Iesu Crist, &amp; þat we loue echone oþur, as he haþ vs comawndid.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.23" type="verse">&amp; þis is þe comaundement of God, þat we byleuen in þe name of his sone Iesu Crist, &amp; þat we louen togydere, as he haþ y-ȝefen ous a comaundement.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.24" type="verse">&amp; whoso kepeþ his comaundementis in him he dwelleþ, &amp; he in him. &amp; in þat we wote þat he dwelleþ in vs, þorow þe spyryt þat he haþ ȝoue vs.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.24" type="verse">&amp; who þat kepeþ his comaundementys
<seg id="b.1JO.3.2" type="verse">My dere frendes, now we be Godes sones, &amp; ȝit was it not schewid what þat we schul be. Soþly we wote, whan þat he schal appere we schul be lyke vnto him; for we schul se him riȝt as he is.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.2" type="verse">My dereste breþeren, now we beþ Goddes children, bote it is noȝt ȝet y-sene what we schuleþ ben. For we wyteþ wel, whan þat he appereþ we schuleþ be lyche to hym; for we schuleþ y-sen hym riȝt as he is.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.3" type="verse">&amp; echone þat haþ þis lykenesse in him, he halweþ him, so as he is holy.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.3" type="verse">&amp; euerych man þat haþ þis hope haleweþ hym-selfe, riȝt as he is holy.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.4" type="verse">Alle þat doþ synne, he doþ also wickednes: for synne is wickednes.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.4" type="verse">And euriche man þat doþ synne &amp; wikkednesse: he is boþe synne &amp; wykkednesse.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.5" type="verse">&amp; ȝe wyteþ þat he appered to don a-wey synne; &amp; in hym ne is no synne.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.5" type="verse">And wite ȝe þat he appered to do a-wey synne of þe worlde, &amp; no synne is in him.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.6" type="verse">Alle þat in him dwelleþ synneþ nouȝt: &amp; alle þat synneþ seeþ him not, ne knoweþ him nouȝt.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.6" type="verse">&amp; who þat dwelleþ in hym ne synneþ noȝt: &amp; who þat synneþ ne knoweþ noȝt God, ne sey noȝt God.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.7" type="verse">My children, late noone disceyue ȝow: whoso doþ riȝtwisnes he is riȝtwis, as he riȝtwise is:
<seg id="b.1JO.3.7" type="verse">My smale chyldren, no man bygyle ȝow:
<seg id="b.1JO.3.8" type="verse">whoso doþ synne of þe deuel it is; for fro þe bygynnynge þe deuel synneþ. In þat apperud Godes Sone, þat he wolde vndo þe deuelis werkes.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.8" type="verse">who þat doþ riȝtfulnesse is riȝtful, as he is riȝtful : &amp; who þat
<seg id="b.1JO.3.9" type="verse">Alle þat beþ bore of God doþ not synne, for his seed in him dwelleþ: &amp; he may not synne, for of God he is bore.
<seg id="b.1JO.3.9" type="verse">And euerich man þat is y-boren of God ne doþ no synne, for þe seed of God dwelleþ in hym: &amp; he ne may noȝt synne, for he is y-boren of God .
<seg id="b.1JO.4.10" type="verse">&amp; in þat is charite not as we haue loued God, but for þat he first loued vs, &amp; sente his sone an helpe for oure synnes.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.10" type="verse">In þis is charyte, noȝt as þouȝ we haden y-loued God, bote for he loued ous furst, &amp; sende his sne to ben forȝeuenesse of oure synnes.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.11" type="verse">My dere breþeren, if God haue loued vs, &amp; we schulde eche loue oþur.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.11" type="verse">My dereste breþeren, ȝef God loued ous, þanne moten we louen togydere.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.12" type="verse">No man haþ y-sey God: ȝef we loueþ to-gydere, God is in ous, &amp; þe charyte of God is parfyt in ous.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.12" type="verse">No man saw God euere (or, eny tyme) : if we loue to-gidere, God in vs dwelleþ, &amp; his charite is in vs parfyte.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.13" type="verse">In þat we knoweþ þat we in him dwelleþ &amp; he in vs, for of his Spirite he haþ ȝeue vs;
<seg id="b.1JO.4.13" type="verse">In þis we knoweþ þat we dwelleþ in hym, for he haþ y-ȝeuen ous of
<seg id="b.1JO.4.14" type="verse">and we haue seye &amp; bere witnesse, þat þe Fadur sente his sone Saueoure of þe worlde.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.14" type="verse">his Spyryt; &amp; we han y-seyn &amp; bereþ wytnesse, þat þe Fader haþ y-send his sone Sauyour of þe world.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.15" type="verse">Who-euere þat knowlecheþ þat Iesu is Goddes sone, God dwelleþ in hym, &amp; he in God.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.15" type="verse">Whoso is a-knowe þat Iesus is Godes sone, God dwelleþ in him, &amp; he in God.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.16" type="verse">&amp; we haue knowe &amp; we trowe to þe charite þat God haþ in vs. God is charite; &amp; he þat dwelleþ in charite, he dwelleþ in God, &amp; God in him.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.16" type="verse">And we han y-knowe &amp; byleueþ þe charite þat God haþ in ous. God is charite; &amp; who þat duelleþ in charyte dwelleþ in God, &amp; God in hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.17" type="verse">In þat is charite parfyte wiþ vs, þat we haue feiþ in þe day of dome; for ryȝt as he is &amp; we beþ in þis worlde.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.17" type="verse">In þis is charite parfyt in ous, þat we han trust in þe day of dome; for ryȝt as he is we beþ in þis world.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.18" type="verse">Drede is not in charite: but parfyte charite putteþ oute drede, for drede haþ peyne; soþly whoso drediþ, he is not parfite in charite.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.18" type="verse">Drede ne is noȝt in charyte: bote parfyt
<seg id="b.1JO.4.19" type="verse">&amp; þerfore loue we God, for first God loueþ us.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.19" type="verse">And we loueþ God, for he loued ous raþer.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.1" type="verse">My dere frendes, ne trowe ȝe not to eche spyryte, but proue þe spyrytes if þei be of God: for many false prophetes ȝede in-to þe worlde.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.20" type="verse">Ȝef eny man seiþ, þat he loueþ God, &amp; hateþ his broþer, he is a lyere: for he þat loueþ noȝt his broþer þat he seþ, how may he loue God þat he seþ noȝt?
<seg id="b.1JO.4.20" type="verse">Whoso-euere seiþ þat he loueþ God, &amp; hateþ his broþur, he is a lyere: þe whuche soþly loueþ noȝt his broþur whom þat he seiþ, how may he loue God whom þat he seeþ nouȝt?
<seg id="b.1JO.4.21" type="verse">&amp; þat biddinge we haue of God, þat whoso loueþ God, he loueþ his broþer.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.21" type="verse">&amp; þis comaundement we han of God, þat he þat loueþ God loue also his broþer.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.2" type="verse">In þat is þe speryt of God knowen: for eche spyryte þe whuche is a-knowe þat Iesu Criste haþ comen in flesche—þat is, boþe God &amp; man—he is of God.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.2" type="verse">In þis þe spiryt of God is y-knowe: euerych spiryt þat knowlecheþ þat Iesu Crist
<seg id="b.1JO.4.3" type="verse">&amp; eche spirite þat vndoþ Iesu Criste, he is not of God: but þis is Antecrist of þe whuche ȝe haue herde. For he comeþ, &amp; now ryȝt he is in þe worlde.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.3" type="verse">come into flesch he is of God: &amp; euerych spiryt þat vndoþ Crist ne is noȝt of God: &amp; þis is Antecrist, of whom ȝe han
<seg id="b.1JO.4.4" type="verse">My children, ȝe beþ of God, &amp; in him ȝe haue ouercomen: for God is grettere þat is in ȝow þan he þat is in þe worlde.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.4" type="verse">y-herd þat he schal come; &amp; now he is in þe world. Bote my smale chyldren, ȝe beþ of God, &amp; ȝe han ouercome hym: for he þat is in ȝow is gretter þan he þat is in þe world.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.5" type="verse">Þei beþ of þe worlde, &amp; þerfore of þe worlde þei speke, &amp; þe world hem heriþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.5" type="verse">Þei beþ of þis worlde, &amp; þerfore þei spekeþ of þe world, &amp; þe world y-hereþ hem.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.6" type="verse">Bote we beþ of God: &amp; who þat knoweþ God y-hereþ ous; &amp; who þat is noȝt of God he ne hereþ ous noȝt. In þis we han y-knowe þe spiryt of trewþe, &amp; þe spiryt of errour.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.6" type="verse">We beþ of God: whoso kneweþ God hereþ ȝow; he þat is nouȝt of God heruþ ȝow nouȝt. &amp; in þat we knowe þe spirite of soþfastnes &amp; þe spirite of
<seg id="b.1JO.4.7" type="verse">My dere breþeren, loue we us to-gidere: for charite is of God; &amp; eche þat loueþ his broþur of God he is bore, &amp; God he knowiþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.7" type="verse">My dereste breþeren, loue we to-gydere: for charyte is of God; &amp; euerych man þat loueþ is y-boren of God, &amp; knoweþ God.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.8" type="verse">He þat loueþ nouȝt knewe not God: for God is charite.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.8" type="verse">Þilke þat loueþ noȝt ne knoweþ noȝt God; for God is charyte.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.9" type="verse">In þat appered þe charite of God in vs: for he sente his owne sone in-to þe worlde, þat we lyue by him.
<seg id="b.1JO.4.9" type="verse">In þis appered þe charyte of God in ous: for God sende his one bygeten sone in-to þis world, þat we lyfen by hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.10" type="verse">Whoso troweþ in Godes Sone, he haþ þe witnes of God in him. He þat troweþ not in þe Sone he makeþ him a lyere, for he troweþ not in þe witnes þat God witnessiþ of his Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.10" type="verse">Who þat byleueþ in þe Sone, he haþ þe wytnesse of God in hym-self: who þat byleueþ noȝt in þe Sone, he makeþ God a gabbere; for he haþ y-bore wytnesse of his Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.11" type="verse">&amp; þis is þe wytnesse, for God haþ y-ȝeuen ous an euerlastynge lyf, &amp; þis lyf is in his Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.11" type="verse">And þis is þe witnesse, for lyfe euere-lastynge he haþ ȝeue to us, &amp; þat is þe lyfe in his Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.12" type="verse">He þat haþ þe Sone haþ lyfe; whoso haþ not þe Sone (of God) , he haþ not lyfe.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.12" type="verse">Who þat haþ Goddes Sone haþ lyf; and who þat haþ noȝt Goddes Sone ne haþ noȝt lyf .
<seg id="b.1JO.5.13" type="verse">Þese þinges y wryte to ȝow, þat ȝe knowen þat ȝe han an euerlastynge lyf, ȝe þat byleueþ in þe name of Goddes Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.13" type="verse">Þis I wryte vn-to ȝow, to make ȝow to wyte þat ȝe haue lyfe euere-lastynge þat troweþ in þe name of Godes Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.14" type="verse">&amp; þis is þe feiþfulnes þat we haue to God, for what þinge so we vse axse aftur his wille, he hereþ us:
<seg id="b.1JO.5.14" type="verse">&amp; þis is þe trust þat we han to
<seg id="b.1JO.5.15" type="verse">after his wylle, &amp; he wole y-heren ous: &amp; we wyteþ wel þat he hereþ ous what-euere we axen hym, for we han oure axinges þat we axeþ of hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.15" type="verse">&amp; we wote þat he hereþ us, what-so we axe: &amp; we wote þat we haue þe axsynges, þat we
<seg id="b.1JO.5.16" type="verse">He þat wote þat his broþur synneþ synne þat is not to þe deeþ, axse for him, &amp; God schal ȝeue lyfe to him þat synneþ not to þe deeþ. Soþly þer is synne vn-to þe deeþ (þat is, euere contynuynge in sȳnne, &amp; endynge in dispeyre, þat is, wanhope) : none, I sey, prey for him.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.16" type="verse">Who þat knoweþ his broþer synne a synne noȝt to þe deþ, preye he, &amp; þer schal ben y-graunted lyf to hym þat synneþ noȝt to þe deþ. &amp; þer is synne to þe deþ: for þat y seye, no man preye.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.17" type="verse">Eche wickednesse is synne, &amp; it is synne vn-to þe deeþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.17" type="verse">Euerich wykkednesse is synne, &amp; þer is synne þat is noȝt to þe deþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.18" type="verse">We knowe þat eche þat is bore of God (or, þorow God) ne synneþ not—þat is, wilfully in deedly synne—but getynge kepeþ him, &amp; þe wicked toucheþ hym not (þat is, þe yuel spirite ouercomeþ him noȝt) .
<seg id="b.1JO.5.18" type="verse">We knoweþ wel þat euerych man þat is y-boren of God ne synneþ noȝt; bote þe bygetynge of God kepeþ hym, &amp; he þat is wykked ne schal noȝt touchen hym.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.19" type="verse">And we knoweþ wel þat we beþ y-boren of God, &amp; þat al þe world is y-set in hym þat is wykked.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.19" type="verse">We wote þat of God we beþ bore, &amp; alle þe worlde is putte in wickednes.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.1" type="verse">Alle þat troweþ þat Iesus is Criste þorowȝ God he is bore: &amp; eche þat loueþ him þat gate, loueþ him þat of him is bore.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.20" type="verse">&amp; we knoweþ þat Goddes com &amp; haþ y-ȝeuen ous a wytt þat we knowen verrey God, &amp; þat we ben in his verrey Sone. Þis is verrey God, &amp; an euerlastynge lyf.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.20" type="verse">&amp; we wote þat Godes Sone come &amp; ȝaf us witte to knowe verrey God, &amp; þat we be in his verrey Sone, Iesu Criste. He þis is verrey God &amp; lyfe euere-lastynge.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.21" type="verse">My children, kepeþ ȝow fro mawmetrye (and symulacris) .
<seg id="b.1JO.5.21" type="verse">My smale children, kepe ȝe ȝow from mawmetes &amp; symulacris. Here endeþ þe furste part of Johnys pystelys, and þe secounde part bygynneþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.2" type="verse">In þat we knowe þat we loue Godes children, whan whe loue God, &amp; we do his byddynges.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.2" type="verse">In þis we knoweþ þat we loueþ hem þat beþ y-boren of God, when þat we loueþ God, &amp; kepeþ his hestes.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.3" type="verse">&amp; þis is þe charyte of God, þat we kepen his comaundementes: &amp; his comaundementes ne beþ noȝt heuy.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.3" type="verse">Þis is soþly charite of God, þat we kepe his biddynges: &amp; his biddynges ne beþ not greuous.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.4" type="verse">For alle þinge þat is bore of God (or, þorowȝ God) ouercomeþ þe worlde: &amp; þis is þe victory þat ouercomeþ þe worlde, oure feiþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.4" type="verse">For euerych þing þat is y-boren of God ouercomeþ þe world: &amp; þis is þe victorye þat ouercomeþ þe world, oure feiþ.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.5" type="verse">&amp; who ouercomeþ þe world, bote he þat byleueþ þat Iesu is Goddes sone?
<seg id="b.1JO.5.5" type="verse">Who is it þat ouercomeþ þe worlde? noon but he þat trowiþ þat Iesus is Godus sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.6" type="verse">Þes comeþ by þe watyr &amp; þe blod of Iesu Crist; noȝt onlyche in watyr, bote in watyr &amp; in blod. &amp; þe spiryt bereþ wytnesse þat Crist is trewþe.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.6" type="verse">Þis is he þat come by water &amp; blode, Iesus Criste; nouȝt only in water, but in watur &amp; blode. &amp; it is þe spyrite þat beruþ witnes þat Crist is soþfastnes.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.7" type="verse">For þer beþ þre þat ȝeueþ wytnesse in hefne, þe Fader, &amp; þe Sone, &amp; þe Holy Spiryt: &amp; þese þre beþ on.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.7" type="verse">For þre þer beþ þat witnes bere in heuene, þe Fadur, þe Sone &amp; þe Holy Goste: and þes þre beþ one.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.8" type="verse">&amp; þer beþ þre þat ȝeueþ wytnesse in erþe, þe Spyrit, &amp; blod, &amp; watyr: &amp; þese þre beþ on.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.8" type="verse">&amp; þre þer beþ þat ȝeueþ witnes in erþe, Spirite, water, &amp; bloode: &amp; þre beþ one.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.9" type="verse">&amp; ȝef we han vnderfonge þe wytnesse of men, þe wytnesse of God is muche gretter; &amp; þis is þe wytnesse of God, þat is gretter, for he haþ y-bore wytnesse of his owene Sone.
<seg id="b.1JO.5.9" type="verse">Ȝif we take witnes of men, more is þe witnes of God; for þat þe witnes of God þat is more, for he bar witnes of his sone.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.10" type="verse">Of whuche hele þe prophetes enquered &amp; souȝte, þe whuche prophecyed grace þat was to come in vs:
<seg id="b.1PE.1.10" type="verse">Of þe whuche hele prophetes han y-souȝt &amp; y-serched, þat han y-prophecyed of þe grace
<seg id="b.1PE.1.11" type="verse">sechynge in what tyme it schulde syngnyfye; þe sperite of Crist, þat was in hem, schewid hem þat beþ in Cristes passyoun what ioye þei schulde haue aftur.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.11" type="verse">þat is to comen in ȝow: þat telleþ as þe spiryt of Crist haþ y-sygnyfyed to hem þis tyme, furst tellynge þe suffrynges of Crist, &amp; siþþe his blisses þat comeþ aftur.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.12" type="verse">&amp; þei mynystrid vn-to ȝow þe þinges þat now beþ schewyd vn-to ȝow by hem þat haue preched vn-to
<seg id="b.1PE.1.12" type="verse">To whuche prophetes it wes y-told, þat þei ne schulde noȝt to hemselfe,
<seg id="b.1PE.1.13" type="verse">&amp; þerfore cutteþ up þe lendes of ȝoure þouȝt, &amp; beþ sober in alle þinges, &amp; parfyt, &amp; hope ȝe in þat grace þat is y-prefed to ȝow in þe reuelacyown of Iesu Crist;
<seg id="b.1PE.1.13" type="verse">Wherfore drawe uppe ȝoure herte fro wordly lustes, &amp; beþ sobre &amp; parfyte &amp; tristiþ þer-inne, þat is, in schewynge þat grace þat is offrud to ȝou in þe reuelacyon of Iesu Crist;
<seg id="b.1PE.1.14" type="verse">as chyldren of obedyence, noȝt ylyche þe desyres of ȝoure
<seg id="b.1PE.1.14" type="verse">as sones of buxomnes, not lyke to ȝoure firste desyres of ȝoure vnknowynge,
<seg id="b.1PE.1.15" type="verse">but aftir him þat cleped ȝow holy. &amp; be ȝee holy in al ȝoure conuersasyoun;
<seg id="b.1PE.1.15" type="verse">vnkunnyngnesse herbyfore , bote y-lyche hym þat haþ ycleped ȝow þat is holy, þat ȝe ben holy in eueriche conuersacyoun;
<seg id="b.1PE.1.16" type="verse">for it is wretyn, Be ȝee holy, for I am holy.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.16" type="verse">for it is y-wryten, Ȝe schuleþ ben holy, for ych am holy.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.17" type="verse">&amp; if ȝe clepe him Fadur þat, wiþ-oute rewarde-takynge of eny persone, demeþ echone aftur his deedis, leueþ in drede þe tyme of ȝoure duellynge heere:
<seg id="b.1PE.1.17" type="verse">And ȝef ȝe clepeþ hym ȝoure Fader, þat demeþ wiþ-outen vndurfongynge of mennes persones , aftur euerych mannes worchynge, haue ȝe þe conuersacyoun in þe tyme of ȝoure
<seg id="b.1PE.1.18" type="verse">wetynge weel þat ȝee be noȝt bouȝt wiþ roten seluer, or golde þat soone wyle ruste &amp; rote, of ȝoure veyn lyuynge, þat ȝee of ȝoure formere fadres tooken;
<seg id="b.1PE.1.18" type="verse">wonynge in þis worlde in drede: knowynge þat ȝe beþ noȝt for-bouȝt wiþ corruptybel þinges, as gold oþer syluer, out of ȝoure ueyn conuersacyoun of ȝoure fadres tradycyones ;
<seg id="b.1PE.1.19" type="verse">but wiþ þe precyouse blood, as of þe lombe wiþ-outyn filþe þat may not be defoulyd, of Iesu Criste.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.19" type="verse">but þoroȝ þe precyous blod of Crist, þat was as a lomb vndefouled,
<seg id="b.1PE.1.1" type="verse">Petre, þe apostul of Iesu Criste, vn-to þe chosen comelynges þat beþ spred a-brode of Ponti, of Galathie, of Capadocie, of Asye, and Bythune,
<seg id="b.1PE.1.20" type="verse">He was knowen of God or euere þe worlde were maade, &amp; afturwarde he was schewyd in þe laste tymys of þe worlde for ȝowe:
<seg id="b.1PE.1.20" type="verse">wiþ-outen wem, þat was y-knowe by-fore þe ordeynynge
<seg id="b.1PE.1.21" type="verse">of þe worlde, &amp; y-schewed in þese laste tymes for ȝow: þat þoroȝ hym beþ trewe in God þat areryd hym vp from deþ to lyfe, &amp; haþ y-ȝeuen hym an euerlastynge blisse, þat ȝoure
<seg id="b.1PE.1.21" type="verse">þat þorow him ȝee be made trewe in God þat reysid him froo deeþ, &amp; ȝafe to him ioye wiþ-outen ende, þat ȝoure feiþe &amp; ȝoure hope schulde be in God,
<seg id="b.1PE.1.22" type="verse">byleue &amp; ȝoure hope were in God, makynge ȝoure soules chaste in buxomnesse of charyte &amp; in loue of bryþerhede; &amp;
<seg id="b.1PE.1.22" type="verse">chastysynge ȝoure soules in buxomnes of charite, in loue of breþurhede. Loueþ echone oþur bysyli in lowenes of herte:
<seg id="b.1PE.1.23" type="verse">eft-borne nouȝt of sede þat may be roten, but of þat þat may not be roten, þorow þe word of lyuynge God &amp; lastynge wiþ-outen ende.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.23" type="verse">loue ȝe sadlyche to-gydere of a sympel herte: y-bore aȝeyn noȝt of a seed þat is corruptybel, bote in-corruptybel, þorowȝ þe word of þe lyuynge God &amp; dwellynge wiþ-outen ende.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.24" type="verse">For al flesch is but as muke or hey, &amp; alle þe ioye of it is as þe floure of hey or of mucke. Þe hey wexiþ drye, &amp; þe floure þer-of felle:
<seg id="b.1PE.1.24" type="verse">For eferich flesch is gras, &amp; his blisse is þe flour of gras.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.25" type="verse">but soþely þe word of God lasteþ wiþ-outen ende. And þis word it is þat is preched a-monges ȝow.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.25" type="verse">Þe gras waxed drye, &amp; his flour fel adoun: bote Goddes word dwelleþ euermore. And þis is þat word þat is yprechyd to ȝow .
<seg id="b.1PE.1.2" type="verse">aftur þe byfore-knowynge of God þe Fadur, in holynes of spiryte, in buxomnes, in sprenkelynge of þe blode of Iesu Criste. Grace be vn-to ȝow, &amp; pees be multiplied.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.3" type="verse">Blessid be God &amp; þe Fadur of oure Lord Iesu Criste, þe whuche þorow his grete mercy eft-gate us a-ȝeyn in-to a leuynge hope þorow þe resureccyoun of Iesu Criste fro deeþ,
<seg id="b.1PE.1.3" type="verse">Y-blessed be God, þe Fader of oure Lord Iesu Crist, þat of his grete mercy haþ bygeten ȝow aȝeyn in-to on hope by þe
<seg id="b.1PE.1.4" type="verse">arysynge from deþ to lyfe of Iesus Crist, &amp; in-to an herytage incorruptybel, vndefouled, þat may noȝt welewe, þat is y-kept
<seg id="b.1PE.1.4" type="verse">in-to þat heritage þat may not be defouled, ne fordone, but is euerelastynge kept in heuene in ȝow,
<seg id="b.1PE.1.5" type="verse">in hefne in ȝow, þat beþ y-kept in þe vertu of God by feiþ
<seg id="b.1PE.1.5" type="verse">þat in þe vertu of God be keped by feiþ in-to hele maked redy þat on þe laste day schal be schewid;
<seg id="b.1PE.1.6" type="verse">in-to hele þat is redy to ben y-schewed in þe laste tyme; in þe whyche tyme ȝe schuleþ ioyen. And now ȝef it behoueþ
<seg id="b.1PE.1.6" type="verse">in þe whuche ȝe schul make ioye. Now if it byhoueþ ȝow a litil to be heuyed in dyuerse trybulacyons,
<seg id="b.1PE.1.7" type="verse">to sorewe to-gedere a luytel in dyuerse temptacyones, þat þe preuynge of ȝowre feiþ be more precyous þan gold þat is y-prefed in þe fuyr, &amp; be y-founde in-to preysynge &amp; ioye &amp;
<seg id="b.1PE.1.7" type="verse">þat þe prouynge of ȝoure feiþe be more precious þan gold is þat is proued wiþ þe fyre, þat ȝoure feiþe be founde in worschupe &amp; ioye &amp; honoure in-to þe schewynge of Iesu Crist:
<seg id="b.1PE.1.8" type="verse">whom, if ȝe him not see, ȝee loue him: in whom now þat ȝee see not &amp; trowe; whom, whan ȝee schulde him see, he schal be ȝoure ioye, ȝoure comfort þat may not be tolde, &amp; þat schal be glorifyed,
<seg id="b.1PE.1.8" type="verse">worschupe in þe reuelacyoun of Iesus Crist: whom ȝe lofeþ, þat ȝe ne hafeþ noȝt y-seye: in whom ȝe bylefeþ, þat ȝe seþ noȝt; but whan ȝe seþ hym, ȝe schuleþ ioyen in a gladnesse þat
<seg id="b.1PE.1.9" type="verse">bryngynge aȝeyn þe ende of ȝoure feiþe, hele of ȝoure soulis.
<seg id="b.1PE.1.9" type="verse">may noȝt ben y-told, y-gloryfyed, &amp; berynge þe ende of ȝoure feiþ, þe hele of ȝoure soules.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.10" type="verse">&amp; þilke þat weren no pupel, now þei beþ Goddes pepel ; &amp; þilke þat founden no mercy, now þei habbeþ y-founde mercy.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.10" type="verse">þe whuche some tyme were not his folke, now soþely ȝe beþ Godes folke; þe whuche some tyme folwyd not aftur mercy, now soþely ȝe folwe þer-aftur.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.11" type="verse">My deere frendes, I beseche ȝow as comelynge &amp; pilgrymes, þat ȝe
<seg id="b.1PE.2.11" type="verse">My leueste frendes, y pray ȝow as straungeris &amp; pyl grymes, to abstene ȝou from fleschlyche desyres, þat fyȝteþ
<seg id="b.1PE.2.12" type="verse">aȝeyn þe soule; hauynge ȝoure conuersacyoun good among folk; þat, in as myche as men spekeþ yuel of ȝou as of yueldoeris, þei gloryfyen God in þe day of visitacyoun, byholdynge in ȝoure goode werkes.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.12" type="verse">hauynge ȝoure conuersacyoun good a-mong þe gentylis; (þat is, a-mong þe puple þat is not trewely turned, to teche hem boþe in lyuynge &amp; also in ȝoure soule) þat whanne þei speke yuel of ȝow by-hynde ȝow and sey ȝe beþ yuel-doeris, þat þei may byholde ȝoure good deedis, &amp; so þat þei may worschupe God in þe day of vysitynge.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.13" type="verse">&amp; be ȝe soget to euerych creature of
<seg id="b.1PE.2.13" type="verse">Beþ sogettis to alle mannes creature (þat is, to eche man or womman þat is Godes creature) , for God (þat is, for Godes loue in þinges þat beþ lefful wiþ þe wille of God) : oþur to a kynge, as he þat is ouer þe;
<seg id="b.1PE.2.14" type="verse">man, for God : to þe kyng, as to hym þat is abouen; to dukes, as to hem þat beþ ysend from hym in-to veniaunce of wykked doeris &amp; preysynge of goode men.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.14" type="verse">oþur to dukes, as to hem þat beþ fro hem sentte to vengeaunce of yuel doeris, &amp; soþely preysynge to good doaris.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.15" type="verse">For so is þe wille of God, þat ȝe make hem þat doþ wel to wexe dombe (þat is, to holde hem stille wiþ-outen preysynge of here good deede, or, on þis wyse) þat ȝe þat do wel make doue þe vnkonyngenesse of vnwyse men (þat is to mene, þat ȝe þorw ȝoure good lyf &amp; ȝoure good speche &amp; sufferynge ȝyfe suche ensample to þe vnwise recheles, þat þei may take ensample, &amp; so of here yuel wordes &amp; deedus waxe dombe) ;
<seg id="b.1PE.2.15" type="verse">For so it is þe wille of God, þat in ȝoure wel-doynge ȝe maken þe vnkunnyngnesse
<seg id="b.1PE.2.16" type="verse">as ȝe þat beþ fre, &amp; not as þei þat haue filþe of chorlhede (þat is, bondage to synne) , &amp; hauynge frenesse of malice, but as þe seruawntes of God.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.16" type="verse">of vnwyse men waxe doumbe; &amp; be ȝe fre, noȝt hauynge þe fredom of wykkednesse, bote as Goddes seruauntes.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.17" type="verse">Beþ sogettis to alle creatures of mankynde, for loue of God; worschupeþ ȝoure kynges
<seg id="b.1PE.2.17" type="verse">Worschupe ȝe alle men, &amp; loue ȝe breþerhede. Drediþ ȝe God ,
<seg id="b.1PE.2.18" type="verse">&amp; be ȝe sogetis in alle drede to lordes, noȝt onlyche to þilke þat beþ goode &amp; softe, bote also to þilke þat beþ wykked.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.18" type="verse">&amp; her mynystris in alle drede to ȝoure lordes, not only to þe goode &amp; debonere, but also vn-to trwawntes.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.19" type="verse">&amp; þis is a grace, ȝef eny man suffreþ any dysese vnriȝtfullyche for þe knowynge of God.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.19" type="verse">Soþly þis is grace, for who suffereþ for consyence of God (þat is, for þat he wul not do aȝeyn consience, leuynge þe wille of God) heuynesse or wo sufferiþ in vnriȝtwysnesse,
<seg id="b.1PE.2.1" type="verse">&amp; þerfore do ȝee awey euerych wickednesse &amp; gyle &amp; symulacyons &amp; enuyes &amp; alle manere
<seg id="b.1PE.2.1" type="verse">Wherefore doþ a-wey alle malice &amp; alle treccherye &amp; alle feynynges &amp; enuyes &amp; alle bakbytynges,
<seg id="b.1PE.2.20" type="verse">Bote what grace is it, ȝef ȝe sungeþ &amp; suffreþ betynges? , þis is a grace to-fore God.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.20" type="verse">þe whuche is grace, if þat ȝe synne &amp; þerfore be smeten in þe necke, ȝe suffre it (&amp; þat riȝtwysly) . But if þat ȝe do wel &amp; þanne paciently suffre (heuynesse &amp; wronges) , þis is grace a-nentis God (þat is, þat grace ȝe haue of God) .
<seg id="b.1PE.2.21" type="verse">&amp; soþely here-to ȝe ben clepid: for Crist sufferid for ȝow, leeuynge ensample þat ȝe folowe his trace:
<seg id="b.1PE.2.21" type="verse">For in þis ȝe beþ y-cleped: for Crist suffrede for ous,
<seg id="b.1PE.2.22" type="verse">leuynge to ȝou ensaumple, þat ȝe swen his steppis: þat dide
<seg id="b.1PE.2.22" type="verse">þat neuere dide synne, ne neuere was trecherie in his mouþe founde:
<seg id="b.1PE.2.23" type="verse">non synne, ne non gyle was y-founde in his mouþ: &amp; whan men cursed hym, he ne cursed noȝt aȝeyn; &amp; whan he suffred, he ne þreted no man, bote he toke hymselfe to þilke
<seg id="b.1PE.2.23" type="verse">þe whuche whan he was mysseyde, he mysseyde not a-ȝeyn; whan þat he schulde suffre, he curside not aȝeyn ; he soþly tooke him-self to þe iuge þat demyd him vnriȝtwisly;
<seg id="b.1PE.2.24" type="verse">þat demed hym vnriȝtfulliche; &amp; he bar oure synnes in his body on þe tre; &amp; þoroȝ his blood we beþ y-heled .
<seg id="b.1PE.2.24" type="verse">þe whuche bar oure synnys in his body (peyne, wowndes &amp; wo, þat he for oure synne suffrede) up-on þe rode-tre: þat we to synnys schulde be de de, &amp; soþly lyue riȝtwisly: þorow whos peyne ȝee beþ helud.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.25" type="verse">&amp; ȝe weren scheep erreden, bote now ȝe beþ y-turned to a schepherde &amp; a byschop of ȝoure soules.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.25" type="verse">Soþly ȝe were as scheep strayȝenge a-boute (departynge from þe flocke) , but now ȝe beþ turned to þe hurde &amp; þe bischop of ȝoure sowlis.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.2" type="verse">as children þat be now bore, koueytynge resonable mylke, wiþ-outen trecherye, þat ȝee helfully wexe þer-wiþ:
<seg id="b.1PE.2.2" type="verse">dettractiones, as chyldren þat beþ nou bygeten, resonabel, wiþouten gyle , coueyte ȝe mylk þat ȝe growen þere into hele;
<seg id="b.1PE.2.3" type="verse">,
<seg id="b.1PE.2.3" type="verse">but not forþi ȝee haf tasted how swete oure Lord is.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.4" type="verse">Drawe ȝow to him þat is þe leuynge stone, reproued of men, but chosen soþely of God, &amp; honoured;
<seg id="b.1PE.2.4" type="verse">ȝef ȝe han y-tasted þe swetnesse of God: to whom ȝe comeþ, to a ston, y-repreuyd of men, bote y-chosen of God &amp; yworschupyd;
<seg id="b.1PE.2.5" type="verse">&amp; be ȝe as quyke stones y-buld abouen in-to spirytual houses, an holy presthod. And offre ȝe spirytual sacrifyces, acceptabel to God by Iesus Crist.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.5" type="verse">&amp; ȝe as quyke stones beþ maked in worke, in gostly houses, holy presthode, to offure gostly offrynges þat beþ acceptable to God þorow Iesu Criste.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.6" type="verse">&amp; þerfore scripture seiþ, Lo, ich wole putten in Syon a chef cornerston, precyous &amp; y-chose. And who þat byleueþ in hym ne schal noȝt ben y-schend.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.6" type="verse">Wherfore is conteynyd in holy writt , Lo, I schal putte in Syon a stone hyȝest cornarde, precyous and chosen, &amp; eche þat troweþ in him schal not be confounded:
<seg id="b.1PE.2.7" type="verse">And þer-fore to ȝow þat by-leueþ
<seg id="b.1PE.2.7" type="verse">þerfore to ȝou þat troweþ, honour: to hem þat troweþ not he is made a stone þat was reproued, &amp; kaste a-wey of hem þat housed, heere he is maked a heued stone in þe corner, (þat is, þat makeþ boþe one in charite)
<seg id="b.1PE.2.8" type="verse">&amp; he is a stomblynge stone, &amp; to sporne aȝeyn, &amp; a stone of sclawndre to hem þat stumblen þeraȝeyn þorow worde, &amp; troweþ not; in whom þei beþ putte (þat is, in whom is here dome or þeire sauacyoun putte) .
<seg id="b.1PE.2.8" type="verse">he is worschupe &amp; an heed-ston of þe corner, bote to hem þat byleueþ noȝt, &amp; buyldynge han reproued þis ston, he is a ston of offence &amp; of sclaundre, to þilke þat offendiþ his word &amp; byleueþ noȝt in hym, in whom þei beþ y-sett.
<seg id="b.1PE.2.9" type="verse">Bote ȝe beþ a kynde y-chose, a kynglyche presthode and holy folk, a pepel of adquysicyoun, þat ȝe schewen openlyche his vertues þat haþ ycleped ȝow out of darknesse in-to his wondurful lyȝt;
<seg id="b.1PE.2.9" type="verse">Ȝe soþeliche beþ a chosen kynrede, ryal presthode, a holy folke, peple i-chose (þat is, gete þorw passyoun &amp; bore þorw bapteme) ; þat ȝe schulde schewe þe vertu of him þat cleped ȝow fro derknesse in-to his merueilouse lyȝt;
<seg id="b.1PE.3.10" type="verse">For who þat wole loue lyf, &amp; y-sen goode dayes, chaste he his tunge from yfel, &amp; his lippis þat
<seg id="b.1PE.3.10" type="verse">Soþly whoso wole loue his lyf, &amp; see goode dayes, wiþ-drawe his tunge fro yuel, &amp; his lyppis þat þei speke no trecherye:
<seg id="b.1PE.3.11" type="verse">bowe him a-wey fro wikkidnes, &amp; do good; seke pees &amp; folowe it.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.11" type="verse">þei speken no gyle: &amp; bowe he a-wey from yfel, &amp; do he good; &amp; seche he pes &amp; swe pes.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.12" type="verse">For þe eyȝen of God loke up-on þe riȝtwyse, &amp; his eris be redy to here preieres; soþly þe semblawnt of God (þat is, þe heuy chere) is up-on hem þat worcheþ þe yuel.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.12" type="verse">For þe yȝen of God beþ on riȝtful men, &amp; his erys to here preyeres; bote þe sterne semblaunt of God is on hem þat doþ yfel.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.13" type="verse">&amp; who is he þat ȝow schal noye, if ȝe folowe me perfytly (&amp; be Godes amynysteris)
<seg id="b.1PE.3.13" type="verse">And who is it þat may noye ȝow, ȝef ȝe beþ goode foleweres?
<seg id="b.1PE.3.14" type="verse">&amp; ȝef ȝe suffreþ eny þing for riȝtfulnesse, þanne ȝe schuleþ ben blessed. Bote ne drede ȝe noȝt þe drede of hem, þat ȝe be noȝt
<seg id="b.1PE.3.14" type="verse">&amp; what so-euere þat ȝee suffre for riȝtwysnesse, in þat ȝe beþ blessed. Ne be ȝe not a-ferid of drede of hem, þat ȝe beþ not lettud ne disturbled;
<seg id="b.1PE.3.15" type="verse">afrayed; bote halewe ȝe oure Lord Crist in ȝoure hertys; &amp; be ȝe redy euermore to ȝeuen a resoun to euerich man þat
<seg id="b.1PE.3.15" type="verse">but hald wel ȝee Crist oure Lord in ȝoure hertus; euer redy to make satisfaccyoun to alle þat axkeþ ȝou resoun þer þat in ȝow is þorow hope &amp; feiþ.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.16" type="verse">axeþ ȝow of þe feiþ &amp; of þe hope þat is in ȝow; &amp; haue a good conscyence in softnesse &amp; in drede, þat þilke þat bakbyteþ ȝow ben confounded, þat chalangeþ ȝoure good conuersacyoun in Crist.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.16" type="verse">But wiþ a mesurid drede haue euere a good conciense, þat in þat at þei bacbite ȝow, as ȝe ware yuel-doaris, þat þei may be confoundid, þat blamen ȝowre goode conuersacioun &amp; lyfynge in Crist.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.17" type="verse">For it is beter, ȝif it be Goddis wille, þat ȝe suffren doynge wel þan doynge yuel.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.17" type="verse">Forsoþe muche bettur it is if þe wel-doaris suffre aftir þe wille of God, þan al þe lykynge of þe yuel-doaris;
<seg id="b.1PE.3.18" type="verse">For Crist haþ ones y-dyed for oure synnes, he þat is riȝtful for us vnriȝtful, þat he wolde offren us to God; y-slawen in flesch
<seg id="b.1PE.3.18" type="verse">for onys Crist was for oure synnes deed, þe riȝtwyse for the vnriȝtwise, to offre us to God; deed soþly in flesche &amp; lyuynge in spirite, et cetera.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.19" type="verse">&amp; y-mad lyfynge in spiryt; in þe whuche spiryt he com &amp;
<seg id="b.1PE.3.1" type="verse">And ben wymmen sogetis to hire housbondes, þat þilke þat byleueþ noȝt to þe word ben y-wonne wiþ-outen
<seg id="b.1PE.3.1" type="verse">And wymmen on þe same manere be maked sugettis to here housbondes, so þat who-so troweþ not to ȝoure worde þat þei may be wonnen wiþ-outyn worde þorow þe goode conuersacyoun of ȝoure wymmen;
<seg id="b.1PE.3.20" type="verse">preched to hem þat weren in prisoun, þat weren vnbyleuynge sumtime, when þei abyden þe pacyence of God in þe dayes of Noe, when þe schyp was y-mad, in þe whuche schip a fewe, as eiȝte soules, weren y-saued by water.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.21" type="verse">&amp; nouþ in þe same manere baptysme makeþ men saf, noȝt þe doynge a-wey of þe fylþe of þe flesch, bote þe axynge of a good conscyence in God, by þe arysynge from deþ to lyfe oure Lord Iesu
<seg id="b.1PE.3.22" type="verse">Crist, þat is in þe riȝtsyde of God, swolewynge deþ, þat ȝe weren y-mad heyres of an eferlastynge lyf; &amp; he is gon to hefne, &amp; haþ y-mad sogettis to hym aungeles and potestates and vertutes .
<seg id="b.1PE.3.2" type="verse">byholdynge in drede ȝoure holy conuersacyoun,
<seg id="b.1PE.3.2" type="verse">word by wymmennes conuersacioun; byholdynge a chaste
<seg id="b.1PE.3.3" type="verse">conuersacioun in drede , þouȝ þer were noȝt wiþouten-forþ arayynge of þe heres of hure hed, ne enuyronynge aboute of gold, oþer an-oþer cloþinge, ne apparayl of cloþes.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.3" type="verse">of whom ne be þei noȝt wiþ-oute (þat is, be not þe wymmen wiþ-outen schewynge ensample) wiþ þe here of here heued, or wiþ serkylyng a-boute wiþ golde, or wiþ bysy arayynge of cloþus.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.4" type="verse">Bote þat þe man of þe herte þat is y-hud be wiþ-outen corrupcioun, of a softe spiryt in reste, þat is ryche in þe syȝt of God.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.4" type="verse">But of þat þat is hydde wiþ-inne in mans herte (þat is, þat þei araye her herte wiþ-inne to þe siȝt of God, schewynge oute to þe folke her holy dedus in mekenes &amp; lowenes) in vnfilynge reste (of here
<seg id="b.1PE.3.5" type="verse">For so sumtyme holy wymmen, hopynge in God, arayed hemselfe,
<seg id="b.1PE.3.5" type="verse">So soþly some tyme holy wymmen, &amp; hopynge in God, enourned hem, sogettes to here housebondes.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.6" type="verse">As Sare was buxom to Abraham, clepynge him her lorde: whos douȝttres ȝe beþ, wel doynge &amp; not dredynge eny perturbacion or lettynge.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.6" type="verse">beynge sogettes to hure housbondes: as Sara was buxom to Abraham, clepynge hym hure lord: whos douȝtren ȝe beþ, wel doynge and dredynge non affray.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.7" type="verse">Men also duellen to-gydere with wymmen, &amp; aftur hure cunynge departynge to hem worschupe, as to a wommanlyche vessel þat is more febel þan ȝe beþ, as to hem þat beþ heyres wiþ ȝow of þe grace of lyf; þat ȝoure preyeres ne ben noȝt ylet.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.7" type="verse">Men also þat beþ duellynge wiþ ȝowre wymmen, aftur witte &amp; connynge reweled, absteyne ȝow fro ȝoure wyues þat beþ þe more freyle, doynge wurschupe vn-to hem, as to hem þat beþ eyres of grace of lyf; þat oure preyeris be not lettud.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.8" type="verse">&amp; be ȝe in feiþ euerychone of on soule, suffrynge togydere,
<seg id="b.1PE.3.8" type="verse">Beþ alle of o wylle in feiþe in ȝoure preyeris, hauynge pyte (&amp; compassyoun echone of oþur) , loueres of breþurhede, merciful, mylde, &amp; meke:
<seg id="b.1PE.3.9" type="verse">louyeris of breþerhed, mercyful, noȝt wroþ , &amp; humel : noȝt ȝeldynge yfel for yfel, ne cursynge for cursynge: bote blessynge aȝeynward; for in þat ȝe beþ y-cleped, þat ȝe owen þe blessynge of herytage.
<seg id="b.1PE.3.9" type="verse">not ȝeldynge euyl for euyl, or mysword for mysword, but euen þer-aȝeyn blysse hem þat cursiþ ȝow, or myssey; for in þat ȝee beþ clepyd (þat is, ȝe be ordeynyd euere to blysse) , þat ȝee may haue þe blyssynge þorow herytage.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.10" type="verse">echone aftur þat he haþ taken grace, scheweþ it vn-to oþur as good dispenderis of þe many-fold grace of God;
<seg id="b.1PE.4.10" type="verse">ȝe eferychone oþer wiþ-outen grucchynge; &amp; eferich man as he haþ vnderfonge grace, mynystre he þat grace to oþer, as
<seg id="b.1PE.4.11" type="verse">goode dyspensatores of many maner grace of God; &amp; who þat spekeþ, speke he as þe wordes of God; &amp; who þat mynystreþ as of þe vertue þat God mynystreþ: þat in alle þinges God be y-worschuped þoroȝ oure Lord Iesu Crist, to whom is blisse &amp; power of comaundynge, world wiþ-outen ende.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.11" type="verse">who-so spekeþ as þe wordis is of God; whoso mynysteriþ as þorow þe vertu þat God mynysteriþ to him: þat God in alle þinges be worschupid by oure Lord Iesu Criste, vn-to whom is honoure &amp; ioye and lordschupe, in worlde wiþ-outen ende, amen.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.12" type="verse">My deere breþeren, wele ȝe not traueyle in hete &amp; brennynge þat stereþ ȝow to temptacyon, as þat some newe þinge falle vn-to ȝowe:
<seg id="b.1PE.4.12" type="verse">My leueste breþeren, ne be ȝe noȝt pilgrymes in þe grete hete þat is y-don to ȝow þoroȝ temptacyones, as þouȝ
<seg id="b.1PE.4.13" type="verse">but communynge to-gedere in Cristis passyon (þat is, echone stere oþur whan he is toward eny temptacyoun, wiþ mynde of þe passyoun of Crist) , make ȝe ioye, þat in þe schewynge of his ioye ȝe mowe make ioye, beynge euere myry.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.13" type="verse">þer fulle any newe þing to ȝow: bote comune ȝe to Cristes suffrynges, &amp; be ȝe glade þat ȝe ben glade &amp; ioyen in þe reuelacion of þe blysse of oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.14" type="verse">And ȝef ȝe beþ obrayded for his name, þanne ȝe schulleþ ben y-blessed; For þe Spiryt of hym þat is of þe worschupe of þe blysse &amp; of þe vertue of God schal resten up-on ȝow.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.14" type="verse">If ȝe be schamed or reproued in þe name of oure Lord Iesu Criste,
<seg id="b.1PE.4.15" type="verse">Bote no man of ȝow suffre as a man-sleer, oþer a þef, oþer a curser, oþer as
<seg id="b.1PE.4.15" type="verse">Suffere noon of ȝow as a manslear doþ, or a þeef, or an yuel, wordly man, or as a coueytour of oþur mennes goodes:
<seg id="b.1PE.4.16" type="verse">but soþly if ȝe be not a-schamed to suffre as he þat is a cristen man, þan ȝe schul glorifye God in þis name.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.16" type="verse">he þat desyreþ oþer mennes goodes: bote who þat suffreþ as a Cristene man, be he noȝt aschamed, bote gloryfye he God
<seg id="b.1PE.4.17" type="verse">For it is tyme þat þe dom bygynne from Godes hous: &amp; ȝef þe bygynnynge be at ȝow, what ende schal be of hem þat byleueþ noȝt to þe euangelye?
<seg id="b.1PE.4.17" type="verse">For it is tyme þat þe dome bygynne of þe hous of God: if it soþly first bygynne of us, what schal be here ende þat trowe not to þe gospel of God?
<seg id="b.1PE.4.18" type="verse">&amp; ȝef þe riȝtful man schal vnneþis ben y-safed, where schuleþ þe wycked men &amp; þe synful man apperen?
<seg id="b.1PE.4.18" type="verse">&amp; if vnne-þus schal a riȝtwys man be sauyd, þe wikkid &amp; þe synner where schal þei appere?
<seg id="b.1PE.4.19" type="verse">Also &amp; þei þat suffre aftur þe wille of God, þei be-take here soules in here goode deedus vn-to here trewe makere.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.19" type="verse">&amp; þerfore þese þat suffreþ aftur þe wylle of God, to a trew makere þei takeþ hure soules to kepe in goode deedis.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.1" type="verse">And þerfore ȝif Crist haþ y-suffred in his flesch, be ȝe
<seg id="b.1PE.4.1" type="verse">Arme ȝow in þouȝt of þe passioun þat Crist suffrode in his flesche.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.2" type="verse">alle manere synnes; For as muche as þe remnaunt þat lyfeþ in flesch, aftur þis tyme lyue aftur þe wylle of God &amp; noȝt aftur mennes lustes.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.3" type="verse">For þe tyme þat is passed suffyceþ to maken an ende of þe wylle of mys-byleued men, þat habbeþ y-walked in hure leccheryes, &amp; in lustes of wyndrynkynges, &amp; etynges, &amp; drynkynges out of mesure, &amp;
<seg id="b.1PE.4.4" type="verse">vnlefful heryenges of maumetes: in whom þei beþ nowþe astonyed &amp; wondreþ þat we ne hurneþ noȝt in-to þe same
<seg id="b.1PE.4.5" type="verse">confusyoun of leccherye, blasphemyng oure God; bote þei schuleþ ȝelden a resoun to hym þat is redy for-to demen boþe quyke &amp; dede.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.6" type="verse">&amp; þerfore it haþ ben y-preched to hem þat beþ dede, þat þei ben y-demed aftur men in flesch, &amp; lyfen aftur God in spiryt.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.7" type="verse">&amp; þe ende of alle þinges comeþ nyȝ: &amp;
<seg id="b.1PE.4.7" type="verse">Beþ ȝe wyse, &amp; wakeþ in praieres;
<seg id="b.1PE.4.8" type="verse">hauynge eche wiþ oþur in ȝoureself lastynge charite. For charite hiduþ þe multitude of synne.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.8" type="verse">þerfore be ȝe wyse, and wake ȝe in preȝeres; &amp; to-fore alle þinges haue ȝe contynuel charyte in ȝow, eferychone to oþer; For charite heleþ þe multude of synnes.
<seg id="b.1PE.4.9" type="verse">&amp; herborewe
<seg id="b.1PE.4.9" type="verse">Holdiþ hospitalite to-gedere wiþ-outen gruchynge;
<seg id="b.1PE.5.10" type="verse">&amp; þerfore soþly God of al grace þat haþ callid ȝow in-to his euere-lastynge ioye in Iesu Crist, he schal fulfille (þe myȝt þat ȝow wanteþ) , conferme (ȝoure þouȝte) , &amp; make it sad.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.10" type="verse">Bote God of eferiche grace, þat haþ y-cleped ȝow into an eferlastynge blesse þat habbeþ y-suffred a luytel , he schal make ȝow parfyt, &amp; conferme
<seg id="b.1PE.5.11" type="verse">In him by ioye &amp; honoure euere wiþ-outen ende. Amen.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.11" type="verse">ȝow, &amp; stable ȝou to hym by blysse &amp; empyre from world to worlde.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.12" type="verse">By oure trewe broþer Syluane, as I suppose, schortly I haue wryton vnto ȝow, prayinge &amp; wyttnessynge þat þis is þe verrey grace of God, in þe whuche loke þat ȝe stonde.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.13" type="verse">Þe chosun churche þat is in Babiloyne greteþ ȝow weel, &amp; Marke my sone.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.14" type="verse">Greteþ wel to-gedere echone oþur in holy kyssynge. Grace be to ȝow alle þat beþ in Iesu Criste. Amen.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.1" type="verse">And y preye þilke þat beþ eldere men among ȝow, y, þat am a wytnesse of þe suffrynges of Crist, &amp; a comuner of his blisse þat schal be
<seg id="b.1PE.5.1" type="verse">I byseche þerfore þe olde þat beþ wiþ ȝou, I, þat am on of ȝoure elderis, &amp; a wittnes of þe passyouns of Crist, þe whuche is commn of his ioye þat schal be schewed in tyme þat is to come,
<seg id="b.1PE.5.2" type="verse">schewed her-aftur, þat ȝe feden Goddes flok þat is in ȝow, takynge kepe to hem, noȝt y-constreyned bote wilfullyche,
<seg id="b.1PE.5.2" type="verse">þat ȝe feede Godes flokke in þat at ȝee may, purueyinge for hem, not constreyned but by ȝoure fre wille, aftur Godes techynge; ne for no hauynge of foule wordly wynnynge, but wilfully (&amp; gladly) ;
<seg id="b.1PE.5.3" type="verse">aftur God; ne for no foul wynnynge, bote wilfullyche; &amp; noȝt as hauynge lordschype in clergye, bote in forme of
<seg id="b.1PE.5.3" type="verse">not as lordis in þe clergye, but a forme (&amp; ensample) to the flokke of good lyuynge;
<seg id="b.1PE.5.4" type="verse">a flok þat is y-mad of ȝoure wylle, of ȝoure soule; þat whan he þat is prince of schepherdes appereþ, ȝe vnderfongen a coroune of blysse þat may noȝt welewe.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.4" type="verse">and whan þe prynce of hirdus schal appere (þat is, Crist on þe day of dome) , ȝe schal take a gloriose croune of ioye.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.5" type="verse">Also, ȝe ȝongelynges, be ȝe sogettes to ȝoure eldren. &amp; eferich man schewe humelnesse to oþer: for God aȝeynstondeþ proude men, &amp; ȝefeþ grace to humel men.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.5" type="verse">&amp; þe same manere ȝe þat be ȝonge be þe sogettes to ȝoure elderis. And scheweþ alle to-gedere mekenes a-mong ȝow: for God þe proude wiþstondiþ, &amp; to þe meke he ȝeueþ grace.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.6" type="verse">&amp; þerfore humel ȝe ȝow vnder þe myȝty hond of God, þat he arere ȝow an hyȝ in þe tyme of
<seg id="b.1PE.5.6" type="verse">And þerfore meke ȝow vndur þe myȝt honde of God, þat he make ȝow hye in tyme of his visitacioun;
<seg id="b.1PE.5.7" type="verse">puttynge in him al ȝoure bysynes, for he haþ kepynge of ȝow.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.7" type="verse">vysytacyoun; &amp; þrowe ȝe al ȝoure bysynesse in hym, for he haþ þe charg of ȝouw.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.8" type="verse">And be ȝe sober, &amp; wake ȝe, for ȝoure aduersarye þe deuel goþ aboute as a lyoun rampaund,
<seg id="b.1PE.5.8" type="verse">Beþ sobre &amp; wakeþ, for ȝoure enmy þe deuele as it wore a romynynge lyon goþ aboute, sechynge whom he may swelowe:
<seg id="b.1PE.5.9" type="verse">sechynge whom he may deuoure: whom aȝeynstonde ȝe strong in feiþ, knowynge þat he doþ in þe same wyse to ȝoure broþerhede þat is in þe worlde.
<seg id="b.1PE.5.9" type="verse">whom ȝe schul wiþstonde, stalworþe in þe feiþ, wytynge þat ȝee mowe suffre þe same passyoun þat he doþ þat is in þe worlde (for eny strenkþ þat ȝe haue of ȝow-self) .
<seg id="b.1TH.1.10" type="verse">seruen a verrey God þat lyueþ, &amp; to abyden his Sone from heuene, whom he arered up from deþ to lyf, Iesu, þat haþ delyuered ous from wraþþe þat is to comynge.
<seg id="b.1TH.1.2" type="verse">We þankeþ God efermore for ȝow alle, &amp; we makeþ
<seg id="b.1TH.1.3" type="verse">muynde of ȝou efermore wiþ-outen styntynge, hafynge muynde of þe werk of ȝoure feiþ, &amp; of ȝoure trafayle, &amp; of ȝoure charyte, &amp; of ȝoure abydynge, &amp; of ȝoure hope of oure Lord Iesu Crist, to-fore God &amp; oure Fader.
<seg id="b.1TH.1.4" type="verse">And knowe ȝe, my
<seg id="b.1TH.1.5" type="verse">lefe breþeren, ȝoure eleccyoun of God, for oure euangelye ne was noȝt to ȝou onlyche in word, bote in vertu, &amp; in þe holy Spiryt, &amp; in gret plente, as ȝe wyteþ whyche we weren in ȝou for ȝou.
<seg id="b.1TH.1.6" type="verse">And ȝe beþ y-maad foleweres of ous, &amp; of oure Lord, takynge þe word in myche tribulacyoun, wiþ þe ioye of
<seg id="b.1TH.1.7" type="verse">þe holy Spiryt; þat ȝe beþ y-maad forme to alle þilke þat byleueþ in Macedonye &amp; in Achaye.
<seg id="b.1TH.1.8" type="verse">For of ȝou Godes is y-sprongen a-brood, noȝt onlyche in Macedonye &amp; in Achaye, bote in-to eferich place ȝoure feiþ þat is in God is y-passed forþ; so þat it is noȝt nedful to speke to ȝou no þing.
<seg id="b.1TH.1.9" type="verse">For þei scheweþ of ous what entre we haden in-to ȝow; &amp; how ȝe beþ y-turned to God fro mawmetes, for-to
<seg id="b.1TH.2.10" type="verse">&amp; ȝe beþ wytnesses, &amp; God also, hou holylyche &amp; ryȝtfullyche and
<seg id="b.1TH.2.11" type="verse">wiþ-outen blame we weren to ȝou þat byleueden, as ȝe wyteþ
<seg id="b.1TH.2.12" type="verse">wel, &amp; preyenge eferichone of ȝou as a fader his chyldren, &amp; comfortynge ȝou, &amp; wytnessed to ȝow, þat ȝe walken worþilyche to God, þat haþ ycleped ȝow in-to his kyngdom &amp; in-to his blisse.
<seg id="b.1TH.2.13" type="verse">&amp; þerfore we þankeþ God wiþ-outen stuntynge , for whanne ȝe hadden vnderfongen of ous þe word of þe herynge of God, ȝe vnderfongen it noȝt as mennes word, bote as þe word of God verreylyche, þat worcheþ in ȝou þat han byleued.
<seg id="b.1TH.2.14" type="verse">For breþeren, ȝe beþ y-mad foleweres of Godes churches þat beþ Iudee in Iesu Crist: for ȝe han y-suffred þe same þinges
<seg id="b.1TH.2.15" type="verse">of oure felowchupes, þat þei habbeþ of Iewes; þat slowen Iesus þat is God &amp; þe prophetes also, &amp; ous þei han purswed, &amp; þei ne pleseþ noȝt God, &amp; to alle men þei beþ aduersaryes:
<seg id="b.1TH.2.16" type="verse">forbedynge ous to speke to mysbylefed men þat þei ben y-saued; þat þei fulfullen efermore hure synnes: for þe wraþþe of God is y-comen on hem to þe ende.
<seg id="b.1TH.2.17" type="verse">And breþeren, we þat ben desolat from ȝou , in mu &amp; in byholdynge, &amp; noȝt in herte, hafeþ muche y-hyȝed to
<seg id="b.1TH.2.18" type="verse">sen ȝoure vysage wiþ muche desyr: &amp; ich wolde haue y-come to ȝou ones &amp; eftsones, bote Sathanas letted me.
<seg id="b.1TH.2.19" type="verse">Whuche is oure hope, oþer oure ioye, oþer þe corone of oure blisse? Ne be ȝe þat noȝt byfore oure Lord Iesu Crist in his comynge?
<seg id="b.1TH.2.1" type="verse">And ȝe ȝouself knoweþ oure entre to ȝou, &amp; þat it ne was noȝt veyn:
<seg id="b.1TH.2.20" type="verse">Ȝe beþ oure blysse &amp; oure ioye.
<seg id="b.1TH.2.2" type="verse">bote furst we suffreden enuyes &amp; disheses, as ȝe wyteþ wel, among Phylypences, bote we haden trust in oure Lord God to speke to ȝou þe euangelye of God in myche bysynesse.
<seg id="b.1TH.2.3" type="verse">&amp; oure exortacyoun ne was noȝt of errour, ne of vnclannesse, ne
<seg id="b.1TH.2.4" type="verse">in gyle: bote as weren y-prefed by-fore God, &amp; as þe euangelye was y-take to ous, so we spekeþ; noȝt as plesynge to men, bote to God þat prefeþ oure hertes.
<seg id="b.1TH.2.5" type="verse">Ne we weren noȝt in no tyme in speche of flaterynge, as ȝe wyteþ wel, ne
<seg id="b.1TH.2.6" type="verse">in occasyoun of coueytyse, God is wyttnesse; ne sechyng
<seg id="b.1TH.2.7" type="verse">worschupe of ȝou, ne of non oþer, whan we myȝten haue y-be
<seg id="b.1TH.2.8" type="verse">hure chuldren: so we han desyred ȝou &amp; wolden noȝt onlyche haue y-take to ȝou þe euangelye, bote also oure owne soules, for ȝe weren leuest to ous.
<seg id="b.1TH.2.9" type="verse">And breþeren, ȝe haueþ mynde of oure trauayl &amp; of oure werynesse: for day &amp; nyȝt we wroȝten, for we ne wolden greue none of ȝow, ne be chariaunt, and precheden to ȝow þe euangelye of God.
<seg id="b.1TH.3.10" type="verse">oure God; preyenge boþe nyȝt &amp; day þat we sen ȝoure vysage, &amp; þat we fulfullen þilke þinges þat lakkeþ to ȝoure feiþ.
<seg id="b.1TH.3.11" type="verse">Bote God oure Fader, &amp; oure Lord Iesu Crist, dresse
<seg id="b.1TH.3.12" type="verse">oure weye to-ward ȝow: &amp; God multyplye ȝou &amp; encrece ȝoure charyte to-gedere, &amp; to alle men, ryȝt as we beþ in
<seg id="b.1TH.3.13" type="verse">ȝow: to conferme ȝoure hertes wiþ-outen blame in holynesse to-fore God oure Fader, in þe comynge of oure God Iesu Crist wiþ alle his seyntes.
<seg id="b.1TH.3.1" type="verse">And for we myȝten no lengere abyden, it plesed ous to
<seg id="b.1TH.3.2" type="verse">lyfen al-one at Athenys: &amp; senden to ȝow Tymothe, oure
<seg id="b.1TH.3.3" type="verse">ȝow, &amp; to byseche ȝou for ȝoure feiþ; þat noman be y-mefed in þese trybulacyons; for ȝe wyteþ ȝow-selfe þat in þis we beþ y-sett.
<seg id="b.1TH.3.4" type="verse">For whenne we weren wiþ ȝow, we tolden ȝou þis byfore, þat we schulden suffre trybulacyones; as it is y-don, &amp; as ȝe knoweþ.
<seg id="b.1TH.3.5" type="verse">And þerfore y ne abode no lengere, bote sende to knowe ȝoure feiþ, lest he þat tempteþ haue y-tempted ȝou, &amp; oure trauayle be y-mad veyn.
<seg id="b.1TH.3.6" type="verse">Bote now when Tymothe comeþ from ȝou to ous, &amp; telleþ ous ȝoure feiþ &amp; ȝoure charyte, &amp; þat ȝe han good mynde on ous, &amp; þat ȝe wolden sen ous, as we wolden ȝow.
<seg id="b.1TH.3.7" type="verse">&amp; þerfore, breþeren, we beþ ycoumforted in ȝow in al oure nede &amp; al oure
<seg id="b.1TH.3.8" type="verse">trybulacyoun þorȝ ȝoure feiþ: for now we lyfeþ, ȝif þat ȝe stondeþ in oure Lord.
<seg id="b.1TH.3.9" type="verse">&amp; what þankynges mow we ȝelde to God for ȝow in al oure ioye, þat we ioyeþ for ȝow to-foren
<seg id="b.1TH.4.10" type="verse">how ȝe schulen lue to-gedere; for þat to alle ȝowre breþeren in al Macedonye. Bote, breþeren , we preyeþ
<seg id="b.1TH.4.11" type="verse">ȝow , þat ȝe ben aboute to ben in reste, &amp; þat ȝe don ȝoure werk, &amp; worchen wiþ ȝoure hondes, as we han y-bede ȝou &amp; y-sayd ȝow her-byfore; þat ȝe walken honestlyche to hem þat ben wiþ-outen-forþ, desyrynge no þing of no mannes.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.12" type="verse">Bote, breþeren, we ne woleþ noȝt þat ȝe ben vnkunnynge of hem þat beþ slepynge; þat ȝe ben noȝt drery, as oþer men, þat habbeþ non hope.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.13" type="verse">For ȝef we bylefeþ þat Iesu was ded, &amp; þat he ros up from deeþ to lyfe, so God schal bryngen þilke þat hafeþ y-sleped by Iesus wiþ hym.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.14" type="verse">For þis we seggeþ in þe word of God, þat we þat lyfeþ &amp; beþ þe resydue in þe comynge of oure Lord, ne schuleþ noȝt gon byforen hem þat han y-slept byfore.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.15" type="verse">For oure Lord in his commaundynge, &amp; in þe voyce of an archaungel, &amp; in þe trompe of God, schal come adown from hefne: &amp; þilke þat
<seg id="b.1TH.4.16" type="verse">beþ dede in Crist schuleþ rysen up furst: &amp; siþþe we þat lyfeþ, þat beþ y-laft, schulen ben y-rauysched to-gedere wiþ hem in clowdes, to mete with Cryst in þe eyr: &amp; so we schuleþ efermore ben with oure Lord.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.17" type="verse">&amp; þerfore be ȝe y-comforted to-gedere in these wordes.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.1" type="verse">And þerfore, breþeren, here-after we preyeþ ȝow and bysecheþ ȝou in oure Lord Iesus, þat, ryȝt as ȝe han vnderfongen of ous how it byhoueþ ȝou to walken &amp; to plesen God, so walke ȝe, þat ȝe wexen more plenteuous.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.2" type="verse">For ȝe knoweþ whyche hestes ich haue ȝeue ȝow þoroȝ oure Lord Iesus.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.3" type="verse">&amp; þis is þe wyl of God, ȝoure holynesse, þat ȝe abstene ȝow from
<seg id="b.1TH.4.4" type="verse">fornycacion; þat eferech man of ȝow conne owe his vessel in
<seg id="b.1TH.4.5" type="verse">holynesse &amp; in worschupe, noȝt in passyoun of lust as folke
<seg id="b.1TH.4.6" type="verse">þat knoweþ noȝt God; ne no man oferpasse ne bygyle his broþer in chaffarynge: for God is wrachful of alle suche men, as we han y-sayd ȝou herbyfore, &amp; y-wytnessed it to ȝow.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.7" type="verse">For God ne haþ noȝt y-cleped ous in-to vnclannesse, bote in-to holynesse.
<seg id="b.1TH.4.8" type="verse">&amp; þerfore who þat dyspyseþ þese þinges, he
<seg id="b.1TH.4.9" type="verse">Of charite of breþerhede we ne haueþ no nede to wryte to ȝou: for of God ȝe han y-lerned ȝow-selfe,
<seg id="b.1TH.5.10" type="verse">Crist, þat dyed for ous, þat, wheþer we waken oþer slepen, we lyfen to-gedere wiþ hym.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.11" type="verse">Wherfore be ȝe y-coumforted to God, &amp; eferich man edyfye oþer, as ȝe doþ.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.12" type="verse">And, breþeren, we preyeþ ȝow þat ȝe know hem, þat trauayleþ a-mong ȝow,
<seg id="b.1TH.5.13" type="verse">&amp; beþ abofen ȝou in oure Lord, &amp; warne ȝou, þat ȝe han hem more plenteuouslyche in charite for hure werk; &amp; haue ȝe pees wiþ hem.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.14" type="verse">And, breþeren, we preyeþ ȝow þat ȝe a-menden vn-pesyble men, &amp; comforteþ men of smal soule, &amp; vnderfongeþ seke men, &amp; be ȝe pacyent to alle men.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.15" type="verse">&amp; lokeþ þat no man ȝelde to oþer yfel for yfel; bote efermo swe þe þing þat is good, eferich man to oþer, &amp; to alle men.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.16" type="verse">&amp; ioye
<seg id="b.1TH.5.17" type="verse">,
<seg id="b.1TH.5.18" type="verse">ȝe efermore; &amp; preye ȝe wiþ-oute stuntynge; &amp; in alle þinges do ȝe þankynges to God: for þis is Godes wille in Iesu Crist in alle ous.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.19" type="verse">,
<seg id="b.1TH.5.1" type="verse">Bote of þe tymes &amp; of þe momentes, my breþeren, it nedeþ noȝt þat y wryte to ȝou.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.20" type="verse">Ne quenche ȝe noȝt þe Spiryt; ne dyspyse ȝe
<seg id="b.1TH.5.21" type="verse">noȝt prophecyes; prefeþ alle þinges, &amp; holdeþ þat þing þat is good; &amp; absteneþ ȝou from al yfel.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.22" type="verse">,
<seg id="b.1TH.5.23" type="verse">&amp; he þat is God of pees halewe ȝou by alle þinges, þat ȝoure spiryt, ȝoure soule, &amp; ȝoure body be y-kept hol wiþ-outen playnt in þe comynge of oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.24" type="verse">&amp; þe trewe God þat haþ y-cleped ȝou, he schal don hyt.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.25" type="verse">Breþeren, preye ȝe for ous.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.2" type="verse">For ȝe wyteþ ȝou-selfe þat þe day of oure Lord schal come as a þef by nyȝte.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.3" type="verse">For whanne me seiþ þat þer is pees &amp; sekernesse, þanne schal þer come a sodayn deþ, as þe sorowȝ of a womman þat bereþ a chylde; bote þei ne schuleþ noȝt flen a-wey.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.4" type="verse">Bote, breþeren,
<seg id="b.1TH.5.5" type="verse">ȝe be noȝt in derknesse, þat þilke day take ȝow as a þef: for alle ȝe beþ chyldren of lyȝt, &amp; Goddes chyldren, &amp; ȝe beþ nouþer of nyȝt, ne of darknesse.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.6" type="verse">And þerfore ne slepe we noȝt, as oþer men, bote wake we &amp; be we sober.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.7" type="verse">For þilke
<seg id="b.1TH.5.8" type="verse">dronken a-nyȝt; bote we þat beþ of þe day, be we sober, and caste we up-on ous an haberioun of feiþ &amp; of charyte, &amp; an helm þat is hope of hele.
<seg id="b.1TH.5.9" type="verse">For God ne haþ noȝt y-put ous in-to wraþþe, bote in-to getynge of hele þoroȝ oure Lord Iesu
<seg id="b.1TI.1.10" type="verse">hure fadres &amp; hure moderes, &amp; to men-sleares, &amp; to lecchoures, &amp; to sodomytes, &amp; to gyloures, &amp; to lyeres, &amp; to men þat beþ forswore, &amp; what-efer elles þat þer be, þat be aȝeyn hol
<seg id="b.1TI.1.11" type="verse">techynge of þe euangely of blysse of God þat is y-blessed, þe whuche euangely is y-take to me.
<seg id="b.1TI.1.12" type="verse">And y þonke hym þat haþ y-comforted me in oure Lord Iesu Crist, for þat he supposed
<seg id="b.1TI.1.13" type="verse">þat ich was trewe &amp; sette me in his seruyse, þat byfore was a blaspheme , &amp; a pursuere, &amp; doynge iniurye to his serfauntes: bote ich haue y-founde þe mercy of God, for vnknowynge y dude it in vnbylefe.
<seg id="b.1TI.1.14" type="verse">Bote þe grace of oure Lord Iesu Crist wes ofer-plentefous wiþ feiþ &amp; lofe þat is in Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.1TI.1.15" type="verse">A trewe word &amp; worþy to ben vnderfonge, þat Iesu Crist com in-to þe worlde to safe synful men; of whom
<seg id="b.1TI.1.16" type="verse">ich was on of þe furste: bote þerfore ich had mercy, for þat Iesu Crist wolde furst schewen in me eferych pacyence, to þe informacyon of hem þat schulden lyfen to hym in-to an eferlastynge lyf.
<seg id="b.1TI.1.17" type="verse">Bote to hym þat is Kyng of worldes, &amp; noȝt dedlyche, &amp; invysybel, þat onlyche is God, be worschype &amp; blysse world wiþ-outen ende.
<seg id="b.1TI.1.18" type="verse">And þis heste y bytake þe, Tymothe my sone, þat þou ocupye þe after þe prophecyes þat
<seg id="b.1TI.1.19" type="verse">habbeþ y-ben byfore þis tyme, hafynge a good feiþ &amp; a good conscyence; whom summe men habbeþ y-put a-wey from hem,
<seg id="b.1TI.1.1" type="verse">Poule , Iesu Cristes apostel þoroȝ þe comawndynge of
<seg id="b.1TI.1.20" type="verse">&amp; han y-had schypbreche aboute þe feiþ: of þe whuche weren
<seg id="b.1TI.1.2" type="verse">God &amp; oure Safyour, &amp; of Iesu Crist oure hope; to Tymothe, my lefe sone in feiþ, be grace, mercy, &amp; pees of God oure Fader &amp; oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.1TI.1.3" type="verse">As y preyde þe þat þou schuldest dwelle stylle at Ephese, whanne þat ich wente in-to Macedonye, þat þou schuldest telle to summe men, þat þei
<seg id="b.1TI.1.4" type="verse">ne tauȝte non oþer wyse, ne toke no kepe to tales, ne to genologyes þat hafeþ non ende, þat meueþ raþer questyones þan to þe edyfycacyon of God þat is in feiþ.
<seg id="b.1TI.1.5" type="verse">For þe ende of þe comaundement is charite of a clene herte &amp; of a good
<seg id="b.1TI.1.6" type="verse">conscience &amp; of feiþ noȝt -feyned : from þe whuche þinges summe men habbeþ y-erred a-wey &amp; beþ y-turned in-to veyn
<seg id="b.1TI.1.7" type="verse">speche, &amp; wolleþ ben doctoures of þe lawe, bote þei ne vnderstondeþ noȝt what þei spekeþ, ne þe þinges þat þev affermeþ.
<seg id="b.1TI.1.8" type="verse">And we wyteþ wel þat þe lawe is good, who-so vseþ hure
<seg id="b.1TI.1.9" type="verse">lawefullyche, knowynge wel, þat þer ne is no lawe y-set to a ryȝtful man, bote to vnryȝtful men, &amp; to þilke þat ne weleþ noȝt ben sogetes, &amp; to wikked men, &amp; to synful men, &amp; to cursed men, &amp; to men þat beþ defouled, &amp; to men þat sleþ
<seg id="b.1TI.2.10" type="verse">margery perles oþer precyous cloþing; but, as it bysemeþ wymmen þat byhoteþ chastyte, by goode werkes.
<seg id="b.1TI.2.11" type="verse">&amp; a womman lerne in scylence with alle subieccyon.
<seg id="b.1TI.2.12" type="verse">Bote y ne lete no womman to teche, ne to hafe lordschupe on hure housbonde, bote to ben in sylence.
<seg id="b.1TI.2.13" type="verse">For Adam was furst y-mad, &amp; syþen Eue.
<seg id="b.1TI.2.14" type="verse">&amp; Adam ne was noȝt bygyled, bote þe womman
<seg id="b.1TI.2.15" type="verse">was bygyled in preuarycacyon: &amp; heo schal ben y-safed by bryngynge forþ of children, ȝef þat he dwelle stille in feiþ &amp; lofe &amp; holynesse wiþ eferiche sobernesse.
<seg id="b.1TI.2.1" type="verse">And þerfore y byseche þat þer ben furst y-mad of alle men preyeres , bysechynges, &amp; þankynges to God for alle
<seg id="b.1TI.2.2" type="verse">men; &amp; for kynges &amp; for alle þilke þat beþ y-ordeyned in hyȝschype; þat we han a pesybel lyfynge &amp; an esy in eferich pyte &amp; chastyte.
<seg id="b.1TI.2.3" type="verse">For þis is good &amp; acceptabel to-fore God
<seg id="b.1TI.2.4" type="verse">oure Safyour, þat wole þat alle men ben y-safed, &amp; þat þei comen to þe knowlechynge of his trewþe.
<seg id="b.1TI.2.5" type="verse">þer is on God , &amp;
<seg id="b.1TI.2.6" type="verse">on medyatour of God &amp; of men, Iesu Crist, þat is a man, þat ȝef hym self redempcyoun for alle men, whos wytnesse is
<seg id="b.1TI.2.7" type="verse">y-confermed in his tymes; in whom ich am y-set a prechour &amp; an apostel, for y seye trewþe &amp; y ne lye noȝt, þat am techere of mysbyleued men in feiþ &amp; in treuþe.
<seg id="b.1TI.2.8" type="verse">And þerfore ich wole þat men preyen in eferich place, lyftynge up clene honden wiþ-outen wraþþe &amp; stryuynge.
<seg id="b.1TI.2.9" type="verse">And wymmen also in a couenabel habyte, wiþ schamfastnesse &amp; sobernesse arayynge hem-selfe, noȝt in heres y-platted, ne wiþ gol oþer
<seg id="b.1TI.3.10" type="verse">Bote ben þese first y-prefed, &amp; so mynystren þei wiþouten blame.
<seg id="b.1TI.3.11" type="verse">&amp; summe wymmen also ben chaste, noȝt bakbytynge, sober &amp; feiþful in alle þinges.
<seg id="b.1TI.3.12" type="verse">Dekenes ben of on wyf, þat rewleþ wel hure chyldren &amp; hure houshold.
<seg id="b.1TI.3.13" type="verse">For þilke þat mynystreþ wel schulleþ geten hem-selfen a good degre, &amp; a muche trust in þe feiþ þat is in oure Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.1TI.3.14" type="verse">Þese þynges y wryte to ȝow , hopynge
<seg id="b.1TI.3.15" type="verse">to come sone to ; &amp; ȝef þat y tarye, þat þou wete how þou schalt haue þi conuersacyoun in þe hous of God, þat is Goddes churche þat lyfeþ, &amp; a pyler &amp; a stabelnesse of þe trewþe.
<seg id="b.1TI.3.16" type="verse">And it is openlyche a gret sacrament of pyte, þat haþ ben y-schewed in flesch &amp; y-iustyfyed in spiryt &amp; appered to aungeles &amp; is y-preched a-mong mysbylefed men &amp; is y-lefed in þe world &amp; y-taken vp in blysse.
<seg id="b.1TI.3.1" type="verse">A trewe word, Who þat desyreþ a byschopryche, he desyreþ a good werk.
<seg id="b.1TI.3.2" type="verse">For it byhoueþ a byschop to ben a man wiþ-outen reprefe, &amp; a man of on wif, sober, redy,
<seg id="b.1TI.3.3" type="verse">chaste , hospiteler, a techere; noȝt dronkelew, ne smytere;
<seg id="b.1TI.3.4" type="verse">bote softe &amp; good, no stryfer, ne coueytous; bote þat gouerneþ
<seg id="b.1TI.3.5" type="verse">eferiche chastyte; &amp; who þat can noȝt rewle wel his owene houshold, how schal he haue þe dylygence of Godes churche?
<seg id="b.1TI.3.6" type="verse">ne þilke þat is late y-baptysed, lest he be hofen up in-to pruyde &amp; falle in-to þe dom of þe defel.
<seg id="b.1TI.3.7" type="verse">For it byhofeþ þat he hafe good witnesse of þilke þat ben wiþouten-forþ, þat he ne falle noȝt in-to obbrayd &amp; in-to þe defeles grun.
<seg id="b.1TI.3.8" type="verse">Dekenes also ben chaste &amp; noȝt of two tunges, noȝt y-ȝeue to myche
<seg id="b.1TI.3.9" type="verse">wyn, ne suynge foul wynnynge; bote hafynge þe mynystrynge of feiþ in a clene consyence.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.10" type="verse">For in þis we trafeyleþ &amp; we beþ y-cursed, for we hopeþ in þe lyfynge God þat is safyour of alle men, bote most of feiþful men. Hote þou þese þinges &amp; teche hem.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.11" type="verse"/>
<seg id="b.1TI.4.12" type="verse">No man dispyse þy ȝouþe; bote be þou ensampel of feiþful men, in word, in conuersacyoun, in charyte, in feiþ, in chastyte.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.13" type="verse">Forto y come, take hede to redynge, to exortacyoun &amp; to doctryne.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.14" type="verse">Ne be þou noȝt necclygent of þe grace þat is y-ȝefe þe by prophecye wiþ puttynge in of þe honden of presthod .
<seg id="b.1TI.4.15" type="verse">Þese þynges by-þenche þou; &amp; be þou in þese þynges, þat þy profytynge be opene to alle men.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.16" type="verse">Take hede to þi-selfe, &amp; to doctrine. Be bysy in hem, for doynge so þou schalt safe þi-selfe &amp; þilke þat y-hereþ þe.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.1" type="verse">But þe spiryt seiþ openlyche, þat in þe laste dayes þer schulleþ summe fallen awey fro feiþ, takynge kepe to spirytes
<seg id="b.1TI.4.2" type="verse">of errour &amp; to þe doctrines of fendes, þat in ypocrysye
<seg id="b.1TI.4.3" type="verse">spekeþ lesynges, þat hafeþ a corrupt consyence, &amp; forbedeþ weddynge, &amp; abstenen from metes þat God haþ y-mad to ben vnderfongen of trewe men, þat han y-knowe þe trewþe wyþ þonkynges to God.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.4" type="verse">For eferiche creature of God is good, &amp; þer ne is no þing to ben y-cast awey þat is vnderfongen wiþ
<seg id="b.1TI.4.5" type="verse">þankynges to God: for it is y-mad holy by Goddes word &amp; by preyere.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.6" type="verse">And proposynge þese þynges to oure breþeren, be þou a good serfaunt of oure Lord Iesu Crist, y-norsched wiþ wordes of þe feiþ, &amp; of þe good doctryne þat þou hast y-folowed.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.7" type="verse">And schunye þou vncouenabel &amp; veyn fables,
<seg id="b.1TI.4.8" type="verse">&amp; excersyse þi-selfe to pyte: for bodylyche excercyse is profytabel to luytel þing; but pyte is profytabel to alle þinges, hafynge a byheste of lyf þat is now, &amp; of lyf þat is to comynge.
<seg id="b.1TI.4.9" type="verse">A trewe word &amp; a worþi to ben accepted.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.10" type="verse">y-ben on mannes wyf, &amp; haþ y-had testymonye in goode werkes; ȝef heo haþ wel y-norsched hure children, ȝef heo haþ y-herborewd men, ȝef heo haþ y-wasche goode mennes fet, ȝef heo haþ y-mynystred to þilke þat habbeþ y-suffred trybulacyoun, &amp; ȝef heo hafe y-swed eferych good werk.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.11" type="verse">Bote schonye þou wydewes þat beþ ȝongere: for when þei haueþ y-don leccherye in Crist , þei wlleþ ben y-weddyd:
<seg id="b.1TI.5.12" type="verse">&amp; hau dampnacyoun, for þei habbeþ y-mad hure furste feiþ veyn.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.13" type="verse">&amp; þei lerneþ to gon to-gedere in ydelnesse, &amp; gon aboute to mennes houses; noȝt onlyche ydel, bote also ful of wordes, and spekynge curyouslyche þinges þat it byhofeþ noȝt for-to speken.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.14" type="verse">And þerfore ich wole þat ȝongere wymmen ben y-weddyd &amp; bryngen forþ children &amp; ben houswyfes, þat þei ȝefen non occasyoun to þe aduersary by enchesoun of efel seyȝenge:
<seg id="b.1TI.5.15" type="verse">for now þer beþ summe y-turned abak aftur Sathanas.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.16" type="verse">And þerfore who þat haþ trewe wydewes, mynystre he to hem, so þat þe churche ne be noȝt y-grefed, &amp; þat heo mowe suffice to þilke þat beþ trewe wydewes.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.17" type="verse">And þilke prestes þat beþ wel abofen oþer men, ben þei y-had worþy to doubel worschupe, &amp; þei most þat traueyleþ in word &amp; in techynge.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.18" type="verse">For holy scripture seyþ, Þou ne schalt noȝt bynde þe mouþ of þe oxe þat tyleþ þi lond. &amp;, A werkman is worþi his mede.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.19" type="verse">&amp; vnderfonge þou non accusasyoun aȝeyn a prest, bote vnder two wytnesses oþer þre.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.1" type="verse">Ne blame þou noȝt hym þat is aldere þan þou, bote byseche hym as þi fader; &amp; ȝonge
<seg id="b.1TI.5.20" type="verse">&amp; vnderneme þilke þat synneþ to-foren alle men, þat oþer ben adrad.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.21" type="verse">And y wytnesse to-fore God, &amp; to-fore Iesu Crist, &amp; aungelis þat beþ y-chosen, þat þou kepe þese þynges wiþouten lattynge of ony enchesoun, &amp; þat þou do no þing bowynge to þe oþer syde.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.22" type="verse">Ne putte þou not þyn honden to no man sone, ne comune þou noȝt to oþer mennes synnes: kepe þi-selfe chaste.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.23" type="verse">Ne drynke þou noȝt water ȝet, but vse þou a lytul wyn for þi stomac &amp; for þi sekenesses þat þou art y-woned to haue.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.24" type="verse">Summe
<seg id="b.1TI.5.25" type="verse">mennes synnes beþ opene, &amp; goynge byfore þe dom; &amp; summe
<seg id="b.1TI.5.2" type="verse">men as breþeren: olde wymmen as moderes; ȝonge wymmen as sustren in alle chastyte.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.3" type="verse">Worschupe wydewes þat beþ trewe wydewes.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.4" type="verse">&amp; ȝef þer be a wedewe þat haþ sones oþer neewes ewes dotted out and cosynes written above in a later hand, S. cosyns P.], lerne he furst to gouerne hure owene houshold, &amp; to ȝelden a-ȝeyn to hure eldren for þe goodnesse þat þei han receyfed of hem: for þis is acceptabel to-fore God.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.5" type="verse">And heo þat is a trewe wydewe &amp; desolat, hope heo in God, &amp; be he in hure preyeres &amp; bysechynges nyȝt &amp; day.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.6" type="verse">For heo þat lyfeþ in delyces is deed.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.7" type="verse">&amp; comaunde þou þese þinges, þat þei ben wiþouten reprefe.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.8" type="verse">&amp; who þat haþ no charge of þilke þat beþ of his, &amp; most of þilke þat beþ homlyche wiþ hym, he haþ forsaken his feyþ, &amp; is worse þan a mysbylefed man.
<seg id="b.1TI.5.9" type="verse">A
<seg id="b.1TI.6.10" type="verse">For þe rote of al efel is couetyse: whom summen hafeþ desyred, &amp; han y-erred from þe feiþ &amp; han y-broȝt hemselfen in-to muche sorewe.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.11" type="verse">Bote þou þat art Goddes man, fleo þese þinges; &amp; folewe þow ryȝtfulnesse &amp; pyte, feiþ, charyte, pacyence, &amp; mansuetude.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.12" type="verse">Fyȝt a good fyȝtynge of þe feiþ, &amp; take þe eferlastynge lyf, in þe whuche þow art y-cleped, &amp; hast y-knowleched a good knowlechynge to-fore many wytnesses.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.13" type="verse">&amp; ich hote þe to-fore God in Iesu Crist, þat makeþ alle þinges lyfen in Iesu Crist, þat ȝef a testymony vnder Pylat of Pounce, a good knowlechynge,
<seg id="b.1TI.6.14" type="verse">þat þow kepe þe comaundement, wiþ-outen wem, vnreprefabel,
<seg id="b.1TI.6.15" type="verse">in-to þe comynge of oure Lord Iesu Crist: whom he schal schewen in his tyme, þat is y-blessed, and al-one myȝty,
<seg id="b.1TI.6.16" type="verse">&amp; Kyng of kynges &amp; Lord of lordes; þat onlyche haþ vndedlynesse, &amp; dwelleþ in lyȝt þat no man may come to, ne no man haþ y-seyn, ne may y-sen it nouþ ; to whom be worschype &amp; blysse &amp; empyre efer wiþ-outen ende. Amen.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.17" type="verse">And byde þou ryche men of þis worlde, þat þei ne safere noȝt an hyȝ, ne þat þey ne hope noȝt in þe vncertaynte of rychesse, bote in þe lyfynge God, þat graunteþ to ous alle
<seg id="b.1TI.6.18" type="verse">þinges plentefouslyche to vsen, &amp; to don wel, &amp; to ben y-mad ryche in goode werkes, &amp; to ȝefen lyȝtlyche &amp; to comune hure
<seg id="b.1TI.6.19" type="verse">goodes; &amp; to maken tresour &amp; a good foundement her-after, þat þei take an eferlastynge lyf.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.1" type="verse">And alle þilke þat beþ in seruytute, worschypen þei hure lordes alle worschupe, leste þe name of God &amp; his doctrine be blasphemed.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.20" type="verse">Tymothe, kepe þat þing þat is y-put to þe, &amp; schonye wykked nofeltees of speches &amp;
<seg id="b.1TI.6.21" type="verse">þe opposynges of þe fals name of connynge, whom þat summen han by-hote &amp; han y-fallen from þe feiþ. Þe grace of God be wiþ þe. Amen.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.2" type="verse">And þilke þat habbeþ feiþful lordes, ne despyseþ þei noȝt hem, for þei beþ hure breþeren; bote serfen hem þe raþer, þat þei beþ feiþful &amp; y-lofed &amp; partyneres of þe benefys of God. Þese þynges teche þou &amp; stere hem þerto.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.3" type="verse">&amp; ȝef eny man teche oþer-wyse, &amp; assenteþ not to þe hol wordes of þe doctryne of oure Lord
<seg id="b.1TI.6.4" type="verse">Iesu Crist, &amp; to þe techynge of pyte; he is proud , knowynge no þing, bote longynge aboute questyones &amp; stryfynges of wordes, of whom ryseþ up enuyes &amp; stryfynges, blasphemyes,
<seg id="b.1TI.6.5" type="verse">efel suspycyones, fyȝtynges of men þat beþ corrupt in þouȝt &amp; beþ depryfed of trewþe, þat weneþ þat getynge by pyte.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.6" type="verse">,
<seg id="b.1TI.6.7" type="verse">Bote a ful gret getynge is pyte wiþ suffysaunce: for we broȝten no þing in-to þis world, &amp; it is certayn wiþ-oute doute þat we mowen beren no þing a-wey.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.8" type="verse">Bote hafe we lyflode &amp; what we mowen ben y-wrye wiþ, holde we ous a-payd þerwiþ.
<seg id="b.1TI.6.9" type="verse">For þilke þat wolleþ ben y-mad ryche men, þei falleþ in-to temptacyoun &amp; in-to þe defeles grun &amp; in-to many vnprofytabel desyres &amp; noyful , þat drencheþ men in-to deþ &amp; in-to perdycyoun.
<seg id="b.2CO.1.10" type="verse">beþ y-chasted, &amp; nouȝt y-slawe; as þilke þat beþ drery, bote efermore ioyenge; as þilke þat beþ nedy, bote makyng many men ryche; as þilke þat hafeþ noȝt, bote oweþ alle þinges.
<seg id="b.2CO.1.11" type="verse">Oure mouþ is opned to ȝow, ȝe Corynthes, oure herte is y-drawen a-brood.
<seg id="b.2CO.1.12" type="verse">Ne be ȝe noȝt y-angwysched in ous, bote be ȝe y-angwysched in ȝoure owne in-wardnesse.
<seg id="b.2CO.1.13" type="verse">&amp; hafynge þe same remuneracyoun, as to my chyldren y seye, Be ȝe y-drawen abrood.
<seg id="b.2CO.1.14" type="verse">Ne lede ȝe no ȝok wiþ mysbylefed men: for what a-cord is þer bytwene riȝtfulnesse &amp; wykkednesse? oþer what felowschupe bytwene lyȝt &amp; derknesse?
<seg id="b.2CO.1.15" type="verse">Oþer what a-cord by-twene Crist &amp; þe defel? oþer what party haþ a welbyleued man wiþ a mysbyleued man?
<seg id="b.2CO.1.16" type="verse">Oþer what assent bytwene þe temple of God &amp; wiþ mawmetes? For ȝe beþ þe temple of lyfynge God ; as God seiþ hym-selfen, Y wole dwellen in hem, &amp; y wole wonen a-mong hem; &amp; y wole ben hure God, &amp; þei schuleþ be my pepel.
<seg id="b.2CO.1.17" type="verse">Wherfore God seyþ, Goo ȝe a-wey from þe myddel of hem, &amp; be ȝe departyd from hem, &amp; ne touche ȝe non vnclene þing; and y
<seg id="b.2CO.1.18" type="verse">wole resceyue ȝou, &amp; y wole be ȝoure Fadur, &amp; ȝe schulen be my sones &amp; my douȝteren. Sustur, in þis manere seynt Poule wryteþ to þe Corynthes.
<seg id="b.2CO.1.1" type="verse">And , breþeren, helpynge ȝow we bysecheþ þat ȝe ne
<seg id="b.2CO.1.2" type="verse">resceyfeþ noȝt þe grace of God in veyn; for he haþ y-sayd, In an acceptabel tyme y haue y-herd þe, &amp; in þe day of hele y haue y-holpe þe; and lo, now is an acceptabel tyme, and a day of hele.
<seg id="b.2CO.1.3" type="verse">&amp; ȝefe ȝe non offencyoun to no man, þat ȝoure
<seg id="b.2CO.1.4" type="verse">seruyse ne be not y-blamed; bote in alle þinges ȝefe we ousseluen as Goddes serfauntes, in myche pacyence, in tribulacyones,
<seg id="b.2CO.1.5" type="verse">in nedyschepe, in angwysch, in woundynges, in prisonynges, in bytrayynges, in wakynges , in trauayles, in
<seg id="b.2CO.1.6" type="verse">fastynges, in chastyte, in kunnynge, in longe abydynge, in
<seg id="b.2CO.1.7" type="verse">softnesse, in þe Holy Gost, in charite noȝt y-feyned, in word of trewþe, in þe uertu of God; þorouȝ þe armer of riȝtfulnesse
<seg id="b.2CO.1.8" type="verse">on þe riȝtsyde &amp; on þe lyftsyde, þoroȝ worschupe &amp; vnnobelnesse, þoroȝ diffamynge &amp; good loos; as gylores, bote as men
<seg id="b.2CO.1.9" type="verse">þat beþ trewe; &amp; þouȝ ȝe ben y-knowe, ȝet be ȝe as þilke þat beþ vnknowe; as þilke þat dyeþ, &amp; lo, we lyfeþ; as þilke þat
<seg id="b.2JO.1.10" type="verse">Who-so comeþ vnto ȝow, &amp; bryngeþ not wiþ hym þis lore , ne wyle ȝe not resceyue hym
<seg id="b.2JO.1.11" type="verse">in ȝoure hous , ne sey not heyl vnto hym: he þat seiþ heyl to hym, he comuneþ with his wikked werkes . Lo, y haue warned ȝow byfore, þat in þe day of oure Lord ȝe be noȝt confounded.
<seg id="b.2JO.1.12" type="verse">Many þinges y haue to wryte vn-to ȝow, bote y wolde not wryte hem by lettere ne by sendynge: for y suppose me come to ȝow, and speke with ȝow mouþ to mouþ, þat ȝoure ioye be full.
<seg id="b.2JO.1.13" type="verse">þer greteþ þe wel ȝoure chosen þi suster douȝter. Þe grace of God be with þe. Amen.
<seg id="b.2JO.1.2" type="verse">han knowen ; for þe soþfastnes þat in ȝou dwelleþ, &amp; wiþ ous schal be wiþ-outen end.
<seg id="b.2JO.1.3" type="verse">Wiþ ȝou b grace, &amp; mercy, &amp; pees of God þe Fader, &amp; of Iesu Crist, þe Sone of þe Fader, in soþfastnesse &amp; charyte.
<seg id="b.2JO.1.4" type="verse">Ych am wel gladud, for y haue founde of þi chyldren goynge in soþfastnes , as we haue taken comaundement of oure Fadur.
<seg id="b.2JO.1.5" type="verse">And now, dame, y preye þe, not as wrytynge to þe a newe comaundement, but þat we haue had fro þe bygynnyng, þat eche of ous loue oþer.
<seg id="b.2JO.1.6" type="verse">&amp; þat is charyte, þat we walken after his comaundementys . Þis is soþly þe comaundement, þat ryȝt as ȝe haue
<seg id="b.2JO.1.7" type="verse">For many dysceyueres ȝeden forþ in-to þe world, þat ne knowlecheþ noȝt Iesu Crist in flesch haue come . He þat soþly is noȝt a-knowe Iesu Crist haue comen in flesch, he is a disceyuere &amp; Antecrist.
<seg id="b.2JO.1.8" type="verse">Takeþ good heede to ȝow-selfe , þat ȝe lese noȝt þat ȝe han wroȝt, but þat ȝe take ȝoure fulle mede.
<seg id="b.2JO.1.9" type="verse">Wyte ȝe, þat eche þat goþ awey &amp; dwelleþ not in þe lore of Crist, he haþ not God: who-so dwelleþ in his lore, he haþ boþe þe Fader &amp; þe Sone.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.10" type="verse">And þerfore, breþeren, be ȝe aboute to maken ȝoure clepynge &amp; ȝoure chesynge certeyn by ȝoure goode werkes: &amp; doynge
<seg id="b.2PE.1.10" type="verse">Wherfore, my dere breþeren, beþ þe more bysy, þat þorow ȝoure goode werkes þat ȝe do &amp; fulfylle ȝowre certeyn clepynge &amp; chesynge (þat is, þat ȝe fulfylle þe dedus þat ȝe beþ chosen and clepyd to) . Soþly if ȝe þus do, &amp; ȝoure clepynge fulfille, þan ȝe schul not synne.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.11" type="verse">And þanne schal abundynglyche (þat is, plenteouslyche) be ȝeuen to ȝow, wher-þorow ȝe schul haue entre in-to þe euere-lastynge kyngdom of oure Lord &amp; Iesu Crist oure saueoure.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.11" type="verse">þese þynges ȝe schulleþ do no synne: &amp; so þer schal be i-mynystred to ȝow plentyuouslyche an entre in-to þe euerlastynge kyngdom of oure Lord &amp; oure Sauyour Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.12" type="verse">Wharfore ich wole by-gynne to warne ȝow of þese þinges, þat knoweþ &amp; beþ y-confermed in þis present trewþe.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.12" type="verse">Wherfore I schal bygynne to meue ȝow &amp; telle ȝow eueremore of þes þinges, þat ȝe soþly be in þem stabled &amp; confermed in soþfastnes.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.13" type="verse">For y deme þat it is ryȝtful, as longe as ich am in þis tabernakel, to
<seg id="b.2PE.1.13" type="verse">Soþly me þinkeþ it riȝtwis, as longe as I schal dwelle in this wonyngestede, (þat is, þe whyle I lyue) to rere ȝow (þat is, to stere ȝow) in warnynges &amp; techynges.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.14" type="verse">arere ȝow up in warnynge; For ich am certeyn þat þe doynge awey of my tabernakel is nyȝ, as oure Lord Iesu Crist haþ y-sygnyfyed to me.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.14" type="verse">Serteyn I am þat smert &amp; hasty is þe doynge dowen of my tabernacle (þat is, I am certeyn þat hastely &amp; sone schal come þe tyme of my departynge of body and of soule) , after þat at oure Lorde Iesu Criste haþ ordeynyd to me.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.15" type="verse">&amp; I schal ȝeue ȝow enchesoun þat I may haue ȝow aftur my deed, þat ȝe haue in mynde þes þynges þat I telle ȝow in my lyfe.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.15" type="verse">And ich wole ȝeue my dylygence to haue ȝow fele syþes after my deþ þat ȝe maken mynde of þese þinges.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.16" type="verse">Ȝe schul not folow þis techynge, as it were yuel tauȝt fabules we haue maad knowen vn-to ȝow: þe vertu &amp; þe for-knowynge of God. But I wele þat ȝe be byholderes of his grete dedus:
<seg id="b.2PE.1.16" type="verse">For we ne haueþ noȝt y-folewed vnwyse fables &amp; y-mad ȝow knowen þe vertue of oure Lord, bote we weren y-mad by-holderes of his gretnesse.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.17" type="verse">For he vnderfong of God þe Fader worschyp &amp; blisse, of a voys þat slod a-doun to hym from þe grete blisse of þe Fadur &amp; seyde, Þis is my leue sone, in whom ich am y-plesed ; y-here ȝe hym.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.17" type="verse">takynge of God the Fadur honoure &amp; ioye, þorow þe voice þat come glydynge fro heuene, fro þe fadur to þe sone, seyinge on þis wyse fro his fulgrete ioye, Here is, or, þis is my deere sone, in whom muche lykyng Iche haue hadde; heere ȝe him.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.18" type="verse">&amp; þis voice we herde fro heuene brouȝte, whanne we were wiþ him in þe holy hylle.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.18" type="verse">And þis voys we herden come from heuene, when we weren wiþ hym in þe holy hul .
<seg id="b.2PE.1.19" type="verse">&amp; we han a more syker word of
<seg id="b.2PE.1.19" type="verse">&amp; we haue þe more ful trewþe &amp; word of prophecye, &amp; in þat ȝe do wele þat ȝe take heede þer-to, as to a lanterne lyȝtenynge in a derke place, forto þe day schyne, &amp; lucifer, the grete sterne, be resen in ȝoure hertis, þat schyneþ so briȝt.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.1" type="verse">Symon Peter, Iesu Cristes seruaunt &amp; apostel, to þilke þat haueþ euene feiþ wiþ ous, þe riȝtfulnesse of oure God,
<seg id="b.2PE.1.1" type="verse">Symon Petre, the seruawnte &amp; þe apostul of Iesu Crist, to hem þat haue taken feiþ euen wiþ vs, in ryȝtwisnesse of oure God &amp; oure saueoure Iesu Crist:
<seg id="b.2PE.1.20" type="verse">And furst vnderstonde ȝe, þat eueriche prophecye of scripture ne is
<seg id="b.2PE.1.21" type="verse">noȝt y-mad in his owene interpretacyoun: For prophecye ne is noȝt y-brouȝt of a mannes owene wylle: bote holy men han y-spoke as þe Holy Spiryt of God hath enspyred hem.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.21" type="verse">Soþely al tyme prophecye is not ȝeuen aftur mannes wille: but alle þe holy seyntes þorow þe Holy Gost spaken þat were enspyred of him.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.2" type="verse">&amp; oure Sauyour Iesu Crist: Grace &amp; pes be fulfillyd to ȝou in þe knowynge of oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.2" type="verse">grace be to ȝow, &amp; pees be fulfillyd in þe knowynge of oure Lord.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.3" type="verse">How alle þinges beþ y-graunted to us, to lif &amp; to pyte, of þe vertue of his godhede, þoroȝ þe knowynge of hym þat haþ y-cleped ous þoroȝ
<seg id="b.2PE.1.3" type="verse">How þat alle þinges beþ ȝeuen to ȝow, þorow þe vertu of God, þe whuche beþ nedeful, &amp; beþ ȝeue to ȝow to lyf &amp; to pyte, by knowynge or
<seg id="b.2PE.1.4" type="verse">by þe whuche vertu moste &amp; precyous byhestes he haþ ȝeuen ȝow; þat þorow him ȝe be maked felowis of þe kynde of God, fleynge þe corrupcyoun of desyres þat beþ in the worlde.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.4" type="verse">his owene blisse &amp; his vertue; by whom he haþ y-graunted ous grete byhestes &amp; precyouse; þat we ben y-maad by hym felawes of þe kynde of þe godhede, fleynge þe corrupcyoun þat is in þe worlde.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.5" type="verse">And ȝe wiþ al ȝoure bysynesse mynystreþ
<seg id="b.2PE.1.5" type="verse">And þerfore putteþ al ȝoure bysynesse to vse vertu in ȝoure feiþ, in vertu to haue connynge,
<seg id="b.2PE.1.6" type="verse">in ȝoure feiþ vertu, in vertu connynge , in connynge abstynence,
<seg id="b.2PE.1.6" type="verse">soþly in kunnynge abstynence, pacyence, in pacyence onlyche of pyte,
<seg id="b.2PE.1.7" type="verse">in abstynence pacyence, in pacyence pyte, in pyte loue of bryþerhed , in loue of bryþerhede charyte.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.7" type="verse">in pyte loue of breþurhede, in brur loue of charite:
<seg id="b.2PE.1.8" type="verse">And ȝef þese þinges ben in ȝow, þei ne schuleþ noȝt make ȝow veyn ne wiþ-outen fruyt in þe knowynge of oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.8" type="verse">Soþly if þis be ȝoure lederis &amp; wiþ ȝow, þei wele leue ȝow voyde, wiþ-outen fruyt in þe knowynge of oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.9" type="verse">And he þat haþ noȝt þese þinges, he is blynd, and gropynge wiþ his hond, &amp; forȝeteþ þe purgacyoun of his olde synnes.
<seg id="b.2PE.1.9" type="verse">Soþly whoso is not redy to þis, soþly he is blynde, &amp; suffereþ temptacyon to muche to haue power in him, forgetynge to muche þe clensynge of his olde synnys.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.10" type="verse">&amp; soþly more hem þat aftur here flesche in desyres of vnclennes walke; to haue any lordschupe þei dispice it (þat is, eny lord to haue ouere hem) ; bolde þei be, &amp; drede not to gadere to hem lykynge companyis, gyses &amp; sectes newe for-to ordeyne, þe whuche be blasphemaris;
<seg id="b.2PE.2.10" type="verse">peynes; &amp; raþere hem þat walkeþ aftur þe flesch in couetyse of vnclannesse , &amp; despyseþ þe lordschupe; bodylyche plesynge to hem-selfe ne dredeþ noȝt to bryngen in sectes
<seg id="b.2PE.2.11" type="verse">blasphemynge God, wher þat aungeles, þat beþ grettere in
<seg id="b.2PE.2.11" type="verse">siþen þat angelis beþ of more vertu &amp; strengþ, þei take no mynde of þat dredeful dome þat schal be ȝeue aȝeyn hem.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.12" type="verse">And þese beþ as vnresonabel bestes, kyndelyche in-to takynge &amp; in-to deþ, blasphemynge in þinges þat þei knoweþ noȝt, in hure corrupcyoun þei schulen peryschen, vnderfongynge þe mede of vnryȝtfulnesse.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.12" type="verse">Þei soþly as it were vnresonable bestes, þat þorow sleyȝtus be taken or þei wite, so þe blasphemaris in here fylþe schal preche, takynge of vnriȝtwisnes.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.13" type="verse">For þei wende þe lustus of þis worlde &amp; þe fylþe &amp; þe lykynges hadde ben delices, folowynge in þer lykynges, in þer festus doynge lecherye,
<seg id="b.2PE.2.13" type="verse">Þese weneþ þat lustes ben delyces of day , &amp; beþ fulfylled wiþ þe delyces of wem of defoulynge, &amp; doþ leccherye wiþ ȝow in hure
<seg id="b.2PE.2.14" type="verse">hauynge here ȝen ful of a-uoutries, wiþouten sessynge of here synne; hauynge rowe soules &amp; vnstable; &amp; vsynge þer hertes in auaryce; childeren of malyson,
<seg id="b.2PE.2.14" type="verse">leccheryes; and haueþ yen ful of avoutrye, &amp; of gult þat may noȝt cessen; deceyfynge soules vnstabel ; habbeþ hure
<seg id="b.2PE.2.15" type="verse">herte y-stered to coueytyse; children of cursynge; &amp; leuynge þe ryȝte weye han y-erred &amp; han y-swed þe weye of Baalam
<seg id="b.2PE.2.15" type="verse">ȝoden omysse, forsakynge ryȝt weye, &amp; folwed þe weye of Baalam, þe whuche loued mede of wickednes;
<seg id="b.2PE.2.16" type="verse">&amp; Booȝor, þat loued þe mede of wyckednesse; bote he had a doumbe beste þat was vnder ȝok a mendement of his wodnesse, spekynge in mannys voys, þat forbed þe vnkunnyngnesse of þe prophete.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.16" type="verse">soþly blamed he was of his wodnesse of a doume beste—as who seiþ, he spak not as resonable man, but as a doume beste þat vndur synne was ȝoked—vndur ȝokke, spekynge wiþ mannes voyce &amp; of his vn-wytte of þe prophete was him forbode, seyinge on þis wyse,
<seg id="b.2PE.2.17" type="verse">Þese beþ welles wiþouten water, &amp; cloudes y-dryfen a-boute wiþ whirlynge wyndes, to whom þe dymschyp of derknesse is y-kept to.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.17" type="verse">Þis beþ welles wiþ-outen watur, &amp; cloudes þrowen aboute wiþ stormes (þat is, þei þat schulde haue watur of wysdom &amp; techynge as men of holy churche, þei been alle drye, &amp; þe cundyte of grace renneþ nouȝt to hem: but beþ cloudes derke wiþ synne, þrowen a-boute wiþ stormes of temptacyon. Þus vndurstonde I þis.) in þe whuche dymnes of derkenes is kept;
<seg id="b.2PE.2.18" type="verse">&amp; spekynge in pruyde of vanyte bygyleþ in þe desyres of þe leccherye of hure flesch þilke þat fleþ a luytel weye from hem; &amp; þei
<seg id="b.2PE.2.18" type="verse">spekynge proude þinges of vanyte, deseyuynge hem in desyres of leccherye of flesche þat tristeþ to hem; &amp; opynly lyfen in here errour,
<seg id="b.2PE.2.19" type="verse">by-hotynge to hem frenes, &amp; by hem-selue bounde &amp; seruantes of corupcyon. Soþly of whom-so eny is ouercomen &amp; þus defoulyd, his seruant he is.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.19" type="verse">haueþ hure conuersacyoun in errour, byhotynge to hem fredom &amp; beþ hem-selfen seruauntis of corrupcyoun. For of whom a man is ofercome, his serfaunt he is.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.1" type="verse">And þer han ben her byfore false prophetys in þe pepel, as þer schulen ben her-after a-mong ȝow maystres of lesynges, þat schuleþ bryngen in sectes of perdycyoun, &amp; forsakynge hure Lord þat haþ y-bouȝt hem, &amp; bryngynge an hasty perdicyoun to hem-selfen.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.1" type="verse">Ther were soþly also fals prophetus a-mong þe folke, ryȝt as a-mong ȝow schul be mayster lyeris, þat bryngen vppe newe sectis (þat is, newe religyon &amp; newe gyses) of dampnacyoun, &amp; þat Lord þat bouȝte hem schul þei denye, chesynge hem a ledere of loste &amp; dampnacyoun.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.20" type="verse">For ȝef men flen þe defoulynge of þe world in þe knowynge of oure Lord Iesu Crist, &amp; afterward medlen wiþ þe same þinges, &amp; ben ofercomen of hem, hure later doynges beþ worse þan þe raþer.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.20" type="verse">Soþly who-so feleþ þe fylynges of þe worlde in knowynge of oure Saueoure &amp; oure Lord Iesu Criste, &amp; efte in þe same ben ouercome, þanne þat lattere fallynge is wors vnto hem þan þe firste was.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.21" type="verse">For it were beter to hem noȝt for-to knowe þe weye of ryȝtfulnes, þan, after þe knowynge, turnen hem aȝeynward from þe holy commaundement þat is y-take to hem.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.21" type="verse">Soþly betre it were to hem not to knowe þe weye of ryȝtwisnesse, þan, aftur þat þei haue knowen it, to turne awey þer-fro aftur þat it is ȝeuen us in holy comawndement.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.22" type="verse">And to hem falleþ þe seyenge of þe trewe prouerbe, Þe hound haþ y-turned hym aȝeyn forto caste, &amp; þe sowe is y-wasche in þe gaseyn of fen.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.22" type="verse">Soþly to hem falleþ þe trewe prouerbe þat is seyde. Lyke þei ben to an hounde þat turneþ aȝeyn to ete þat he haþ spewe, and also to þe sowe þat wascheþ hyre in þe podel wiþ mukke al fyled.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.2" type="verse">&amp; many schul folowe aftur here leccheryes (þat is to seye, þer schal come in holy churche maysterus þat schul mayntene lesynges, boþe of lerid &amp; lewyd, peruertynge
<seg id="b.2PE.2.2" type="verse">&amp; many schul swe her leccheryes, by whom þe weye of trewþe schal ben blasphemed.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.3" type="verse">&amp; þorow auaryce (þei schul be erandebereris &amp; depraueris to lette ȝow) in ȝoure wordis, &amp; ȝoure deedus þei schul bye &amp; sylle (þat is, in þat ȝe teche þe peple þe peryl of yuel lyf to make hem to haue drede, in þat þei schul bye &amp; sylle her synne for syluer &amp; for golde) , to whom þe dome now ne somtyme sessiþ noȝt, &amp; here dampnacyoun slepeþ nouȝt.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.3" type="verse">And þei schuleþ chaffaren of ȝow wiþ feyned wordis in here couetyse: bote hure dom ne cesseþ noȝt, ne hure perdicyoun ne slepeþ noȝt.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.4" type="verse">For ȝef God ne sparyd not aungelis þat synneden, bote þrew hem doun in-to helle, &amp; toke hem to ben y-turmentyd
<seg id="b.2PE.2.4" type="verse">Soþly if God sparud not to þe aungeles þat synnede, but bytoke hem to be drawen wiþ þe romynynge deueles of helle, whan þei deuelis bycome, echone to drawe oþur, euere þere to be turmentid, kepid vn-to þe dome.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.5" type="verse">&amp; origynale worlde he sparud not, but al it fordide, safe Noe &amp; þo þat wiþ him were, wiþ þe grete flode.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.5" type="verse">&amp; y-kept to þe dom; And ȝef he ne spared not þe orygynal worlde &amp; kept Noe þe eyȝteþe man, þat was a bedel &amp; a fore-goere of ryȝtfulnesse, &amp; broȝte a gret flod in-to þe
<seg id="b.2PE.2.6" type="verse">And þe cytees of Sodome &amp; Gomorre turnyd it in-to poudre orow his vpturnynge, &amp; dampnede hem alle, ȝeuynge hem ensample þat aftur wolde do yuele;
<seg id="b.2PE.2.6" type="verse">worlde of wycked men; &amp; ȝef he ouer-turned þe cytees of Sodom &amp; Gomor , &amp; turned hem in-to axen , &amp; dampned, &amp; putte hem þe ensampel of hem þat schulden don wyckedlyche;
<seg id="b.2PE.2.7" type="verse">&amp; delyuered Loth þat was a ryȝtful man and oppressed of þe iniurye of wycked men &amp; of hure leccherous
<seg id="b.2PE.2.7" type="verse">&amp; þe ryȝtwyse Loth þat wiþ þe wickede was ouerlyen, &amp; holdun dowen wiþ here vnriȝtwyse lyfynge, God him fayre delyuerede:
<seg id="b.2PE.2.8" type="verse">conuersacioun: for boþe in byholdynge and in herynge he was ryȝtful, wonynge among hem þat from day to day þoroȝ hure wycked werkes turmenteden a ryȝtful soule.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.8" type="verse">soþly þorow syȝt &amp; herynge ryȝt-wyse he was dwellynge a-monges hem, þat from day to day his ryȝt-wyse soule wiþ wickede dedus þei turmented.
<seg id="b.2PE.2.9" type="verse">&amp; God can delyueren goode men out of temptacioun, &amp; kepen wycked men in-to þe day of dom, to ben y-turmented in
<seg id="b.2PE.2.9" type="verse">God wolde his ryȝtwyse from temptacyoun delyuere, and soþly þe wicked vnto þe day of dome in peyne &amp; turmentis hem kepede;
<seg id="b.2PE.3.10" type="verse">And þe day of oure Lord schal comen as a þef; in þe whuche day hefne schal passen in a gret hastynesse, &amp; þe elementes schuleþ ben vnbounde þoroȝ hete , &amp; þe erþe &amp; al þe werkes þat beþ þer-ynne schuleþ ben y-brand.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.10" type="verse">Soþfastly þe day of God sodeynly schal come as a þef vnwarned, in whos comynge hastyly heuenes schul passe (þat is, heuenly soules schul passe fro þe dredeful dome vnto þe blisse of heuene) , þe elementes soþly þorow hete schul be vndone, &amp; þorow brennynge of fyre þei schul be wastud, þe erþe soþly &amp; alle þinges þat schal be þere-inne, alle þei schul be brent.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.11" type="verse">And seþþe alle þese þinges schuleþ ben vndon, Whyche byhoueþ it þat we ben in
<seg id="b.2PE.3.11" type="verse">Þerfore syþen alle þes beþ to be vndone, how nedeful is it þanne to us to be holy in lyfynge &amp; pyte,
<seg id="b.2PE.3.12" type="verse">abydynge &amp; makynge us redy aȝeyn þe dredful comynge of oure Lord Iesu Criste, þorow whom heuenes brennynge
<seg id="b.2PE.3.12" type="verse">holy conuersacyones &amp; pytees, abydynge &amp; hyȝenge in þe comynge of oure Lord, þorouȝ whom brennynge hefnes schuleþ ben vndon, &amp; þe elementys schuleþ roten þoroȝ þe hete of þe fuyr?
<seg id="b.2PE.3.13" type="verse">&amp; we abydeþ newe hefnes &amp; a newe erþe &amp; his byhestes, in þe whuche riȝtfulnesse woneþ ynne.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.13" type="verse">Soþfastly newe heuenes &amp; newe erþe we abyde &amp; his byhestes, in þe whyche ryȝtwysnes dwelliþ.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.14" type="verse">And þerfore, my dereste breþeren, be ȝe abydynge wiþ-outen wem and vndefouled, &amp; schape ȝe ȝow to ben y-founden in pes.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.14" type="verse">Wherfore abydynge þes þinges, my dere breþeren, bysy ȝow to be founden a-nentes him in pees vnsoyled &amp; vnfouled,
<seg id="b.2PE.3.15" type="verse">&amp; deme þat þe longe a-bydynge of oure Lord Iesu Crist is hele, as oure dereste broþer Poule, aftyr þe wysdom þat was
<seg id="b.2PE.3.15" type="verse">&amp; trowiþ wel þat þe longe a-bydynge of oure Lord Iesu Crist is for oure hele, ryȝt as oure dere broþur Poule, aftur þe witte þat was ȝeuen him, wrote vnto ȝow;
<seg id="b.2PE.3.16" type="verse">&amp; as he in alle his pistelys spake of þes þinges, in þe whyche somme beþ harde to vndurstonde, þat þei þat be vnstable &amp; vn-tauȝt deprauen, as þei don oþur wrytynges, vnto þeire oune dampnacyon.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.16" type="verse">y-grauntyd hym, wrot to ȝou; as he haþ y-don in his oþer
<seg id="b.2PE.3.17" type="verse">And þerfore, ȝe my breþeren, knowiþ it byfore, kepeþ ȝoure-self, þat þorow þe errour of hem þat beþ vnwyse ȝe be nouȝt deceyuyd, fallynge fro ȝoure firste strengþe.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.17" type="verse">And þerfore, my breþeren, seþþe ȝe knowe þese þinges byfore, kepeþ ȝow-selfe, þat ȝe ben noȝt y-lad in þe errour of vn-wyse men, &amp; fallen awey þoroȝ ȝoure owene infirmyte.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.18" type="verse">Bote waxe ȝe in þe knowynge &amp; in þe grace of oure Lord Iesu Crist oure Sauyour; to hym be blysse now &amp; efermore her-aftur. De gracias?
<seg id="b.2PE.3.18" type="verse">But beþ wexynge in grace &amp; in þe knowynge of oure Saueoure Iesu Crist; to him be ioye &amp; worschupe, worlde wiþ-outen ende. Amen.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.1" type="verse">And lo, my leueste frendes, y write to ȝow þis seconde
<seg id="b.2PE.3.1" type="verse">My dere breþeren, I wryte þis vnto ȝow to be ȝoure secunde pistil in þe whyche I stere ȝoure ful clere myndes þorowe biddynge &amp; bysekynge,
<seg id="b.2PE.3.2" type="verse">epystel to stere ȝow in-to warnynge to a cler þouȝt , þat ȝe
<seg id="b.2PE.3.2" type="verse">þat ȝe þenke vpon þe wordis þat Crist haþ spoken vnto ȝowe and of þe apostelus wordes, &amp; also of þe prophetes, &amp; of þe comawndementis of oure Lord &amp; oure Sauyour.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.3" type="verse">&amp; wyte ȝe wel þat first þer schal come in þe laste dayes bygyleris to disceyue, þat schal rewel hem aftur þeir owne lustus &amp; þer lykynges,
<seg id="b.2PE.3.3" type="verse">And knowe ȝe furst, þat þer schuleþ comen men in þe laste dayes in deceyt gylours, walkynge
<seg id="b.2PE.3.4" type="verse">after hure owene coueyse , &amp; seyenge, Where is þe byheste oþer þe comynge of hym? For, seþþe þat oure fadres habbeþ y-slept, alle þinges abydeþ stylle from þe bygynnynge of creatures.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.4" type="verse">&amp; bschul seye (þat is, of Crist to helpe &amp; to deme) Where is his byheste, or where is his comynge? Seþen þat þe olde fadrus were deede, ȝut alle þinge lastuþ þus fro þe bygynnynge of eche creature.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.5" type="verse">Bote to þilke þat han þis wyl it is y-hud from hem, For hefne was sumtyme, and erþe, of watyr &amp; abydynge þoroȝ watyr by þe word of God.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.5" type="verse">But þei haue no mynde how þat he made heuene &amp; erþe, see &amp; londe, &amp; alle þorow his worde.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.6" type="verse">By whom þe world was þo y-clensed &amp; perysched by watyr.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.6" type="verse">Þorow þe whuche word he distroyede þanne þorow flowynge water al þe worlde, saue a fewe þat were kept.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.7" type="verse">Bote hefnes þat beþ now , &amp; þe erþe, þoroȝ þe same word beþ y-kept to fuyr in-to þe day of dome, &amp; of perdycyoun of wycked men.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.7" type="verse">Soþly þe heuenys þat now ben &amp; erþe wiþ þe same worde—þat is, to heuene schal be fordon &amp; erþe schal brenne—beþ maked a-ȝeyn, &amp; kepte vnto þe fyre on þe day of dome, &amp; vnto þe day of lesynge &amp; peryschynge of þe wickede men.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.8" type="verse">Bote naþeles, my dere frendes , þis on þing ne be noȝt y-hud from ȝow, þat on day is to-fore God as a þousande ȝeres , &amp; a þousande ȝeer as on day.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.8" type="verse">But o þinge, my dere breþeren, be knowen to ȝow &amp; not hyde, þat o day wiþ God is as it were a þousande ȝeere, &amp; a þousande ȝere but as it were o day.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.9" type="verse">And God ne targeþ noȝt his byheste as summe men weneþ; bote doþ pacyentlyche for ȝow, &amp; nul none men perysche, Bote þat alle men ben y-turnyd aȝeyn to penaunce.
<seg id="b.2PE.3.9" type="verse">God taryeþ not in þinges þat he haþ byhette as some folke wene; but sufferyngelyche he abyduþ vs, willynge þat none perysche: but he wile þat alle be turned to penawnce in a-mendynge of here lyf.
<seg id="b.2TH.1.10" type="verse">blisse of his vertu, whenn þat he comeþ to ben y-gloryfyed in his seyntes, &amp; to ben wondurful in alle þilke þat han byleued, &amp; oure witnesse schal ben y-lefed on ȝou, in þat day.
<seg id="b.2TH.1.11" type="verse">&amp; we preyeþ euermore for ȝou, þat God fouche saaf to clepe ȝou þoroȝ his clepynge, and fulfulle al þe wylle of his
<seg id="b.2TH.1.12" type="verse">goodnesse &amp; þe werk of feyþ in verteu; þat þe name of oure Lord Iesu Crist be y-claryfyed in ȝou, &amp; ȝe wiþ hym þoroȝ þe grace of oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2TH.1.3" type="verse">And , breþeren, we oweþ to þanke God efermore for ȝou, as it is worþi, for efermore ȝoure feiþ waxeþ, &amp; ȝoure charite
<seg id="b.2TH.1.4" type="verse">waxeþ plenteous of eferichone to oþer; so þat we ous-selfe ioyeþ in ȝou in Goddes churches for ȝoure pacyence &amp; ȝoure feiþ in alle persecucyons and ȝoure tribulacyounes þat ȝe
<seg id="b.2TH.1.5" type="verse">suffreþ, in ensample of þe ryȝtful dom of God; þat ȝe ben y-had worþy to þe kyngdom of God, for whom ȝe suffreþ:
<seg id="b.2TH.1.6" type="verse">ȝif it be ryȝtful to-fore God to ȝelde trybulacyoun to þilke þat
<seg id="b.2TH.1.7" type="verse">anuyeþ ȝou, &amp; to ȝow þat haueþ trybulacyoun, reste wiþ ous , in þe reualacyoun of oure Lord Iesu Crist from hefne wiþ þe
<seg id="b.2TH.1.8" type="verse">angeles of his vertu, doynge veniaunce in lye of fuyr in hem þat ne haueþ noȝt y-knowe God, ne beþ noȝt buxom to
<seg id="b.2TH.1.9" type="verse">þe euangelye of oure Lord Iesu Crist: &amp; þei schulleþ ȝeuen eferlastynge peynes in deþ from þe face of oure Lord &amp; þe
<seg id="b.2TH.2.10" type="verse">Sathanas in eferich vertu &amp; sygnes &amp; false wondres, &amp; in eferych bygylynge of wykkednesse to þilke þat peryscheþ;
<seg id="b.2TH.2.11" type="verse">worchynge of errour, þat þei bylefen to lesynge; &amp; þat alle þei ben y-demed þat bylefeþ noȝt to þe trewþe, bote assenteden to wykkednesse.
<seg id="b.2TH.2.12" type="verse">Bote we oweþ efermore to þanke God for ȝow, þat beþ y-lofed of God, þat God haþ y-chosen ous þe furste fruyt in-to hele in þe holynesse of
<seg id="b.2TH.2.13" type="verse">Spiryt &amp; feiþ of trewþe, in þe whuche God haþ y-cleped ȝou by oure euangelye, in getynge of þe blisse of God &amp; of oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2TH.2.14" type="verse">&amp; þerfore, breþeren, stonde ȝe, &amp; holdeþ þe tradicyones þat ȝe han y-lerned, wheþer it be by word, oþer by oure epistel.
<seg id="b.2TH.2.15" type="verse">And oure Lord Iesu Crist, &amp; God oure Fader þat lofed ous &amp; haþ y-ȝefen ous an eferlastynge comfort
<seg id="b.2TH.2.16" type="verse">&amp; a good hope in grace, conferme ȝoure hertes in eferich good werk &amp; good word.
<seg id="b.2TH.2.1" type="verse">Bute breþeren, we preyeþ ȝou by þe comynge of oure Lord Iesu Crist, &amp; of oure congregacion in-to þe same þing,
<seg id="b.2TH.2.2" type="verse">þat ȝe ben noȝt sone y-mefed from ȝoure wyt, ne þat ȝe ben noȝt afrayed, as þouȝ þe day of oure Lord were y-come, nouþer by epystel, as þoȝ heo were y-send from ous, ne by spiryt, ne
<seg id="b.2TH.2.3" type="verse">by word; ne no man bygyle ȝou in no manere: for bote ȝif þat þer come dissencyoun furst, &amp; he be y-schewed, þat is
<seg id="b.2TH.2.4" type="verse">man of sunne &amp; child of perdycyoun, þat is aduersary &amp; y-hofen up a-bofen alle þinge þat is y-cleped God oþer heryed, so þat he sytte in þe temple of God, schewynge hymselfe as þouȝ he were a God.
<seg id="b.2TH.2.5" type="verse">Ne holde ȝe noȝt, þat þese þynges y sayde to ȝou, whyles þat ich was wiþ ȝou?
<seg id="b.2TH.2.6" type="verse">&amp; þat wiþholdeþ now ȝe knoweþ, þat he be y-schewed in his tyme.
<seg id="b.2TH.2.7" type="verse">For he wercheþ now þe mystery of wykkednesse: onlyche þat he þat holdeþ now, holde he, forto he be y-don out of þe myddel.
<seg id="b.2TH.2.8" type="verse">And þanne þilke wykked schal ben y-schewed, whom oure Lord Iesus schal slen wiþ þe spiryt of his mouþ, &amp; schal distroyen hym þoroȝ þe schynynge &amp; þe brytnesse of
<seg id="b.2TH.2.9" type="verse">his comynge; hym, whos comynge is þoroȝ þe worchynge of
<seg id="b.2TH.3.10" type="verse">For whyles þat ich was wiþ ȝow, þis y sayde to ȝow, He þat ne wol not trafaylen, ne ete he noȝt .
<seg id="b.2TH.3.11" type="verse">For we herden þat þer weren summe a-mong ȝow , þat walkeden in reste, worchynge no
<seg id="b.2TH.3.12" type="verse">And we chargeþ suche men &amp; bysecheþ hem in oure Lord Iesu Crist, þat þei worchen in sylence &amp; eten hure bred.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.13" type="verse">Bote breþeren, ne fayle ȝe noȝt wel doynge.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.14" type="verse">And hwo þat ne boweþ noȝt to oure word by þis epystel, marke ȝe hym, &amp; ne medleþ noȝt wiþ hym, þat he be confounded.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.15" type="verse">Bote ne holde hym not as ȝoure enemy, bote amendeþ hym as ȝoure broþer.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.16" type="verse">And God of pees he graunte ȝou pees in eferich place. And God be wiþ ȝow alle.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.1" type="verse">And breþeren, her-aftur preyeþ for ous, that Goddes word
<seg id="b.2TH.3.2" type="verse">renne &amp; be y-claryfyed, as it is wiþ ȝou; &amp; þat we ben delyuered from vncofenabel men &amp; wykked; for þe feiþ ne is noȝt of alle men.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.3" type="verse">Bote God is trewe, þat schal conferme ȝow &amp; kepe ȝou from yuel.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.4" type="verse">&amp; we trusteþ in ȝow in God, þat ȝe doþ &amp; schulen don þilke þinges þat we hafeþ y-bede ȝou don.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.5" type="verse">And oure Lord dresse ȝoure hertes in þe charite of God, &amp; in þe pacyence of Crist.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.6" type="verse">And breþeren, we chargeþ ȝou in þe name of oure Lord Iesu Crist, þat ȝe wiþ-drawe ȝou from eferich broþer þat walkeþ in-ordynatlyche , &amp; noȝt after þe tradycyon þat ȝe han vnderfongen of ous.
<seg id="b.2TH.3.7" type="verse">And ȝe ȝouselfen wyteþ hou it byhofeþ ȝou to folewen ous; for we ne were not
<seg id="b.2TH.3.8" type="verse">vnpesybel a-mong ȝow, ne eten noȝt oure bred of no mannes ȝefynge, bote trauayleden &amp; weren wery boþe nyȝt &amp; day, for
<seg id="b.2TH.3.9" type="verse">we ne wolden noȝt chargen no man of ȝou: noȝt as þoȝ we haden y-had no power, bote for we wolden ȝefen ous-selfe forme to ȝou, how ȝe schulden folewen ous.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.10" type="verse">y-passed, bote now it is y-schewed þoroȝ þe lyȝtynge of Iesu Crist oure Safyour, þat haþ distruyed deþ &amp; y-lyȝted lyf
<seg id="b.2TI.1.11" type="verse">&amp; in-corrupcyoun by þe euangely, in whom ich am y-set prechour, &amp; apostel, &amp; mayster of men þat weren mysbylefed.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.12" type="verse">For þe whuche enchesoun þis y suffre: bote y ne am noȝt confounded; for y wot to whom ich hafe bylefed, &amp; ich am certeyn þat he is myȝty þat tresour þat he haþ y-take me to kepe to kepen hym-selfe in-to þat day .
<seg id="b.2TI.1.13" type="verse">&amp; hafe þou þe forme of hole wordes þat þou hast y-herd of me, in feiþ &amp; in lofe þat is in Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.14" type="verse">And þe goode tresour þat is y-ȝefe þe by þe Holy Gost þat dwelleþ in ous, kepe þou.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.15" type="verse">For þow wost wel, þat alle þilke þat weren in Asya beþ y-turned awey from me; of whom weren Phylegeus and Hermogenes.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.16" type="verse">&amp; God hafe mercy on Honesyphores houshold : for ofte syþes he refresched
<seg id="b.2TI.1.17" type="verse">me, &amp; was noȝt a-schamed of my chayne; &amp; whenne he come to Rome, he soȝte me bysylyche for-to þat he fond
<seg id="b.2TI.1.18" type="verse">me—oure Lord graunte þat he fynde mercy in þat day—and how wel he mynystred to me at Ephese, þow knowest wel y-nowȝ.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.1" type="verse">And oþer epystel Poule wryteþ to Tymothe, &amp; seiþ, Poule Iesu Cristes apostel by þe wyl of God, after þe byheste of lyf
<seg id="b.2TI.1.2" type="verse">þat is in Iesu Crist, to Tymothe, my dereste sone: Grace, mercy, &amp; pes of God þe Fadur &amp; oure Lord Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.3" type="verse">And y þanke my God, to whom y serfe in a clene conscyence, þat ich hafe wiþ-outen cessynge mynde of þe in my preyeres ,
<seg id="b.2TI.1.4" type="verse">nyȝt &amp; day desyrynge to sen þe, hafynge þoȝt on þy teres of
<seg id="b.2TI.1.5" type="verse">wepynge, þat y be fulfulled wiþ ioye; byþinkynge on þe feiþ þat is in þe vnfeyned; þat dwelled furst in þi graundam Loyde, &amp; in þi moder Eurace: &amp; ich am certayn þat it is in þe.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.6" type="verse">For þe whuche enchesoun y warne þe þat þou arere up aȝeyn þe grace of God, þat is in þe by þe puttynge yn of myn honden.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.7" type="verse">For God ne haþ noȝt y-ȝefen ous a spyryt of drede: bote of vertu &amp; of lofe &amp; of sobernesse.
<seg id="b.2TI.1.8" type="verse">And þerfore ne be þou noȝt a-schamed of þe wytnesse of oure Lord Iesu Crist, ne of me þat am y-bounden: bote y trafayle neþeles to þe
<seg id="b.2TI.1.9" type="verse">euangelye, þoroȝ þe vertu of hym þat haþ delyfred ous &amp; haþ
<seg id="b.2TI.2.10" type="verse">&amp; þer-fore al þing y suffre for hem þat beþ y-chosen, þat þei ben y-safed þoroȝ þe hele of oure Lord Iesu Crist wiþ an hefnelyche blis.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.11" type="verse">A trew word: Ȝef we beþ dede
<seg id="b.2TI.2.12" type="verse">to-gedere with Crist, we schule lyfen to-gedere wiþ hym: &amp; ȝef we suffreþ, we schulleþ regne to-gedere: &amp; ȝef we forsakeþ
<seg id="b.2TI.2.13" type="verse">hym, he wole forsaken ous: ȝef we ne bylefeþ noȝt, he duelleþ stille trewe, &amp; he ne may noȝt forsaken hym-selfen .
<seg id="b.2TI.2.14" type="verse">Þese þinges warne þou, witnessynge to-fore God, &amp; ne stryfe þou noȝt in wordes, for þat is profytabel to no þing, bote to turnen hem up þat hereþ.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.15" type="verse">And be bysy to ȝefe þi-selfen y-prefed to God, &amp; a werk-man wiþ-outen schenschyp, tretynge ryȝtlyche þe word of trewþe.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.16" type="verse">And schenye þou boþe wykked speches &amp; veyn speches: for þei profyteþ muche
<seg id="b.2TI.2.17" type="verse">to wykkednesse, &amp; þe speche of hem crepeþ pryfelyche as
<seg id="b.2TI.2.18" type="verse">a cancre: of whom Phylet &amp; Ymene beþ, þat beþ y-fallen a-wey from þe trowþe, seyenge þat þe resurreccyoun of dede men is now y-don; &amp; þei turneþ up þe feiþ of summe men.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.19" type="verse">Bote þe stabel foundement of God stondeþ stylle, hafynge þys marke, Oure Lord haþ y-knowe þilke þat beþ of his: &amp;, Eferich man departeþ hym-selfe fro wykkednesse þat clepeþ þe name of oure Lord.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.1" type="verse">And þerfore, my sone, be þou y-comforted in þe grace þat
<seg id="b.2TI.2.20" type="verse">&amp; in a gret hous þer beþ noȝt onlyche vesseles of gold &amp; of sylfer, bote also of treo &amp; of erþe; and summe beþ to worschupe, &amp; summe to defoul.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.21" type="verse">Bote who þat makeþ hym-self clene from þese, he schal ben a vessel y-halewed in-to worschupe, and profytabel to God, and redy to eferich good werk.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.22" type="verse">&amp; fleo þou þe desyres of ȝouþe, bote folewe þou ryȝtfulnesse, feiþ, charyte, &amp; pes, wiþ þilke þat clepeþ þe name of oure Lord wiþ a clene herte.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.23" type="verse">And schonye þou questyones of foly &amp; þat beþ wiþ-outen techynge , knowynge þat þei bryngeþ forþ stryfynges.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.24" type="verse">And it byhoueþ Godes serfaunt to ben no stryfere, bote good &amp; softe to alle
<seg id="b.2TI.2.25" type="verse">men, habel to ben y-tauȝt, pacyent, &amp; wiþ softnesse amendynge
<seg id="b.2TI.2.26" type="verse">ȝefen hem myȝt for-to knowe þe trewþe, þat þei ascapen from þe defeles grunnes, of whom þei beþ y-holde prysoneres after his wylle.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.2" type="verse">is in Iesu Crist of þilke þinges þat þou hast y-herd of me by many wytnesses, &amp; þese þinges bytake þou to feiþful men, þat mowen also techen oþer men.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.3" type="verse">&amp; trauayle þou as a good knyȝt of Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.4" type="verse">þer ne is no man serfynge God þat implyeþ hym-selfe to wordlyche doynges, þat he plese hym to whom he haþ y-prefed hym-selfe.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.5" type="verse">For he þat fyȝteþ in batayle ne schal noȝt ben y-crowned, bote ȝif he fyȝte leffullyche.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.6" type="verse">&amp; it byhoueþ þat þe erþe-tylyer þat trauayleþ furst perceyfen of þe fruytes.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.7" type="verse">Vnderstonde what y seye to þe; for God wole ȝefe þe vndurstondynge in alle þinges.
<seg id="b.2TI.2.8" type="verse">&amp;
<seg id="b.2TI.2.9" type="verse">seed of Dauyd, aftur myn euangely: in whom y trauayle, for whom ich am y-bounde; bote Goddes word ne is noȝt y-bounde.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.10" type="verse">Bote þou hast folewed my techynge, myn ordeynynge, &amp; my purpos, feiþ, longanymyte (þat
<seg id="b.2TI.3.11" type="verse">is longabydynge) , lofe, pacyence, persecucyones, suffrynges, whyche habbeþ y-ben y-do to me at Anthyoche, at Yconye &amp; at Lystres; whuche persecucyones ich haue y-suffred: bote God haþ defended me of hem alle.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.12" type="verse">And alle þilke þat woleþ lyfen mukelyche in Crist schulleþ suffre persecucyoun.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.13" type="verse">Bote wykkede men &amp; gyloures schulleþ profyten into worse, errynge hem-selfen, &amp; bryngen oþer men in-to errour.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.14" type="verse">Bote dwelle þow stylle in þese þinges, þat þou hast y-lernyd &amp; þat beþ y-take to þe, knowynge of whom þou hast y-lernyd;
<seg id="b.2TI.3.15" type="verse">&amp; þat from þi ȝouþe þou hast y-knowe holy wrytynges þat mowen enforme þe in-to hele by þe feiþ þat is in Iesu Crist.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.16" type="verse">And eferich wrytynge þat is inspyred of God is profytabel to techen men, &amp; to vndernymen hem, &amp; to amenden hem,
<seg id="b.2TI.3.17" type="verse">&amp; to enformen hem in ryȝtfulnesse: so þat a Goddes man is parfyt &amp; enformed to eferich good werk.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.1" type="verse">And knowe þou þis, þat in þe laste dayes þer schuleþ ben perylous tymes.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.2" type="verse">For men schulleþ ben lofynge hemselfen, coueytous and proude, blasphemes, in-obedyent to
<seg id="b.2TI.3.3" type="verse">hure eldren, vnkynde, cursede, wiþ-outen lofe, wiþ-outen pes, blamynge oþer men, incontynent, noȝ muke, with-outen
<seg id="b.2TI.3.4" type="verse">benygnyte, traytoures, fro-ward, swellynge þoroȝ pruyde,
<seg id="b.2TI.3.5" type="verse">loferes of lustes more þan of God; hafynge þe lyknesse of pyte bote forsakynge his vertu: and þese schenye þou.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.6" type="verse">For of þese þer beþ þat perseþ mennes houses, &amp; ledeþ wiþ hem wrecchede wymmen þat beþ y-charged wiþ synnes
<seg id="b.2TI.3.7" type="verse">&amp; y-lad wiþ dyuerse desyres, &amp; efermore þei beþ lernynge, bote þei ne comeþ nefer to þe knowynge of trewþe.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.8" type="verse">And as Iannes &amp; Mambres aȝenstoden Moyses, so þese aȝeynstondeþ þe trewþe; men þat beþ corrupt in pouȝt, &amp; wykked a-boute þe feiþ.
<seg id="b.2TI.3.9" type="verse">Bote þei ne schuleþ noȝt profyten: for hure vnkunnyngenesse schal ben openlyche y-knowen to alle men, ryȝt as þe oþeres was.
<seg id="b.2TI.4.1" type="verse">And y wytnesse to-fore God, &amp; oure Lord Iesu Crist, þat schal deme boþe quyke men &amp; dede, &amp; by his comynge &amp; his
<seg id="b.2TI.4.2" type="verse">kyngdom; preche þou þe word, &amp; stonde bysylyche boþe in hese &amp; in anuy; &amp; vndernyme þou, &amp; byseche, &amp; blame þou in eferich pacyence &amp; in techynge.
<seg id="b.2TI.4.3" type="verse">For tyme schal come when men ne wolleþ noȝt susteyne good techynge &amp; hol; bote þei schuleþ gedere to-gyder maystres, ycchynge heres ,
<seg id="b.2TI.4.4" type="verse">&amp; þei schulleþ turnen awey hure herynge from trewþe, &amp; þei schuleþ turnen hem to tales.
<seg id="b.2TI.4.5" type="verse">Bote wake þou, &amp; trauayle þou in alle þinges, &amp; do þou þi werk of þe euangelye, &amp; fulfulle þi mynystrynge. &amp; be þou sober.
<seg id="b.3JO.1.10" type="verse">Þerfore, ȝef y come, y schal moue his werkes þat he doþ with wykked wordes, iangelynge in ȝow: &amp; as þese þinges suffyce not to hym, ne he resceyued breþeren, &amp; þei þat resceyueþ hem he forfendeþ, &amp; putteþ hem out of churche.
<seg id="b.3JO.1.11" type="verse">My dere broþer, ne be þou not folewere of yuel, but þat þat good is. Who-so doþ wel, he is of God: who-so doþ yuele, he seþ not God .
<seg id="b.3JO.1.12" type="verse">To Demetrio wytnesse is y-ȝolde of alle goode men, &amp; of trewþe: &amp; we bere wytnesse of hym; &amp; þou hast knowe þat oure wytnesse is trewe .
<seg id="b.3JO.1.13" type="verse">Many þinges y haue to wryte to þe,
<seg id="b.3JO.1.14" type="verse">bote with lettere y wolde not sende it; For y trowe hastly to se þe, &amp; mouþ to mouþ we schul speke. Pees be vn-to þe. Þi frendes grete þe wel, &amp; grete þou wel oure frendes by name. Here endeþ þe pystel of Ion. Here bygynneþ þe pystel of Iude.
<seg id="b.3JO.1.2" type="verse">Dere frend, of alle þinge y make my preyere in prosperyte þat þou entre &amp; wel-fare as þi soule welfareþ.
<seg id="b.3JO.1.3" type="verse">Gretly y am maked ful glad of breþeren þat comeþ &amp; bere wytnes of þi soþfastnesse, as þou in soþfastnesse gost.
<seg id="b.3JO.1.4" type="verse">More grace haue y noȝt of þise, þan þat y here þat my sones go in soþfastnesse of charyte.
<seg id="b.3JO.1.5" type="verse">My dere frend, feiþfully þou dost what-so þou dost in oure breþeren, (þat is, anentys oure
<seg id="b.3JO.1.6" type="verse">breþeren) &amp; þat in pylgrymes, þat bere wytnesse of þi charyte in þe syȝt of holy churche: þe whuche worþily þou ledest to God þoroȝ þi goode dede.
<seg id="b.3JO.1.7" type="verse">Soþly for his name þei ȝede forþ, takynge no þing of gentyles.
<seg id="b.3JO.1.8" type="verse">And þerfore suche we schulde vnderfonge, þat we beþ helperes to soþfastnesse .
<seg id="b.3JO.1.9" type="verse">Y had wryte peraunter to þe churche: bote he, Diotropes, þat loueþ to bere prelacye in hem, ne resceyued not ȝow.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.10" type="verse">Ande efter whanne hym hungred, he wolde 25go vnto þo mete25 ; þo whileste þei dighte his mete in spiritte he was rauysched;
<seg id="b.ACT.10.11" type="verse">ande he sawe heuen opunde, ande a vessel kome þerfro, as
<seg id="b.ACT.10.12" type="verse">heuen vnto erþe: in þo whiche wore alle foure-fotud bestes ande nedders of erþe ande fowles of heuen.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.13" type="verse">&amp; a voyce from heuen kome vnto hym, ande sayde , Rise, Peter, slee ande ete.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.14" type="verse">Ande Peter soþely saide, God forbede, Lorde; for neuer ȝitte I ete alle komune &amp; vnclene (as who sey , none suche bestes) .
<seg id="b.ACT.10.15" type="verse">Ande efte þo voyce saide vnto hym, Þat at God has made clene, calle þow hit not comune .
<seg id="b.ACT.10.16" type="verse">Ande þis was þries done, &amp; þo vessel taken agayne vppe into heuen.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.17" type="verse">Ande þo while Peter mused in hymseluen what þis vision schulde be, þe whiche vnto hym schewed, þo men komen þat wore sende from Cornelyo, ande spirde vnto Symondes
<seg id="b.ACT.10.18" type="verse">house, ande stoden at þo ȝate; ande called ynne ande asched if Symon, þat es called Peter, wore harbarowed atte þat place.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.19" type="verse">Soþely as Peter was þenkande vpon his visione, þo spirit saide vnto hym, Loo, three men sechen þe.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.1" type="verse">Ande þo whileste þer was a man in Cesarye þat hatte Cornelyus,
<seg id="b.ACT.10.20" type="verse">Rise vppe þerfore, ande go downe, ande wende forþe wiþ þem; &amp; be þow noghte aferde, for I þoo men sente .
<seg id="b.ACT.10.21" type="verse">Saynte Peter ȝode downe ande sayde vnto hem , Lo, I am he whom þat ȝhe seche: what es þo cause wharfore þat ȝhe hider come?
<seg id="b.ACT.10.22" type="verse">Þo whiche ansuered vnto hym, Cornelius centurio, a man þat es rightwise ande trewly dredes God ande has wytnes þeroffe alle þo folke of þo Iurye, an ansuere he hade of þo holy awngel forto sende efter þe ande brynge þe vnto his howse þi wordes forto here.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.23" type="verse">Ande Peter ledde hem inne, ande he þem þer harbarowede; ande vpon þo toþer daye roos ande ȝode forþe wiþ hem; ande summe of his breþer ȝode fro Ioppen wiþ hym.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.24" type="verse">&amp; soþely þo toþer daye þei enterde into Cesarye . Soþely Cornelyus gadured togider his knowne frendes ande hem þat nedfulle were vnto hym, ande abode Peter ande þoo þat wore wente hym.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.25" type="verse">Ande so whanne Peter was komen ande schulde enter into his howse,
<seg id="b.ACT.10.26" type="verse">Ande Peter lyfte hym vppe ande saide, Rise, for I am a man as þow erte.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.27" type="verse">Ande whanne to-gider þei haden spoken, Peter ȝode ynne wiþ hym, ande
<seg id="b.ACT.10.28" type="verse">fonde þer many þat wore komen togader: ande he sayde vnto hem, Ȝhe wote how þat hit es loþely þinge a Iewe forto haue comunynge togider or forto come vnto men of oþer nacyones . Bot God schewed vnto me þat I schulde
<seg id="b.ACT.10.29" type="verse">calle no man comune or vnclene: ande þerfore wiþouten dowte I am comen vnto ȝowe. Ande þerfore I asche ȝowe for what cause sende ȝe efter me forto kome vnto ȝowe.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.2" type="verse">centurio, a man þat was relygyowse ande dredande God wiþ alle hise howsemeyne , þat many almes vnto þo puple did; ande euer preyande God.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.30" type="verse">Ande þanne Cornelius saide, Fro foure dais siþen vnto þis houre I haue fastud ande preyed in my howse; ande þo nynte houre a man stode bifore me in a schynande white
<seg id="b.ACT.10.31" type="verse">cloþinge, ande saide, Cornely, þi preyer es harde, ande þine almes-dedus ben þoghte vpon þo sighte of Godde.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.32" type="verse">Sende þerfore vnto Ioppen efter Symonde, þat es callud Peter; he es harbarowed in Symonde howse, þo curyoure, bi þo see.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.33" type="verse">Ande þerfore als smertely I sente vnto þe; ande þow wele dideste þat þow come vnto vs. Now þerfore we alle ben here bifore þi sighte, forto here alle þinges þat ben comawnded of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.34" type="verse">Peter soþely opunde his mouþe ande saide, In soþefastenes I hafe fownde ande vndurstonden þat
<seg id="b.ACT.10.35" type="verse">God es noghte outetaker of parsons: bot in alle folke þat dredes hym ande dos rightwisenes, he acceptes ande receyues.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.36" type="verse">He sente his worde vnto þo childer of Israel, techande ande schewande pees þurghe Iesu Criste. He þis es Lorde soþely of alle.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.37" type="verse">Ȝhe knowe þat þo worde was made ande knowen bi alle þo Iurye, bigynnande fro Galilee, efter þo bapteme þat
<seg id="b.ACT.10.38" type="verse">saynte Iohn preched, Iesum fro Nazareth, how God ennoynted hym þurghe þo Holygoste ande vertewe: þo whiche passed by, wele doande, ande helande alle þat wore ouerlyne wiþ þo dewle.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.39" type="verse">For wiþ hym was God. Ande we ben wytnes of alle þinges þat he did in þo Iewrye ande Ierusalem; whom þei slowe, hongande hym vpon a tree.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.3" type="verse">He þis sawe in visione , as hit wore þo nynte houre of þo daye, þo awngel of God 12enterande in vnto hym12 , ande þus vnto hym he sayde, Cornely.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.40" type="verse">Hym God raysed vnto life þo þridde daye, ande made 3hym forto be sene (or gafe hym to be mayntende, þat es, opunly knowen þat he es
<seg id="b.ACT.10.41" type="verse">risen agayne3 ), noghte vnto alle folke, bot to wytnesses þat wore bifore ordeynd of God, vnto vs þat eten ande dranke wiþ hym efter þat he was risen fro deþe.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.42" type="verse">Ande he bade vs preche vnto þo puple, ande bere wytnes: for he hit es þat of God es iustise of qwikke ande of deade.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.43" type="verse">Vnto hym alle prophetes wytnesses beren ; bi þo name of hym alle men þat trowne in hym forto take forgifnes of alle þer synnes.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.44" type="verse">Þo whileste Peter spake þise wordes, þo Holygoste fel vpon alle þat harde þo wordes.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.45" type="verse">Ande wore awondurd þurghe þo circumsicyon þo trewe folke þat komen wiþ Peter, for in nacyons þo grace was ȝotted oute of þo Holygoste (þat es, for þat oþer nacyons hade þo grace of þo Holygoste).
<seg id="b.ACT.10.46" type="verse">Þei harden hem forsoþe spekande langages ande preysande God.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.47" type="verse">Thanne ansuered Peter, None may werne ne defende water, þat þise ben noghte baptised, þat han receyued þo Holygoste as we
<seg id="b.ACT.10.48" type="verse">haue; ande comawnded hem forto be baptized in þo name of Iesu Criste. Thanne þei preyed hym forto dwelle þere summe days wiþ hem .
<seg id="b.ACT.10.4" type="verse">Ande loked vpon hym, ande wondurfully was aferde, ande saide, Lorde, who erte þowe? Ande þo awngel saide vnto hym, Þi preyers ande þine almes-dedes ben steghne vppe ande ben hade in mynde in þo sighte of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.5" type="verse">Ande sende now men vnto Ioppen, ande make þe
<seg id="b.ACT.10.6" type="verse">knowne wiþ Symonde, þat es called Peter, þat es harbarowed atte Symons howse, þo curyoure , whos howse stondes biside þo see; ande he schal teche þe what þe bihoues to do.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.7" type="verse">Ande whanne þo awngel was departud fro hym þat so vnto hym spake, he called tweyne of his owne howse þat wore homely wiþ hym, ande alsso a knyghte þat mykel dredde God, to be one of hem forto wende þat waye.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.8" type="verse">Whanne he hade tolde hem how hit was, he sende hem vnto Ioppen.
<seg id="b.ACT.10.9" type="verse">Þo toþer day þei ȝode þer waye ande kome nere vnto þe cyte. Saynte Peter wente vppe abouen into þo howse forto saye hise preyers, aboute þo houre of myddaye.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.10" type="verse">Ande whanne þei loked vppe into heuen efter hm wendande, lo, twoo men stoden biside hem in white
<seg id="b.ACT.11.10" type="verse">8Ande þat was thryes done8 , ande alle were taken vppe into heuen.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.11" type="verse">Ande als smertely three men stoden in þo howse þat I was inne, sende fro Cesarye vnto me.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.12" type="verse">Ande þo Spiritte saide vnto me þat I schulde go wiþ hem, no þinge dowtande. Soþely þer come wiþ me þise sexe breþer; ande we ȝode into
<seg id="b.ACT.11.13" type="verse">þo mannes howse: ande he tolde vnto vs how he hade sene þo awngel of God stondynge in his howse, ande sayande vnto hym, Sende into Ioppen to Symon, þat es called Peter, forto
<seg id="b.ACT.11.14" type="verse">come vnto þe; þo whiche schal speke wordes to þe, in þo whiche þow schalte be saued, þow ande alle þi meyne.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.15" type="verse">Soþely whanne I biganne to speke, þo Holygoste come downe vpon hem, as he did vponne vs in þo bigynnynge.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.16" type="verse">Forsoþe I vmþoghte me of þo wordes of oure Lorde, as he saide, Iohn forsoþe baptised wiþ water; ȝhe soþely schul be baptised wiþ þo Holygoste.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.17" type="verse">Þerfore if God haue gifen vnto hym þo same grace þat he haues vnto vs, þat trowed in Iesu Criste, whatte was I to werne oure Lorde forto gife hem þo Holygoste? (19As who say, how myghte I or schulde I warne God to gife vnto hem þo Holygoste19 ), þat trowed in þo name of Iesu Criste.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.18" type="verse">Whanne þei hade harde þis, þei helde hem stille, ande þanked God, ande saide, Þerfore God
<seg id="b.ACT.11.19" type="verse">Ande þei for certayne þat wore spredde obrode fro þo tribulacyone þat vndur Steuen was done, ȝeden aboute to þei kome vnto Fenys, ande to Ciprum, ande Antioche, to no man spekande worde bot onely vnto þo Iewes.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.11" type="verse">cloþinges, þo whiche saide vnto hem, Men of Galilee, wherto stonde ȝhe biholdande into heuen? , righte as ȝhe sawe hym ascende vnto heuen , right so schal he kome as ȝhe sawe hym wende.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.1" type="verse">Þo apostuls harden ande conceyueden, &amp; alsso þo breþer, þat þo gentiles hade receyued Goddes worde, ande worschipped God þeroffe.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.20" type="verse">Soþely summe of hem wore men of Cipri ande of Cireny, þo whiche, whanne þei comen vnto Antioche , þei speken vnto þo gentiles, tellande ande schewande Ihesu Criste.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.21" type="verse">Ande Goddes myghte was wiþ hem, ande myche noumbur of trowande was conuerted vnto God.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.22" type="verse">Soþely þo worde þeroffe come vnto þo heryng of þo chirche, þat was in Ierusalem, of þise þinges: ande þei sende Barnabas vnto Antioche.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.23" type="verse">Whanne þat he come þider, ande sawe þo grace of God, he was ioyful; ande he excited hem alle to holde þer hertes stabul in þer purpos to God.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.24" type="verse">For he was a gode man, ande fulle of þo Holygoste ande of faiþe: ande myche puple put hem vnto God.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.25" type="verse">After he ȝode to Tharsum forto seche Sawle; þo whiche, whanne þei haden hym fownden, he ledde hym vnto Antioche.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.26" type="verse">Ande alle a hole ȝhere þei dwelled þore togider in chirche, ande tawghten myche puple; so þat þei wore knowne in alle Antioche for Cristes discipuls.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.27" type="verse">Ande soþely in þise days þat þei þer wore, þer come prophetes fro Ierusalem vnto Antioche.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.28" type="verse">Ande one of hem, whos name was Agabus, ros vppe, ande prophecyed or bitokende þurghe spiritte a grete hunger þat was forto come þurgh-oute alle þo worlde; þo whiche was done in þo tyme of Claudii.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.29" type="verse">Þo disciples, icheone forsoþe after þat þei haden, purposed to sende vnto þer breþer, þat hit myghte serue hem þat wore dwellande atte Iude vnto þer sustynaunce.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.2" type="verse">Whanne Peter was wente vppe agayne vnto Ierusalem, þei þat wore circumsiced striuen wiþ
<seg id="b.ACT.1.12" type="verse">Þan turned þei agayne vnto Ierusalem fro þe mownte of Olyuete, þat es biside Ierusalem.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.30" type="verse">Ande so þei diden, sendande hit vnto þo eldeste by Barnabas ande Saule .
<seg id="b.ACT.1.13" type="verse">Ande whanne þei hade enturde into þer cynacle (a howse þat þei dwelled inne), þei ȝode vppe where Peter dwelled, ande Iohn, ande Iames, ande Andrewe, ande Philippe, &amp; Thomas, ande Bartholomew , ande Mathewe ande Iacob Alphei, ande Symon Zelotes &amp; Iudas Iacobi.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.3" type="verse">hym, ande saiden, Why ȝodeste þow vnto men þat hade þer circumsicynge (15þat es, whi ȝodeste þow wiþ hem þat haden þer prepucy15 ande wore noghte circumsiced )? ande þow
<seg id="b.ACT.1.14" type="verse">Alle þise were lastande in preyer togader wiþ wymmen, ande Mary Jesu moder, ande hire breþer.
