<seg id="b.ACT.11.5" type="verse">hem bi ordur, ande saide, I was in þo cyte of Ioppen preyande: ande I sawe, as I was rauisched in spiryt, a visione, a vessel comande downe, as hit hade ben a grete schete laten downe bi þo foure korners fro heuen, ande kome vnto me.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.15" type="verse">In þo dais Peter ros uppe inmyddes þo breþer, ande saide—þo company of men þat was þer togider was
<seg id="b.ACT.11.6" type="verse">Ande as I bihelde þer-inne, I sawe foure-fotud bestes of erthe &amp; crepande wormes ande fowles of heuen.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.16" type="verse">nerehande a hundreþe ande twenty —Ȝhe men ande my breþer, þo writte þat þo Holigoste has bifore saide, hit bihoues to be fulfilled of Iudas by Dauid mowþe, þo whiche was
<seg id="b.ACT.11.7" type="verse">Ande soþely I harde a voyce sayande to me, Rise, Peter, slee ande ete.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.17" type="verse">ledar of hem þat toke Iesu; þo whiche was noumburde in vs (þat es , was of oure company), ande he es lotted in þo lote of þis priuete.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.18" type="verse">Ande he þis forsoþe fledde away, ande helde þo felde of þo hire of wikkednes (þat es, þat was boghte wiþ þo money þat Criste was solde fore), ande honged hymseluen, ande braste ymiddes , ande alle hise guttes &amp; entrailes wore ȝette oute.
<seg id="b.ACT.11.8" type="verse">Ande I saide agayne, Nay, Lorde, for alle vnclene þinge enturde noghte into my mowþe. Ande soþely þo voyce
<seg id="b.ACT.1.19" type="verse">Ande hit es knowne þinge vnto alle þat dwellen in Ierusalem, so as þat felde was called on þer langage Acheldemac, þat es, Þo felde of blode .
<seg id="b.ACT.11.9" type="verse">ansuered þo secunde tyme, ande saide, Þat at God haues clensed, say þow noghte hit es vnclene.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.1" type="verse">apostuls, ande sais vpon þis wise, Forsoþe, þou Theophul, þe firste sermone I made of alle þat Iesus bigan to do ande
<seg id="b.ACT.1.20" type="verse">Soþely hit es writen in þo boke of Psalmes, His dwellynge be deserte, ande be þer none to dwelle þerinne: ande, An oþer hafe hise bischopriche.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.10" type="verse">Þei passed soþely þo firste ande þo secunde warde, ande komen vnto þo iren ȝhate þo whiche ledes vnto þo cyte, þat onone was opunde to hem: ande þei ȝode oute ande wente forþe into a way; ande þo awngel departed fro hym.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.11" type="verse">Ande Peter turned hym vnto hymseluen, ande saide, Nowe wote I wele, þat God haues sende his awngel vnto me, ande delyuered me oute of þo power of Herowde, &amp; fro alle þo abidynge of þo puple of þe Iewrye.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.12" type="verse">Ande he bihelde ande come vnto Maryes howse, þat was Ioones modure, þo whiche was knowen name Marcus, where þat many wore gadured togider, ande were preyande.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.13" type="verse">Ande soþely whan he knokked at þo dore of þo ȝhate, þer come forþe a wenche þat hatte Rode, to loke who was þere.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.14" type="verse">Ande whanne sche harde þo voyce of Peter, for ioy sche ranne , lefte þo ȝhate sparde , ande tolde hem þat Peter stondes bifore þe ȝate.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.15" type="verse">Ande þei saide vnto hire, Þow maddes . Sche saide, Soþely hit es so.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.16" type="verse">Ande soþely þei saide, Hit es an awngel. Peter soþely stode stille atte þo ȝhate ande knokked. Whanne þei hade þo ȝhate opunde, þei sawe hym ande wore awondured.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.17" type="verse">Ande he bekkende vnto hem wiþ hise honde þat þei schulde holde þem stille. He tolde how þat God hade ledde hym oute of prisone, ande saide, Sendes worde herof vnto Iames, ande to oure breþer. Ande he ȝede forþe, ande wente into an-oþer place.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.18" type="verse">Whanne þat þo day come, þer was not made a lytel turbulynge amonge þo knyghtes þat hym kepped, what was bifallen of Peter.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.19" type="verse">Soþely whanne Herowde asched efter hym, ande wolde haue ledde hym vnto þo puple, ande fonde hym noghte, he 8made to asche8 of þo kepars, ande brynge hem vnto hym. Ande Peter ȝode fro Iu into Cesarye, ande þer he dwelled.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.21" type="verse">Ande þerfore it bihoues of þise men þat ben
<seg id="b.ACT.12.1" type="verse">Þo same tyme sente Herowde þo kenge powere, summe of holy chirche to tourmente.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.20" type="verse">(!) þat was þe kenges higheste chaumbirleyn, þei asked pees of hym, for þat he schulde goo into þere kengdomes. ]
<seg id="b.ACT.12.21" type="verse">Afterworde, vpon a day þat was ordeynde, Herowde cladde hym in kenges cloþinge, ande sette hym vpon a sege, ande cownseyld wiþ þo folke of Tiris ande Sidone.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.22" type="verse">Ande þo folke cried, Wiþ goddes voyce ande noghte with mannes.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.23" type="verse">Ande alsso smertely an awngel of God smote hym, for he gafe noghte worschip nor honoure vnto God, ande was wastud with wormes ande dyed.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.24" type="verse">Soþely þanne þo worde of God wexe and was made myche .
<seg id="b.ACT.12.25" type="verse">Wanne Barnabas ande Saule haden don þer office atte Ierusalem, þei turne þem agayne, ande toke wiþ hem
<seg id="b.ACT.1.22" type="verse">Iesu Criste kome ande ȝode amonge vs, bigynnande fro þo bapteme of Iohn, vnto þo day þat he was vp-taken fro vs, of þis forto be a witnes wiþ us of his uprisinge.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.2" type="verse">Soþely he slowe Iames, Jones broþer, wiþ a swerde.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.23" type="verse">Ande þei sette tweyne, Ioseph þat was called Barsabas, ande his kouþe name es Rightwise, ande Mathewe.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.3" type="verse">He sawe þat he myghte plese to þo Iewes.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.24" type="verse">Ande preyande þei saide, Þow Lorde, þat knewe þo hertes of alle, schewe vs
<seg id="b.ACT.12.4" type="verse">He sette forto take Peter , ande whanne þat he hade hym taken, he sende hym into prisone, ande bitawghte hym to foure knyghtes forto kepe; for hit was lenten tyme, ande efter Paske wolde he lede hym forþe vnto þo puple.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.5" type="verse">Ande Peter soþely was holden in prisone: soþely preyer was made for hym vnto God wiþouten cessynge of holy chirche.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.25" type="verse">whom þow haueste chosen of þise twoo , to take þe place of þis priuete ande of þis seruice, &amp; þo apostulhed of whiche Iudas es depriued, þat he may dwelle in hise stede.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.26" type="verse">Ande þei gafe hem lottes, ande þo lotte felle vpon Mathewe, ande he was anoumburde wiþ þo eleuen apostuls.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.6" type="verse">Forsoþe whanne þat Herowde schulde haue ledde hym forþe , in þat nyghte bifore was Peter slepande bitwene twoo knyghtes, bownde wiþ twoo chenyes; ande kepars bifore þo ȝhates kepped þo prisone.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.7" type="verse">Ande lo, þer stode by hym an awngel , ande lyghteful schyned in þo stede þer he was: he smote Peter vpon þo side, ande stired hym &amp; sayde, Rise vppe smertely. Ande þo chenyes felle of hise hende .
<seg id="b.ACT.12.8" type="verse">Ande soþely þo awngel saide vnto hym, Girde þe, ande do vpon þi schone ande þine hoses. Ande so he did. &amp; he sayde vnto hym, Keste þi cloþes aboute þe, ande folow me.
<seg id="b.ACT.12.9" type="verse">Ande he ȝode oute, ande he folowed, ande wiste noghte þat hit was soþe þat þat was now done bi þo awngel: for he wende þat he hade ben in a visione.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.2" type="verse">teche, vnto þat daye þat daye þat he ascended vppe (or was taken uppe), comawndeande vnto þo apostuls þurghe þo Holigoste
<seg id="b.ACT.13.10" type="verse">ande bihelde hym, &amp; saide, A, þow þat erte ful of alle gile, ande fulle of fallace, ande sone of þo fende, &amp; enmye of alle rightwisenes, þow styntes noghte to vndo þo righte ways of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.11" type="verse">&amp; lo, þo honde of God es vpon þe, ande þow schalte be blynde, ande þow schalte noghte see þo sonne vnto certayne tyme. Ande onone dymnes ande derkenes felle vpon hym; ande he wente aboute sekande if any wolde
<seg id="b.ACT.13.12" type="verse">Thanne þo proconsul, whanne he sawe þis, he trowed in God, ande meruayled on þo doctrine of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.13" type="verse">Ande whanne Poule ande þoo þat wore wiþ schipped fro Papho, þei come vnto Pergen of Pamphilye: ande Iohn departed fro hem ande turned agayne vnto Ierusalem.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.14" type="verse">Ande þei passande þurghe Pargen come vnto Antioche of ; ande in þo daye of sabbate þei enterd into þo synagoge ande sete þerinne.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.15" type="verse">Ande efter þo lessone of þo lawe ande of þo prophetes, of þo synagoge sende vnto hem, sayande, Ȝhe men, dere breþer, if þer be any worde of exhortacyon vnto þo puple, says hit.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.16" type="verse">Ande Poule risande ande wiþ his honde biddande silence he saide vnto hem, Men of Israel, ande ȝhe þat dreden God, heres þise wordes.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.17" type="verse">Þo God of þo folke of Israel chesed oure faders, ande he highed hise folke þe whileste þei were comelynges ande dwellynge in þo lande of Egipte, ande in stalworþe arme ande highe myghte he ledde hem oute of þo lande of Egipte.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.18" type="verse">Ande by þo tyme of fourty ȝeres
<seg id="b.ACT.13.19" type="verse">he suffured þer maners in þo deserte; ande destroyed seuen nacyons in þo lande of Chanaan, ande by lotte he dalte vnto
<seg id="b.ACT.13.1" type="verse">þer wore at Antioche in þo chirche prophetes ande doctoures, amonge þo whiche wore Barnabas ande Symeon, þat was called Blakke, ande Lucy of Cyrene , ande Manaen þat was þo plawfere of Herowde þo Tetrarke , ande Saulus.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.20" type="verse">hem þer londe, as after foure hundreþe ande fifty ȝere. Ande after þis he gafe hem domes-men to rewle hem vnto þo tyme of Samuel þo prophete.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.21" type="verse">Ande fro þo tyme of Samuel þei asched a kenge to be þer gouernoure: ande God gafe hem a kenge, Saul þo sone of Cys, of þo tribe of Beniamyn, fourty ȝhere.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.22" type="verse">Ande after hym þis Saule, God gafe vnto hem Dauid þo kenge, vnto whom he beres wytnes, ande says , I haue fownden Dauid, þo sone of Iesse, a man efter my hertte þo whiche schal do alle my willes.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.23" type="verse">Of þo sede of hym þis Dauid God sende, as he biheghte, a sauyoure vnto Israel, Ihesu.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.24" type="verse">Ande Iohn preched bifore þo face of his comynge þo baptyme of penawnce vnto alle þo
<seg id="b.ACT.13.25" type="verse">Ande whanne Iohn hade fulfilled his course, he saide vnto po folke of Israel, I am noghte he whom ȝhe supposed þat I was. Bot loo, he comes efter me, of whom I am noghte worþi to lowse þo chausers of hise fete.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.26" type="verse">Ande vnto ȝowe, dere breþer ande childer of þo kynne of Abraham, ande to þoo þat in ȝowe drede God es sende þo worde of þis hele .
<seg id="b.ACT.13.27" type="verse">Bot þoo þat dwelled in Ierusalem, ande þo princes of þat cyte, þat knewe noghte þis Iesu, ande þo voyce ande þo spekynge of þo prophetes, þo whiche ben redde iche sabbate, þei fulfilled, demande hym.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.28" type="verse">Ande no cause of deþe þei fonde in hym, ande ȝitte þei asched of Pilate forto slee hym.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.29" type="verse">Ande whanne þei hade ended alle þinges þat wore writen of hym, þei toke hym downe of þo tree, ande layde hym in a graue.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.2" type="verse">Ande whanne þei mynisterde vnto Godde ande fastud, þo Holygoste saide vnto hem, Twynnes to me Barnaban ande Saulum vnto þo warke þat I haue taken þem to.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.30" type="verse">Ande God raysed hym fro deþe vpon þo thridde daye, ande he was sene bi many
<seg id="b.ACT.13.31" type="verse">dayes of hem þat komen wiþ hym fro Galilee vnto Ierusalem, þat ȝitte vnto þis day ben hise wytnes to þo puple.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.32" type="verse">Ande we schewe vnto ȝowe þo biheste þat God highte vnto oure
<seg id="b.ACT.13.33" type="verse">fadirs: þat God haues fulfilled hit in oure childer, raysande Iesu fro þo deþe; as hit es writen in þo secunde psalme, My sone þow erte, þis day I haue goten þe .
<seg id="b.ACT.13.34" type="verse">Ande for þat he so raysed hym from þe deþe, þat he schulde no more see corupcyone, þus he saide, I schal gife vnto ȝowe þo holy trewe þinges of Dauid.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.35" type="verse">Ande þerfore he says in an-oþer place, I schal noghte gife þine halowe forto see corrupcyone.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.36" type="verse">Bot Dauid in his generacyone, whanne he hade mynysterde vnto þo wille of God, he slepped (or, dyed), ande was layde vnto hise faders, ande he sawe corrupcyone.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.37" type="verse">Bot he þat God raysed fro þo deþe sawe no corrupcyone.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.38" type="verse">Ande þerfore ȝhe men, dere breþer, be hit knowne vnto ȝowe þat bi hym es schewed to ȝowe of alle remyssion of ȝoure synnes,
<seg id="b.ACT.13.39" type="verse">,
<seg id="b.ACT.13.3" type="verse">Þan þo apostules fastud ande preyed ande layde onne hem þer hondes ande lete hem go.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.40" type="verse">Bot in hym whoso trowes, he es iustified. Bes ware þerfore, þat hit kome noghte vnto ȝowe, þat es writen
<seg id="b.ACT.13.41" type="verse">in þo prophetes: Ses, ȝhe despisars, ande ȝhe meruayle, ande ȝhe ben loste; for a warke I wirche in ȝowre days, þo warke þat ȝhe schal noghte trowe, if any telle hit vnto ȝowe.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.42" type="verse">Ande whanne þei wente oute of þo synagoge, þo puple preyed hem þat þei schulde speke þise wordes in þo nexte sabbate filowande.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.43" type="verse">Ande whanne þei hade lefte þo synagoge, many Iewes ande comelynges folowed Poule ande Barnaban; ande þei amonestud þem forto dwelle in þo grace offe God.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.44" type="verse">Ande in þo nexte sabbate folowande alle þo cyte almoste come forto here Goddes worde.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.45" type="verse">Ande þo Iewes see grete multitude of folke come forto here Poule, ande þei wore fulle of enuye ande agaynsaide þo wordus of Poule, blasphemande.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.46" type="verse">Thanne saiden Poule ande Barnabas traistely vnto þe Iewes, To ȝowe firste hit bihoued to speke Goddes worde. Bot for ȝhe refuse hit, ande deme ȝoureseluen vnworþi to aylastande life, loo, we turnen vs vnto nacyons ande leue ȝowe.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.47" type="verse">For so oure Lorde bade vs, I haue sette þe, he saide, in lyghte of nacyones, þat þow be my hele vnto þo ende of þo erþe.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.48" type="verse">Ande þe nacyons whanne þei harde þis worde, 11þei wore ioyfulle, ande þei glorified þo worde11 of God: ande als many as wore ordeynde to aye-lastande life troweden.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.49" type="verse">Ande þo worde of God was sparpulde þurghe alle þo contree.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.4" type="verse">&amp; Barnas ande Sawle , þat wore sende of þo Holigoste, ȝode vnto Selewce, ande fro þeþen þei schipped vnto Cyper.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.50" type="verse">Ande þo Iewes stirde relygiowse wymmen ande honeste, ande þo firste of þo cyte, &amp; þei stirde a persecucyone to Poule ande Barnaban, ande keste hem oute of þer contrees .
<seg id="b.ACT.13.51" type="verse">Ande Poule ande Barnaban keste þo powder of þer fete agaynes hem, ande kome vnto Yconye.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.52" type="verse">Ande þo discipules wore fulfilled wiþ ioye &amp; wiþ þo Holygoste.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.5" type="verse">Ande whanne þei wore komen to Salamyne, þei preched Goddes worde in þo synagoges of þo Iewes, ande þei haden wiþ hem John in mynisterynge of Goddes worde.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.6" type="verse">Ande whanne þei hade ouergone alle þat ile vnto Paphum, þei fonde a man þat was a wycche, a false prophete ande a Iewe, ande hise name was
<seg id="b.ACT.13.7" type="verse">Baryehu; þat was wiþ þo proconsul Sergyo Paulo, þo whiche was a ware man ande wise . (A proconsul es he þat ledes a towne, or guuernes bi cownseyl.) He þis proconsul called Barnaban ande Poule vnto hym, for he desired to here þo worde of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.8" type="verse">Ande he Elymas þo wiche wiþstode hem, for þus was hise name expowned or called , Elymas. Ande he þis wyche was abowte in alle þat he kouþe to turne þo proconsul fro þo faiþe.
<seg id="b.ACT.13.9" type="verse">Ande Poule was fulfilled wiþ þo Holygoste,
<seg id="b.ACT.1.3" type="verse">þo whiche he chees: ande vnto þo whiche he schewed hymseluen lifande efter hise passion in many argumentes, bi fourty days apperande vnto hem, ande spekande of þo
<seg id="b.ACT.14.10" type="verse">Ande whanne þo companyes seghe þis þat Poule did, þo men of Lycaonye lyfte vppe þer voyce &amp; saide, Goddes ben comen vnto vs in lyknes of men.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.11" type="verse">Ande þei called Barnaban Iouem ande Poule Mercurye, for he was ledar ande spekar of þo worde.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.12" type="verse">Ande þo preste of Iouys, þo whiche was bifore þo 17cytee, broghte bulles ande corownes bifore þo17 ȝhates, ande wiþ þo puple he wolde haue done sacrifice vnto Poule ande Barnabas.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.13" type="verse">Ande whanne þo apostuls harden þis, þei schere þer cloþes ande stirtte forþe amonge þo multitude, criande ande sayande, A, men, wherto done ȝhe þus?
<seg id="b.ACT.14.14" type="verse">We ben bot dedly men lyke to ȝowe, schewande ande prechande vnto ȝowe forto turne ȝowe fro þise vayne þinges vnto þo lifande God, þat made heuen ande erthe, þo see ande alle þat ben in
<seg id="b.ACT.14.15" type="verse">hem: þo whiche God in generacyones bifore lete gentiles to enter hise ways.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.16" type="verse">Ande noghte wiþouten testymonye lefte he hymseluen, wele doande, ande gifande raynes from heuen ande fruteful tymes, &amp; fillande ȝoure hertes wiþ mete ande gladnes.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.17" type="verse">Ande ȝitte whanne þei saide þise, vneþes myghte þei stille þo companyse þat ne þei wolde sacrifice vnto hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.18" type="verse">Bot summe Iewes comen in þo mene tyme from Antyoche ande Yconye, ande made ille suggestion to þo puple of Poule, ande þei stoned hym, ande drowe hym wiþouten þo cyte, supposande þat he was dede.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.19" type="verse">Ande whanne þo discipuls comen abowte hym, he roos vppe ande entered into þo cyte: ande in þo daye after he wente wiþ Barnabas into Derben.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.1" type="verse">Ande hit bifelle in Iconye, þat grete multitude of Iewes ande of Grekes enturde togadire vnto þo synagoge.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.20" type="verse">Ande whanne þei hade preched vnto þat cyte, ande haden tawghte many, þei wente agayne vnto Lyster ande Yconye
<seg id="b.ACT.14.21" type="verse">ande vnto Antyoche, ande confermed þo sowles of þo discipuls, ande made exhortacyone to hem þat þei schulde dwelle in þo faiþe, ande tolde vnto hem þat hit bihoues by many tribulacyones to enter into þo kengedam of God .
<seg id="b.ACT.14.22" type="verse">Ande whanne þo apostuls haden ordeynde vnto hem by syngulere chirches prestes, ande whanne þei hade preyed ande fasted, þei comended hem vnto God in whom þei trowed.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.23" type="verse">Ande þo apostuls passande þurghe Psidie , þei come into Pamphilye.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.24" type="verse">Ande þei speke Goddes worde in
<seg id="b.ACT.14.25" type="verse">Pergen, ande fro þeþen þei wente vnto Atthlaye; ande fro þeþen þei schipped into Antioche, where þei wore bitaken to þo grace of God into þo warke þat þei hade fulfilled.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.26" type="verse">Ande whanne þei wore comen þider ande hade gaderd togider þo disciples of holy chirche , þei tolde how myche God hade done wiþ hem, ande how þat God hade opunde vnto þo nacyons þo ȝate of þo faiþe.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.27" type="verse">Ande þei dwelled a longe tyme wiþ þo disciples.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.2" type="verse">Ande þo Iewes þat wore vntrowþeful stired persecucyone, ande excited þo hertes of nacyons agaynes þo breþer.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.3" type="verse">Bot God grawnted sone pees, ande longe tyme þei dwelled þer, doande trestly &amp; stedfastely in God, þat bere wytnes vnto þe worde of hise grace, ande grawnted wondures ande tokens to be done by þo hende of hise seruantes.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.4" type="verse">Bot þo multitude of þat cytee was deuydid; for summe helde wiþ þo Iewes, summe wiþ þo apostuls.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.5" type="verse">Ande whanne þo hastynes of þo Iewes ande þe gentyles assentud togider wiþ þer princes, forto punysche þo apostuls wiþ iniuryos wordes, ande forto stone
<seg id="b.ACT.14.6" type="verse">hem, whanne þei knewe þis, þei fledde into þo cytes of Lycaonye, Lystram ande Derben ande alle þo contre aboute: ande þere þei wore prechande. Ande alle þo multitude was stired in þer doctrine; ande Poule ande Barnabas dwelled in Lystris.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.7" type="verse">Ande þer was a man in Lystris þat was 9seke in his fete, ande was9 halte ande lame fro his moder wombe, ande neuer wente vpon hise fete.
<seg id="b.ACT.14.8" type="verse">He þis harde Poule spekande: ande Poule bihelde hym &amp; sawe þat he hade
<seg id="b.ACT.14.9" type="verse">faiþe to be sawfe, ande cryed wiþ a grete voyce ande saide, To þe I saye in þe name of oure Lorde Iesu Criste, rise vpon þi fete righte. Ande he stirte vppe ande ȝode.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.4" type="verse">kengdome of God: ande etande he comanded hem þat þei schulde noghte departe nor go away fro Jerusalem, bot þat þei schulde abide þo sonde ande þo bihetynge of þo fader,
<seg id="b.ACT.15.10" type="verse">Bot nowe þanne wharto tempte ȝhe to laye þo ȝoke ande charge vpon þo heued of þo disciples, þat noþer oure faders nor we myghte bere?
<seg id="b.ACT.15.11" type="verse">Bot we hopen forto be saued by þo grace of oure Lorde Iesu Criste, as þei ben.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.12" type="verse">Ande alle þo multitude was stille; ande þei harden Barnaban ande Poule tellande how myche God hade done merueyles ande tokens in nacyons by hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.13" type="verse">Ande after þat þei wore stille, Iames ansuered ande saide, Ȝhe men , dere breþer, heres me.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.14" type="verse">Symon has tolde vnto ȝowe onne what maner firste God visit , to take þo puple of nacyones vnto his name.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.15" type="verse">Ande to hym
<seg id="b.ACT.15.16" type="verse">accorden þo wordes of þo prophetes: as hit es wryten, Efter þise I schal go agayn, ande I schal edifye agayne þo tabernacle of Dauid, þo whiche es fallen ; ande I schal bigge
<seg id="b.ACT.15.17" type="verse">agayn þo broken of it, ande I schal vpraise hit: þat þo remnaunte of men seche þer Lorde, ande alle nacyons vpon whom es incalled my name, sais þe Lorde doande þis.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.18" type="verse">For fro þo worlde es knowne vnto God his warke.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.19" type="verse">Wharfore I iuge hem þat ben turned vnto God offe nacyons noghte
<seg id="b.ACT.15.1" type="verse">Ande summe þat comen from þo Iewrye tawghte ande preched vnto þe breþer ande saide, Bot if ȝhe be circumcydid efter þo custome of Moysi, ȝhe maye noghte be saue.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.20" type="verse">forto be vneside: bot forto write vnto hem þat þei abstene hem fro contamynacyone of mawmetes, ande fro fornycacione, ande fro þo suffocate, ande blode.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.21" type="verse">For Moyses fro olde tymes has in syngulere cytes þat prechen hym in synagoges, where he es redde bi iche sabbate.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.22" type="verse">Thanne hit liked vnto þo apostuls ande to þo elders, wiþ alle þo chirche (or, congregacyone), forto chese summe of hem, ande to sende vnto Antioche wiþ Poule ande Barnabas; ande þei chesed Iudas þat was surnamed Barsabas, ande Sylam, þo whiche wore þo
<seg id="b.ACT.15.23" type="verse">firste amonge þo breþer: writande bi þo hende of hem, Þo apostuls ande þo elder breþer to hem þat ben at Antyoche ande Sirie ande Cilyce breþer of nacyones, gretes wele (or,
<seg id="b.ACT.15.24" type="verse">ȝernes hele): For þat we haue harde þat summe of oures goande fro vs haues droued ȝow wiþ wordes, turnande ȝoure
<seg id="b.ACT.15.25" type="verse">hertes ; to whom we bade noghte; ande þerfore hit plesed to vs to gader vs in one ande forto chese men ande sende
<seg id="b.ACT.15.26" type="verse">vnto ȝowe wiþ oure dere breþer Poule &amp; Barnaban, þo whiche ben men þat han sette þer lyfes for þo name of oure Lorde Iesu Criste.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.27" type="verse">Ande þerfore we sentte vnto ȝowe Iudas ande Silam, þo whiche alsso schal telle þo same vnto
<seg id="b.ACT.15.28" type="verse">ȝowe, þat hit es sene to þo Holygoste no more charge forto lay vpon ȝowe þanne þise þat ben nedfulle;
<seg id="b.ACT.15.29" type="verse">þat ȝhe abstene ȝowe fro þinges þat ben offerde vnto mawmetes, ande fro sacrifice of ydolatrye, ande fro blode þat es suffocate, ande fro fornycacyone; ande þat ȝhe wille noghte were done vnto ȝowe, dos hit noghte vnto an-oþer; ande if ȝhe kepe ȝowe fro þise, ȝhe schal wele do. Fares wele.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.2" type="verse">Ande a grete sedicyon was made vnto Poule ande Barnabas agaynes hem; ande Poule saide vnto hem þat þei schulde abide in þo same trowþe þat þei wore inne. Ande Poule &amp; Barnabas ande summe of oþer disciples ordeynde þat þei schulde goo vnto þo apostuls ande þo prestes þat wore in Ierusalem to wyte of þis question .
<seg id="b.ACT.15.30" type="verse">Ande Poule, Barnabas, Iudas ande Sylas wente fro þo apostuls, ande kome vnto Antioche; ande whanne þei haden gaderd þo multitude of þo disciples, þei toke hem þo
<seg id="b.ACT.15.31" type="verse">epistel; þo whiche whanne þei haden redde, þei ioyed in a grete ioye for þo comforþe þat þei hade.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.32" type="verse">Ande Iudas ande Sylas, for þat þei wore prophetes ande prechors, wiþ myche spekynge þei comforþed þo breþer ande confermed hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.34" type="verse">Ande hit bisemed vnto Syle to dwelle þore, ande only Iudas wente agayne into Ierusalem.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.35" type="verse">Ande Poule ande Barnabas dwelled atte Antioche, techande ande prechande, wiþ oþer discipuls of Criste, Goddes worde.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.36" type="verse">Ande efter summe days Powle saide vnto Barnabas, Turne we agayne, ande visite we oure breþer bi alle þo cytes in þo whiche we han preched Goddes worde, ande see we how þei hafe hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.37" type="verse">Ande Barnabas wolde take Iohn wiþ hem, þo whiche es surnamed Marchus.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.38" type="verse">Ande Poule preyed Barnaban, þat he þat departed fro hem fro Pamphilye ande wolde noghte go wiþ hem in warke of þo gospelle, þat he schulde noghte be taken wiþ hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.39" type="verse">Ande so amonge hem was made discencyone, in so myche þat
<seg id="b.ACT.15.3" type="verse">9Ande þei, whanne þei wore forþe-ledde of þo disciples9 , þei passed þurghe Fenyce ande Samarye, tellande þo conuersacyone ande þo lifynge of nacyons: ande þei made myche ioye to alle þo breþer.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.40" type="verse">Ande Poule toke wiþ hym Sylam ande wente his waye, whanne he was bytaken vnto þo grace of God of þo breþer.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.41" type="verse">Ande he wente þurghe Sirye ande Cylyce, confermande þo congregacyone of holy chirche, &amp; bade hem þat þei schulde kepe þo biddynges of þo apostuls ande of þo eldars.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.4" type="verse">Ande whanne þei come to Ierusalem, þei wore receyued of þo congregacyone ande of þo apostuls ande þe eldars, ande þei tolde what God hade done wiþ hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.5" type="verse">Ande þanne ros vppe summe of þo heresie of þo Pharisees, þe whiche trowed, ande saide þat hit byhoued hem forto be circumcided ande alsso forto bidde to kepe þo lawe of Moysi.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.6" type="verse">&amp; þo apostuls ande þo eldars wente togider to auyse of þis worde.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.7" type="verse">Ande whanne grete aschinge ande sechinge was of þis þinge, Peter ros vppe, ande saide vnto hem, Ȝhe men, oure breþer, ȝhe knowe þat fro elder days in vs God haues chosen bi my mouþe nacyons to here þo worde of þo gospelle ande forto trowe.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.8" type="verse">Ande he, þat knewe þo herttes of alle, bere wytnes vnto þis, gifande vnto hem þo Holygoste as to vs.
<seg id="b.ACT.15.9" type="verse">Ande noghte he departed (or, made difference) bitwixe hem ande vs, clensande in þo faiþe þo hertes of hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.5" type="verse">þat ȝhe haue harde, he saide, bi my mowþe: for forsoþe Iohn baptised in water, forsoþe ȝhe schal be baptised þurghe þo Holigoste noghte myche efter þise dais.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.10" type="verse">Ande onone as he hade sene þis vision, we þoghte to go into Macedonye, for we were certayne þat God called vs to preche to hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.11" type="verse">Ande we schipped from Troade, ande righte course we come vnto Samotrache ande
<seg id="b.ACT.16.12" type="verse">þo nexte daye to Neapolym; ande fro þeþen vnto Philyppis , þo whiche es þe firste of þo contree of Macedonye, þo cyte of Coleyne : ande we wore in þis cyte certayn days techande.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.13" type="verse">Ande in þo day of sabbate we wente wiþouten þo ȝhate biside þo flode, where preynge semed forto be; ande þere we sete, and speke vnto wymmen þat þider come togider.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.14" type="verse">Ande a womman whos name was Lydda , a purpurere of þo cyte of Thiathire, þo whiche worschipped God, herde vs: whos herte God opunde, forto biholde vnto þo þinges þat wore saide of Poule.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.15" type="verse">Ande whanne sche was baptised, hire howse, she preyed, sayande, If ȝhe deme me trewe vnto God, enteres into my howse, ande dwelles þere . Ande sche gartte vs.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.16" type="verse">Ande hit bifelle, whanne we wente forto preye, þat a wenche þat hade a spiritte of a wycche mette vs, þo whiche gafe grete wynnynge vnto lordes by dyuynynge.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.17" type="verse">Sche folowed Poule ande vs, criande ande sayande, Þise men ben þo seruantes of þo highe God, þo whiche schewen to ȝowe þo waye of hele.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.18" type="verse">Þis sche did many days; ande Poule mournande for hire, he turned hym ande spake vnto þo spiritte, I bidde þe in þo name of Iesu Criste to go oute fro hire. Ande þo yuel spiritte wente oute of hire in þo same howre.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.19" type="verse">Ande whanne hire lordes see, þat þe spiritte of was away, þei toke Poule ande Sylam, ande ledde hem forþe
<seg id="b.ACT.16.1" type="verse">Ande whanne þei hade gone abowte þise nacyons, he come vnto Derben ande Lystram: ande þer was a discipul, þat was called Tymothe, þat was a trewe wydowe sone; bot his fadir was a panyme.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.20" type="verse">into þo market vnto þo princes, ande schewed hem to þo magistrates, sayande, Þise men sturbulen ande deceyue
<seg id="b.ACT.16.21" type="verse">alle oure cytee, for þei ben Iewes, ande þei tellen a maner þat es noghte leffulle to vs to receyue or do, siþen we ben Romaynes.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.22" type="verse">Ande þo puple ranne agayn hem, ande þo magistrates, þer cloþes torne, ande comanded hem forto be beten wiþ ȝerdes.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.23" type="verse">Ande whanne þei hade beten hem longe, ande made hem fulle of wondes , þei put hem in prisone, ande bade vnto þo kepar of þo prison þat he schulde bestly kepe hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.24" type="verse">Ande he, efter þat he was boden , he putte hem in þo inner prisone, ande he strayned þer fete in a tree.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.25" type="verse">Bot atte þo mydnyghte
<seg id="b.ACT.16.26" type="verse">ande sodenly was made a grete erþe-schake, so myche þat þo grownde of þo prisone stired .
<seg id="b.ACT.16.27" type="verse">Ande he þat kepped þo prisone, drowe oute a swerde, ande wolde haue slayne hymseluen, supposande þat alle þo prisons wore gone oute.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.28" type="verse">Ande Poule cried vnto hym wiþ a grete voyce ande saide, Do þe no harme : for we alle ben here.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.29" type="verse">Ande he toke lyghte, ande enterde into þo prisone, ande quakande he felle
<seg id="b.ACT.16.2" type="verse">To hym bere trewe wytnes þoo þat wore in Lystris ande Yconye.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.30" type="verse">downe to þe fete of Poule ande Silas; ande he broghte hem forþe ande saide, Leue lordes, whatte bihoues me forto do þat I myghte be saufe?
<seg id="b.ACT.16.31" type="verse">Ande þei saide vnto hym, Trowe in oure Lorde Iesu, ande þow schal be saufe ande al þi howse.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.32" type="verse">Ande þei preched vnto hym þo worde of God ande to alle þat wore in his howse.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.33" type="verse">Ande þo kepar of þo prisone toke hem in þo same houre of þo nyghte, ande wesche þer wondes; ande onone he was baptised, ande alle hise howse alsso.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.34" type="verse">Ande efter þat he hade broghte hem into hise howse, he sette a borde to hem, ande he was gladed wiþ alle house, trowande to God.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.35" type="verse">Ande whanne daye was comen þo magistrates sente baylys (or, bedels), sayande , Late þoo men goo. &amp; þo kepar of þo prisone tolde þis vnto Poule, þat
<seg id="b.ACT.16.36" type="verse">þo magistrates han sende þat ȝe ben laten go: ande þerfore gos nowe forþe in pees.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.37" type="verse">Ande Poule saide to hem, Þei hauen beten vs 17vnrightly ande vndampned17 , ande we ben men of Rome , ande priuely þei
<seg id="b.ACT.16.38" type="verse">putte vs oute; noghte so, bot come þei hemseluen ande putte þei vs oute. Ande þo bedels (or, þo baylyes) tolde þise wordes to þo magistrates: ande þo magistrates, whanne
<seg id="b.ACT.16.39" type="verse">þei harden þat þei wore Romaynes, dredde hem; ande come
<seg id="b.ACT.16.3" type="verse">Hym wolde Poule þat schulde go with hym; ande he toke hym ande circumcyded hym for þo Iewes þat wore in þo places: for alle wiste wele þat hise fadir was a gentile (or, a paynyme).
<seg id="b.ACT.16.40" type="verse">Ande þei outegoande of þo prisone þei enterde into Lyddam: ande whanne þei sawe þo breþer, þei tolde hem whatte God hade done wiþ hem, ande comforþed þo breþer ande wente on þer way.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.4" type="verse">Ande as þei passed bi cytes, þei tawghte hem þo techynges þat wore ordeynde of þo apostuls, whanne þei wore at Ierusalem.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.5" type="verse">Ande þo chirches wore confermed in þo faiþe, ande encresced in nowmbur alle daye.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.6" type="verse">&amp; as þei passed þurghe Phrigye ande Galace , þei wore
<seg id="b.ACT.16.7" type="verse">letted of þo Holygoste to speke Goddes worde in Asye; ande whanne þei wore comen vnto Misy, þei assayde to passe by Bethenye; ande þei wore letted bi þo spiritte of Iesu.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.8" type="verse">Ande whanne þei passed Misye, þei wente vnto Troyden.
<seg id="b.ACT.16.9" type="verse">Ande in þo nyghte was a visione schewed vnto Poule, þat a man of Macidonye stode, ande preyed hym, ande sayde, Go into Macedonye, ande helpe vs.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.6" type="verse">Þerfore þei þat wore komen togader asched hym, ande saide, Schalt þou in þat tyme restore þo kengdome of Israel ?
<seg id="b.ACT.17.10" type="verse">Ande þo breþer one in þo nyghte lete Poule ande Sylam into Beram ; ande whanne þei wore comen þider, þei enterde into þo synagoge of þo Iewes.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.11" type="verse">Ande þise men of Beroam
<seg id="b.ACT.17.12" type="verse">Ande many trowed of hem; ande grete multitude alsso of honeste wymmen þat were gentyles (þat es, of þo nacyones þat wore called gentyles) , ande many men alsso.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.13" type="verse">Ande whanne þo Iewes þat wore in Thessalony knewe þat Goddes worde was preched in Beroam of Poule, þei come þider 4ande stirde ande stourebulde4 myche of þo puple.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.14" type="verse">Ande onone þo breþer lefte Poule, þat he myghte goo vnto þo see: and Syle ande Tymoþe dwelled þere.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.15" type="verse">Ande þo breþer þat wente wiþ Poule þei broghte hym to Athenys; ande he bade hem þat als sone as þei come to Syle ande Tymothe þat þei schulde saye hem hastely to come to hm .
<seg id="b.ACT.17.16" type="verse">Ande Poule whileste he abode hem in Athenys, his spiritte was gretely stired in hym, for he sawe þat þo cytee was gifen to ydolatrye.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.17" type="verse">Ande he disputed in þo synagoge wiþ þo Iewes ande þo dwellande , in þo market, by alle þo days, to hem þat wore neghe .
<seg id="b.ACT.17.18" type="verse">Ande summe Epichurens ande Stoycens ande philysofers disputed wiþ hym. Ande summe saide, What wole he þis sower of wordes saye? ande oþer saide, Hit bisemes þat he es a schewar of newe fendes: ande þis þei saide for he schewed vnto hem Iesu ande þo resurreccyone.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.19" type="verse">&amp; þei toke hym, ande ledde hym to þo Ariopage (þat es, to a strete of Athenys, where þo philisofers studied), ande þei saide, Maye we knowe þis newe doctrine þat þow spekes of?
<seg id="b.ACT.17.1" type="verse">Ande whanne þei hade gone bi Amphibolym ande Appollonye, þei come to Thessalony, were a synagoge of
<seg id="b.ACT.17.20" type="verse">Newe þinges þow bringes in oure eres, ande þerfore wole we knowe what þei may be.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.21" type="verse">Ande þo men of Athenys &amp; oþer comelynges þat dwelled þer, gafe þer entente vnto noghte elles bot forto say or forto here summe newe þinge.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.22" type="verse">Ande Poule stode vppe in myddes of þat towne (or, strete), ande saide, Ȝhe men Atthenyenses,
<seg id="b.ACT.17.23" type="verse">For I haue passed ande sene ȝoure mawmetes, &amp; I fonde an auter in þo whiche were writen þise wordes, To þo vnknowne god. Ande þerfore þat ȝhe worschipe vnknowande, þat schewe I vnto ȝowe.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.24" type="verse">Þo God þat made þo worlde ande alle þinges þat ben in þo worlde , he siþen he es Lorde of heuen ande erþe, he wonnes noghte
<seg id="b.ACT.17.25" type="verse">in temples made wiþ hende ; nor he es worschipped wiþ mennes hende for þat he has nede of any þinge þat man dos, siþen he gifes vnto alle life, ande wynde, &amp; inspiringe, ande
<seg id="b.ACT.17.26" type="verse">alle oþer þinges; ande of one þinge he maked alle mankynde forto inhabyte on alle þo face of þe erthe, ordeynande certayne
<seg id="b.ACT.17.27" type="verse">tymes ande termes (or, endes) of þer habitacyone; forto seche þer God, If in aunter þei may drawe hym to hem or
<seg id="b.ACT.17.28" type="verse">fynde hym, þofe he be noghte ferre fro icheone of vs: for in hym we life, ande in hym we stire , ande in hym we ben; as summe of ȝoure poetes has sayde, Ande we ben alsso hise kynne.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.29" type="verse">Ande siþen we ben þo kynne of God, vs owe noghte to suppose þat þat purtenes vnto God es lyke to golde, ande syluer, or to stone of þo crafte of grauynge, ande þat comes of mannes þenkynge ande of mannes hondewarke .
<seg id="b.ACT.17.2" type="verse">Iewes was: ande Poule, as he was wonte, enterde vnto þem, ande by þre sabbates he preched to hem of holy scriptures,
<seg id="b.ACT.17.30" type="verse">Ande God þat despices þo tymes of þis ignorawnce, nowe he schewes
<seg id="b.ACT.17.31" type="verse">to men þat icheone, whersoeuer þei be, do penaunce: for þat he has ordeynde a daye, in þo whiche he schal deme alle þo worlde in euenhede, gifande faiþe vnto alle in a man þat he raysed fro deþe.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.32" type="verse">Ande whanne þei harde þo resurreccione , summe scorned hym; ande summe saide, We schal here þe efte of þis.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.33" type="verse">Ande so Poule wente fro þo myddes of hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.34" type="verse">Ande summe wente wiþ Poule, ande trowed vnto hym: in whom was Dyonyse þo mayster of þo
<seg id="b.ACT.17.3" type="verse">declarande ande shewande, þat hit bihoued Criste to suffur ande to rise fro þo deþe; ande þat he þis es Iesus whom I schewe vnto ȝowe.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.4" type="verse">Ande summe of hem , ande wore ioyned vnto Poule ande to Sylas; ande alsso of þo gentyles grete multitude, ande many noubul wymmen.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.5" type="verse">Ande summe of þo enuyous Iewes token summe ille men of þo puple, ande gadured a grete companye, ande stired þo cyte agayne þo apostuls, ande wente vnto þo house of Iason forto brynge hem forþe vnto þo puple.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.6" type="verse">Ande whanne þei fonde noghte hem, þei drowe Iason ande summe breþer vnto þo princes of þo cite, criande ande sayande, Þise ben þei þat stiren alle þo worlde 15ande hider þei come15 ;
<seg id="b.ACT.17.7" type="verse">ande he þis Iasone receyued hem: ande alle þise done agayne þo ordynawnce of þo Cesar, ande sayne þat þer es anoþer kenge þat highte Iesu.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.8" type="verse">Ande þei stired gretely þo puple ande þo princes of þo cites þat harde þise þinges.
<seg id="b.ACT.17.9" type="verse">Ande whanne Iason ande oþer hade made satisfaccyon (or, excusinge) to þo princes of þo cyte, þei lete hem go.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.7" type="verse">Ande he saide soþely unto hem, Hit es noghte ȝoures to knowe þo tymes (or, hit falles noghte to ȝowe) ande þo momentes, þo whiche my Fader has putte in his power.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.10" type="verse">bot speke, ande be noghte stille; for-whi I am wiþ þe, ande none schal be putte to þe þat schal noye þe: for myche folke es to me ande myne in þis cyte.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.11" type="verse">Ande Poule sete þer a ȝhere ande sexe moneþes, techande amonge hem þo worde of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.12" type="verse">Ande whanne Gallyo was þe proconsul of Achaye, þo Iewes ros wiþ one hertte agaynes Poule, ande ledde hym
<seg id="b.ACT.18.13" type="verse">to þo sete of þo domes-man, sayande, þat he þis agaynes
<seg id="b.ACT.18.14" type="verse">Ande as Poule biganne to opun his mouþe to speke, Gallyo saide vnto þo Iewes, Ȝhe men, Iewes, if hit wore any wikked þinge or grete mysdede, rightly schulde I susteyne (or, suffure) ȝowe.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.15" type="verse">Bot if hit be bot questions of þo worde ande names of ȝoure lawe, auyse ȝoure-seluen, for I wole noghte be iuge of þise .
<seg id="b.ACT.18.16" type="verse">Ande he made hem go from hise demynge-place.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.17" type="verse">Ande þo Iewes token one Sostynen, þat was prince of þo synagoge, ande þei smote hym bifore hise sete of dome. Ande Gallyo roghte
<seg id="b.ACT.18.18" type="verse">noghte þeroffe, (ande toke no kepe þeroffe.) Ande Poule made his haylsinge to þo breþer, ande schipped vnto Sirye, &amp; wiþ hym ȝode Priscille ande Aquila, þo whiche Priscille hade dodded his heued; for so hade he vowed.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.19" type="verse">Ande Poule come vnto Ephesum, ande lefte hem þere; ande he enterde into þo synagoge ande disputed wiþ þo Iewes.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.1" type="verse">After þise Powle wente fro Athenys, ande come vnto Corynthum.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.20" type="verse">Ande þo disciples preyde þat he lenger tyme schulde dwelle. Bot he assented
<seg id="b.ACT.18.21" type="verse">noghte, bote bade hem fare wele, ande saide, Efte I schal come to ȝow, if God wole. Ande so he wente fro Ephesum.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.22" type="verse">Ande goande to Cesarye, he haylsed þo chirche þat þore was, ande so he wente vnto Antioche.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.23" type="verse">Ande whanne he hade ben þore a certayne tyme, he ȝode his waye, ande wente by ordure þurghe þo contree of Galace ande Phrigye, confermande alle þo discipuls.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.24" type="verse">&amp; a Iewe whos name was Apollo, of Alexander borne, an eloquente man ande conynge scriptures, come vnto Ephesum.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.25" type="verse">He þis was tawghte þo waye of God; ande he was feruente in spiritte, ande teched besily þinges þat wore of Iesu Criste; ande onely he knewe þo bapteme of Ioon.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.26" type="verse">He þis biganne tristely to do in þo synagoge. Ande whanne Priscille ande Aquyla harde hym, þei toke hym vnto hem, ande besily expowned to hym þo waye of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.27" type="verse">Ande whanne he wolde go vnto Achaye, þo breþer wrote vnto þo discipuls, þat þei schulde receyue hym: ande
<seg id="b.ACT.18.28" type="verse">þat trowed; ande gretely he ouercome þo Iewes, opunly schewande bi scriptures þat Iesu Criste was.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.2" type="verse">Ande þer he fonde a Iewe, ande hise name was Aquila, þat late come fro Ytalye wiþ Priscille his wife, for Claudynes hade biden þat alle þe Iewes schulde goo oute
<seg id="b.ACT.18.3" type="verse">of Rome: ande vnto hem he wente; ande for he was offe þo same crafte þat þei wore of, he dwelled wiþ hem ande wroghte; ande þei were of þo crafte of makynge of tabernacles (or, of cordes ande ropes).
<seg id="b.ACT.18.4" type="verse">Ande he disputed in þo synagoge in iche sabbote , ande euermore in his saynge he menged ande sette þo name of Iesu, ande he ammonested þe Iewes ande þo Grekes.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.5" type="verse">Ande whanne Sylas ande Tymothe weren comen fro Macedonye, Poule was besy in prechinge, berande wytnes vnto þo Iewes þat Iesu Criste was.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.6" type="verse">Ande whanne þo Iewes agaynsaide Poule wordes blasphemed , he schoke his cloþes ande saide, Ȝoure blode be vpon ȝoure heued , for I am clene of þis: I schal go to þo naciones.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.7" type="verse">Ande he wente fro þeþen , ande enterde into þo house of one þat was called Tytus, þo whiche was rightwise ande worschippande God. Ande his howse was ioyned vnto þo synagoge.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.8" type="verse">Ande Crispus, þat was maister of þo synagoge, trowed vnto God wiþ alle hise howse; ande many of þo men of Corynthi þat harde Poule trowed, ande wore baptized.
<seg id="b.ACT.18.9" type="verse">Ande God saide by a visione in þo nyghte vnto Poule, Drede noghte,
<seg id="b.ACT.1.8" type="verse">Bot ȝhe schal take vertewe comande fro abouen vnto ȝowe of þo Holygoste into ȝowe: ande vnto me witnesses ȝhe schal be in Ierusalem, ande in al Iury ande Samarye, ande vnto þo ferreste ande laste of erþe.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.10" type="verse">Ande þis he dide bi twoo ȝere; in so myche þat men þat wonned in Asye harde þo worde of God, boþe þo Iewes ande gentiles.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.11" type="verse">Ande
<seg id="b.ACT.19.12" type="verse">many vertewes did God by þo hende of Poule: in so myche þat men broghten sudaries girdels from hise body, ande layde hem vpon þo seke, ande þe sekenes wente fro hem, ande þo wikked spirittes wente oute of men .
<seg id="b.ACT.19.13" type="verse">Ande summe of þo exorcistes of þo Iewes þat wente aboute, assayde forto calle þo name of Iesu vpon hem þat hade yuel spirittes, &amp; saide, We coniure ȝowe bi Iesu whom Poule preches.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.14" type="verse">Ande þer wore in a house of a Iewe, þat was prince of prestes, seuen sones þat diden þis.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.15" type="verse">Ande þo wikked spiritte ansuerande
<seg id="b.ACT.19.16" type="verse">Ande þo man in whom þo fende was lepe to hem, ande he hade maisterschippe of boþe, ande was myghtye agayne, in so myche þat wonded ande naked þei fledde fro þo house.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.17" type="verse">Ande þis was made knowne vnto alle þe Iewes ande gentiles þat dwelled atte Ephesy; ande grete drede felle vpon alle hem, ande þei loued þo name of oure Lorde Iesu.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.18" type="verse">&amp; many of þo trowande come, schriuande, ande schewande þer dedes.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.19" type="verse">Ande many alsso þat vsed curiostes broghte þer bokes, ande brente hem bifore alle: ande whanne þei hade acownted þo price of hem, þei fonde money of fifty thowsande penyes (þat es, so myche wore þei worþe in price).
<seg id="b.ACT.19.1" type="verse">Ande hit bifelle, whanne Apollo was at Corynthy, þat Poule hade gone þo ouer contrees, ande kome vnto Ephesum;
<seg id="b.ACT.19.20" type="verse">Ande so wexe þo worde of God ande was confermed.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.21" type="verse">Ande whan þise wore ended, Poule purposed in spiritte to go vnto Macedonye ande Achaye , ande so forto goo vnto Ierusalem, ande saide to hymseluen, þat efter þat I haue ben þore, me bihoues to see Rome.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.22" type="verse">Ande he sende two of þoo þat mynisterde unto hym, Tymothe ande Eraste, into Macedonye, ande he dwelled vnto a certayne tyme in Asye.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.23" type="verse">Ande in þat tyme was grete turbacione of þo waye of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.24" type="verse">For one, whos name was Demetrye, þat was a siluer-maker, ande made þo thabernacles of þo goddes Dyane of syluer, he gafe vnto þo
<seg id="b.ACT.19.25" type="verse">warke-men grete money, ande called hem togider, ande saide vnto hem þat wore of þat crafte, Ȝe men, ȝhe wyten wele þat of þis crafte es oure getynge ande lyuynge.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.26" type="verse">Ande ȝhe seen ande heren, þat noghte onely at Ephesum, bot alsso alle þo multitude of Asye, he þis Poule bi his techinges haues turned, ande teches, þat þoo ben noghte goddes þat ben made
<seg id="b.ACT.19.27" type="verse">wiþ hende : ande noghte onely schal oure crafte perische ande be in reproue to vs; bot alsso þo temple of þo grete Dyane, oure goddes, schal be destroyed ande broghte to noghte, ande hire mageste schal be vndone, þo whiche alle Asie ande alle þo worlde worschippes.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.28" type="verse">Ande whanne þise
<seg id="b.ACT.19.29" type="verse">Ande þo cyte was fulfilled wiþ confusione: ande wiþ one hertte þei made an hastines into þo spectacle; ande þore þei toke Gaye ande Aristarke, men of Macedonye, þo felowes of Poule.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.2" type="verse">ande he fonde summe of þo disciples, ande saide vnto hem, If ȝhe haue taken þo Holygoste trowande? Ande þei sayde to hym, Bot we haue noghte harde if þo Holygoste es. Ande Poule saide, In whom þanne ben ȝhe baptised?
<seg id="b.ACT.19.30" type="verse">Ande Poule wolde haue gone into þo puple, ande þo discipuls wolde noghte suffure hym go .
<seg id="b.ACT.19.31" type="verse">Ande summe of þo princes of Asye, þat wore hise frendes, sente vnto hym 5ande preyed hym5 þat he schulde sytte atte þo spectacle.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.32" type="verse">Ande summe cried ande saide oþerwise; ande þo chirche was confused , ande many wiste noghte for whatte cause þei wore comen togider.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.33" type="verse">Ande þei wiþdrowe Alexander fro þo company, þe Iewes puttande hym forþe. Ande Alexander made token of cylence wiþ hise honde, in wille forto schewe hise skille to þo puple.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.34" type="verse">Ande onone as þei knewe þat he was a Iewe, onone was bot as one voice of alle, fully two houres cryande, Þo grete Dyane of Ephesye.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.35" type="verse">Ande whanne þe scribe hade stilled þo companyse , he saide, Ȝhe men of Ephesie, whatte man es þat þat knowes noghte þo cytee of Ephesie worschippar of þo grete Diane, ande of Iouys hire childe?
<seg id="b.ACT.19.36" type="verse">Ande siþen none may agaynesay þis, hit bihoues ȝowe to be stille, ande to do no þinge folily.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.37" type="verse">For ȝe han broghte hider þise men, þat noþer are fownden giltye, nor blasphemares of ȝoure goddes.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.38" type="verse">Bot if Demetryus, ande þo warke-men þat ben wiþ hym, haue any cause agaynes any, gider hem wiþoute-forþe ; ande þer ben proconsuls, late hem accuse þem togider bifore hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.39" type="verse">Ande if any oþer þinge be þat ȝhe asche, in þo lawful chirche hit may be assoyled.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.3" type="verse">Ande þei saiden, In þo bapteme of Iohn.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.40" type="verse">Ande we ben in perele to be reprehendid of þo sedicione of þis daye, siþen þere es none blame-worþi, of whom we may gife skille (or , wyte) of þis concourse. Ande whanne he hade saide þis, he lefte þo chirche.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.4" type="verse">Poule saide, Iohn baptised in bapteme of penaunce þo pupul, techande, þat þei schulde trowe in hym þat was to come efter hym, þat es, in Iesu.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.5" type="verse">Ande whanne þei hade harde þis, þei wore baptised in þo name of oure Lorde Iesu Criste.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.6" type="verse">Ande whanne Poule hade laide on hem hise hende , þo Holygoste come vpon hem; ande þei speke wiþ tunges ande prophecyed.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.7" type="verse">Ande alle þo men wore nerehande twelue.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.8" type="verse">Ande Poule entered into þo synagoge, ande tristely he speke by þree monythis, disputande ande techande of þo kengdome of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.19.9" type="verse">Ande for summe were indurate ande wolde noghte trowe, waryande þo way of God bifore þo multitude, he, goande fro hem, departed þo discipuls, disputande iche daye in þo scole of a tyraunte fro þo houre of sexte to þo houre of tenne.
<seg id="b.ACT.1.9" type="verse">Ande whanne he hade saide þise þinges, hem seande, he was lifte vppe; ande a clowde toke hym fro her eyghne.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.10" type="verse">Ande whanne Poule come vnto hym, he laye vpon hym, 16ande he clipped hym16 , ande saide, Bes noghte droued ; for his sowle es in hym.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.11" type="verse">Ande þanne Poule ȝede, ande breke brede ande ete; ande whan he hade ynowghe spoken, vnto þo day was comen, so he wente forþe hise waye.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.12" type="verse">Ande þo men þat were þer broghte þo childe Eutyce lifande, ande þei wore gretely comforþed.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.13" type="verse">Ande we wente into a schippe ande schipped into Asson, for þer schulde we fynde Poule: for so ordeyned he, forto make hise way bi þo londe.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.14" type="verse">Ande whanne he fonde vs, alssone fro þeþen he wente vnto Mitylene.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.15" type="verse">Ande fro
<seg id="b.ACT.20.16" type="verse">For Poule purposed forto ouerschippe Ephesum, þat he schulde noghte be taried in Asye. For he hastud, þat, if hit wore possibul, he myghte make þo day of Pentecoste atte Ierusalem.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.17" type="verse">Ande fro Milete he sente vnto Ephesum, ande he clepud þo moste worþi of þo chirche.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.18" type="verse">Ande whanne þei were comen vnto hym, ande þei ande he wore togider, he saide vnto hem, Ȝhe knowe how I hafe ben wiþ ȝowe in alle tyme , fro
<seg id="b.ACT.20.19" type="verse">þe firste daye in þo whiche I enterde into Asye, ande how I haue serued to God in alle mekenes, ande myldnes, &amp; teres, ande temptaciones þat han fallen vnto me of þo waytynges
<seg id="b.ACT.20.1" type="verse">Ande efter þo grete noyse was stilled, Poule called þo discipuls, ande ammonested hem, ande bade hem fare wele;
<seg id="b.ACT.20.20" type="verse">of þo Iewes: ande how I haue noghte wiþdrawne fro ȝowe any profitabul þinge þat ne I haue schewed vnto ȝowe,
<seg id="b.ACT.20.21" type="verse">ande tawghte ȝowe opunly &amp; bi ȝoure howses, wytnesande to þo Iewes into God penaunce, ande faiþe into oure Lorde Iesu Criste .
<seg id="b.ACT.20.22" type="verse">Ande lo , I, þat am nowe bownden in spiritte, go into Ierusalem, noghte knowande what schal
<seg id="b.ACT.20.23" type="verse">bifalle to me in hit, bot þat þo Holygoste wytnes to me be alle þo cytes, sayande , þat bondes ande tribulaciones abiden me in Ierusalem.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.24" type="verse">Bot I drede no þinge of þise, nor I make my life more preciouse þanne meselfe, whileste þat I ende my course ande mynisterynge of þo worde, þat I haue taken of oure Lorde Iesu Criste, forto wytnes þo gospelle of þo grace of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.25" type="verse">Ande lo, nowe I wote þat ȝhe schal nomore see my face, ȝhe alle, bi whom I haue passed ande preched þo kengedame of God.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.26" type="verse">Ande þerfore I wytnes ȝowe þis daye, þat I am clene fro þo blode of ȝowe alle.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.27" type="verse">Forwhi I haue noghte letted, þat ne I haue schewed alle þo counseyle of God to ȝowe.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.28" type="verse">Takes kepe þerfore vnto ȝoure-seluen ande to alle þo flokke, in þo whiche flokke þo Holygoste haues sette ȝowe bischoppes, forto guuerne his chirche, þe whiche he boghte bi hise owne blode.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.29" type="verse">For I wote þat efter my disses schal
<seg id="b.ACT.20.2" type="verse">Ande whanne he hade gone þo contrees, ande hade ammoneste hem wiþ
<seg id="b.ACT.20.30" type="verse">spare vnto þo flokke of God; ande of ȝoure-seluen schal rise men, spekande mys þinges, þat þei may lede disciples efter hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.31" type="verse">Wharfore bes ware ande waker, ande holdes in mynde þat bi thre ȝere nyghte ande daye I cessed noghte wiþ teeres monestande icheone of ȝowe.
<seg id="b.ACT.20.32" type="verse">Ande nowe I komaunde ȝowe vnto God, ande to þe worde of his grace, þo whiche es myghty to edifye, ande forto gife heritage in alle hise halowes .
