<seg id="b.ACT.21.24" type="verse">Wiþ vs ben foure men þat has on hem owe ; take þise, ande halow þe wiþ hem, ande gife þow in hem þat þei schaue þer heuedes: ande alle 11schal knowe, þat what þei haue harde of þe ben fals; bot alsso þei11 schal knowe, þat þow gos ande kepes þo lawe.
<seg id="b.ACT.21.25" type="verse">Ande of þoo þat trowen of þo nacyons, we haue writen, demande þat þei abstene hem fro þinge þat es sacrified vnto idoles, ande fro blode, ande fro beeste þat es chokud in blode, &amp; fro fornycacyone.
<seg id="b.ACT.21.26" type="verse">Thanne Poule toke þise men, ande whanne he was purde þo nexte daye efter he wente wiþ hem into þo tempul, schewande þo fulfillynge of þo dais of þo purificacyone, vnto þat offeringe wore offerde for icheone of hem.
<seg id="b.ACT.21.27" type="verse">Ande whan þo seuen dais wore ended, þo Iewes þat wore of Asie, whanne þei see hym in þo temple, þei stired alle þo puple, ande keste
<seg id="b.ACT.21.28" type="verse">þer hondes on hym criande, Ȝhe men of Israel, helpes: þis es þo man þat teches in iche place alle maner of men agayne þo puple, þo lawe, ande þis place : &amp; alsso he haues broghte þo gentiles into þo temple, ande has filed þis holy place.
